title: fresh raspberry crisp
directions: Place raspberries in bottom of a 9-inch square microwave-safe cake pan.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Blend margarine, flour, brown sugar and oats until mixture resembles coarse meal. Sprinkle the oat mixture over the raspberries.
Microwave on Medium (50% power) for 5 to 10 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes. Serve warm or cold.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions; drain.
Grease a 1-quart casserole dish.
Place broccoli, 1/8 cup butter and cheese in dish.
Add milk.
Combine crackers with remaining 1/8 cup butter.
Sprinkle over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter and simmer chopped onion while cooking broccoli in microwave.
Cook rice as directed.
Drain broccoli.
Mix all ingredients and pour into large casserole dish.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.

title: crock pot roast
directions: Place meat in crock pot and pour envelope of onion soup mix over meat.
Pour soup over meat.
Cover with water.
Add peeled potatoes and carrots.
Cook on high for 6 - 8 hours.

title: baked clams on half shell
directions: In medium nonstick skillet, brown garlic, onion, parsley and oregano in oil.
Add bread crumbs; continue to brown and stir. Add clams; toss to heat through.
Pour in clam juice; toss just to heat.
Spoon into bakeable half shells.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Serve with lemon wedge.

title: meat-potato dinner
directions: Melt Crisco in skillet.
Cut steak into small cubes and flour; now add to Crisco in skillet and brown.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Put into a casserole and sprinkle with the 3 tablespoons flour, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and some garlic salt. Pour the 2 cups water over this.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for about 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and place potatoes on top. Sprinkle with salt and paprika.
Turn oven to 450°.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: baked squash
directions: Cook bacon crisp. Saute onion and squash in grease with salt and pepper until done.
Combine egg and sour cream.
Stir in half the bacon.
Add to the squash and stir.
Spoon half the squash in a baking dish and sprinkle with half the cheese.
Add remaining squash.
Top with remaining cheese and bacon.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Several hours in advance, mix softened cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning mix.
Spread on large platter or quiche type dish.
Cover with drained salsa or taco sauce, then chopped lettuce, tomatoes, onion and shredded Cheddar.
Serve with Doritos or Tostitos.

title: country stew
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef; drain off excess fat.
Cut frankfurters into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Add frankfurter pieces to beef along with undrained mixed vegetables, tomato sauce, water and Sloppy Joes seasoning mix.
Cook and stir until mixture is hot and bubbly.
Serve with chunks of crusty bread.

title: chicken and swiss casserole
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Place Swiss cheese over chicken.
Pour soup over all. Bake at 350° for 2 to 3 hours.

title: sweet potato treat
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Add potatoes, milk and vanilla. Mix until thoroughly blended. Place in a buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Cover with a topping made by crumbling together brown sugar, flour, pecans and margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger and onion.
Mix in taco seasoning and 1/2 tomato sauce and put aside.
Mix beans and remaining tomato sauce.
Crumble 1/2 of tostados in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Next, make layer of hamburger mixture and sprinkle 1/2 of Cheddar cheese over it.
Make layer of refried beans and tomato sauce and top with rest of shells.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Cook 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Serve topped with lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, etc.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: homemade bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, salt and milk together and bring to a boil.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add to mixture.
Add flour gradually.
Place in greased bowl and let rise until double in size.
Turn dough onto floured board and knead well.
Divide and place in greased pans.
Cover and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 small loaves.

title: best ever pie crust
directions: Cut the shortening into the flour and salt.
Add the soda; mix until mixture forms a ball.
This will keep several days in the refrigerator.

title: baked bluefish new england style
directions: Leave fish whole.
Season inside and out.
Mix crumbs, onion, herbs and butter, adding a little milk or fish broth if stuffing seems too dry.
Stuff fish; secure with skewers or toothpicks. Slit skin of fish several times to prevent bursting.
Lay 2 slices pork in heated baking pan.
Place fish on top; dredge with flour. Cover with third pork slice and place in hot oven.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes per pound.
Baste as soon as fat runs and continue to baste every 8 to 10 minutes until done, which will be in about 3/4 hour.

title: beefy round steak
directions: Will need enough aluminum foil to go under and on top of steak.

title: new orleans shrimp salad
directions: Cook rice, drain and cool. Drain and cut shrimp in half. Chop pepper and onions fine. Separate cauliflower into sections, olives in slices. Mix shrimp, rice, vegetables and lemon juice. Add rest of seasoning and mayonnaise.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie crust.
Fill it with strawberries.
Combine water, sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon on stove; stir until it boils.
Add strawberry gelatin.
Chill in refrigerator for 3 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: noodle pudding(kugel)
directions: Melt butter; mix with noodles (cooked).
Beat remaining ingredients together and add noodles and butter.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes with mixer.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: fast turkey casserole
directions: Layer tortilla chips, turkey, onion, green chilies, half the cheese, tomatoes and rest of cheese in a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish. Combine soup and milk in a bowl.
Mix well.
Pour over layers. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Heat together in double boiler, flour, 1 Tbsp. butter and sugar.
Add Cheddar cheese and sour cream to double boiler mixture; heat until blended together.
Mix with broccoli, place all in baking pan and top with corn flakes which have been sauted with remaining 2 Tbsp. butter.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour.

title: honey-mustard chicken and eggplant
directions: Heat broiler.
Arrange chicken pieces skin side down and eggplant rounds on broiler pan rack.
Brush all with half the bottled sauce.
Broil 4 to 6 inches from heat source 8 minutes. Turn chicken over.
Brush with remaining sauce.
Broil 8 minutes longer or until chicken is hot and glazed and eggplant is tender.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Fill casserole with egg halves.
Add 2 pounds cooked, cooled and peeled shrimp to sauce and pour over eggs.
Saute 2 cups soft fine bread crumbs in 1/4 cup butter until brown.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: strawberry fantasy
directions: Brown margarine, brown sugar, nuts and flour in baking dish for 15 minutes at 350°.
Stir 3 or 4 times.
Put half of crumbs aside for topping and press remaining crumbs in dish for crust.

title: company vegetable casserole(yields 8 servings)
directions: In a bowl, combine beans, corn, soup, sour cream, cheese and onion.
Pour in an ungreased 2-quart baking dish.
Combine margarine and crumbs; sprinkle over vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Beat eggs together, then mix in the remaining ingredients. Pour into a large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until browned.

title: double chip cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat butter or margarine, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs; beat well.
Stir together flour and baking soda; blend into sugar mixture.
Stir in peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Yields 5 dozen cookies.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine; add eggs, one at a time, and continue beating.
Add soda and cinnamon to flour.
Alternate flour and sour milk to first mixture.
Last, add apples.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Chop artichokes.
Mix all ingredients together in a bowl by hand.
Pour into a greased baking dish (quiche size does well). Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: shrimp spread(teacher favorite)
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve as spread with bland crackers.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a medium size bowl; stir to mix well.
Remove 1/2 cup of the mixture to small bowl; mix with the water until smooth.
Cut shortening into remaining flour mixture in medium size bowl until mixture resembles coarse meal; mix in flour-water mixture until well blended.
Shape into ball.
Wrap dough in wax paper.
Refrigerate while preparing apple filling.

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: In large bowl, mix peanut butter, corn syrup and confectioners sugar.
Add powdered milk.
Knead until smooth.
Mold dough into any shape.
Eat when finished.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: In a bowl, mix together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening. Mix in milk.
Roll out onto floured board.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake in a preheated 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: gravy baked pork chops
directions: Sprinkle chops with salt and pepper.
In a 10-inch skillet, brown in hot shortening.
Pour off drippings.
Pour around the chops the soup mixed with milk and water.
Cover and cook chops and gravy about 45 minutes over low heat, stirring now and then, until chops are tender.
If desired, place in baking dish and bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Stir gravy well.
When the chops are done, the gravy's made.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients together until sticky.
(If too runny, add a little more flour.)
Place into hot liquid and cook, uncovered. Done when they float to the top of pan.

title: virginia bethea's cheese wafers
directions: Mix shortening and cheese with hands until very soft.
Add sifted flour.
Mix well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Pinch walnut size amount of dough; make into balls.
Press down with fork.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes on cookie sheet.

title: summer pasta
directions: This dish can be served warm or cold. To serve warm add all ingredients while pasta is still hot and serve.
To serve cold, rinse pasta in cool water, drain add other ingredients and chill. Serves 8 to 10.

title: pretzel cream salad
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients and press into a glass dish 8 x 8 x 2-inches.
Bake 10 minutes at 325°.
Cream the cream cheese, sugar, crushed pineapple and Cool Whip; set aside.
Take pineapple juice and cornstarch; cook until thick.
Spread on top of crust and then spread cream cheese mixture on top of second layer.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain and rinse the three cans of beans.
Mix in the other ingredients.
Add a little celery seed and parsley if you like.

title: caramel icing
directions: Brown 1/2 cup sugar in a heavy saucepan.
Add cream.
When the mixture comes to a boil, add the remaining sugar.
Stir with a wooden spoon constantly for 15 minutes.
Add flavor and butter and cook another 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven
Place sheets of foil on countertop for cooling cookies. Combine shortening, peanut butter, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg.
Beat just until blended. Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix just until blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten slightly in crisscross pattern with tines of fork.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until set and just beginning to brown.
Do not overbake.
Cool 2 minutes on baking sheet.
Remove cookies to foil to cool completely.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: so easy sugar cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat 3/4 cup sugar, margarine, oil, milk, almond extract and egg until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt; blend well.
Spread evenly into an ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan; sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool 5 minutes.
Cut diagonally into bars.

title: sour cream clam dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Serve chilled.

title: tuna spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Makes 1 1/2 cups (enough for about 48 crackers).
Serve on Melba rounds or crackers.

title: coconut fluff cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients 3 times.
Cream butter and add sugar gradually.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Add flour alternatively with milk, small amounts at a time.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Fold in egg whites quickly and thoroughly.
Pour into prepared cake pan and bake at 375 degrees 20-30 minutes.

title: sticky buns
directions: Spread frosting over the bottom of an oblong pan. Put a Hershey's Kiss in each biscuit and wrap it around. Seal at top. Lay each biscuit over frosting. Bake at 350° until done or about 35 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Cool slightly and set aside.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add Jell-O, beating well.
Stir in pineapple and baby food.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour mixture into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish; cover and chill until firm.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix together thoroughly eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Add flour, cinnamon, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix together until blended and pour into a jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Use toothpick test for done.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix well.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 9 minutes.
Very good!

title: steak and potato soup
directions: In separate pot, cook vegetables in salted water until tender. Add cooked meat.
Add instant mashed potatoes as thickener. Correct seasoning.
Cool for about 1/2 hour and stir in half and half cream.

title: oreo shake
directions: Mix into your blender the ice cream, milk and Oreo cookies; blend for 5 to 10 seconds.
Pour into cup and serve.
Makes 1 shake.

title: scalloped chicken and spaghetti
directions: Heat fat; add onion, garlic and mushrooms and cook about 10 minutes or until soft and lightly browned.
Add flour and stir until blended; slowly add stock and stir over low heat until thick and smooth.
Season to taste.

Add chicken, tomatoes and cheese. Arrange chicken mixture and spaghetti in layers in a greased casserole; top with buttered bread crumbs and a dash of paprika. Bake in oven at 375° for about 25 minutes or until browned.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in a glass jar airtight. To use, mix 1 rounded teaspoon mix with a cup of boiling water. Makes a soothing cup of tea.

title: pastry
directions: Make Crisco and flour mix into pea size pebbles; add 2 tablespoons ice water (1 at a time).
Roll in a ball and put in wax paper in the freezer.
When ready to use pastry, let thaw and roll between wax paper with rolling pin to size large enough for the 9-inch pie pan.
I like to bake in Pyrex pie pans.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine apples with 2 tablespoons flour and white sugar. Spread in bottom of pan. Blend butter with brown sugar, 1/2 cup flour and oats. Spread over apples in pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until brown on top. Serve warm with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Soften butter and mix soda, vanilla, white sugar, brown sugar and eggs together.
Next, mix in peanut butter, then put in half the flour and mix, then the other half of the flour and mix.
Form into balls and flatten on a cookie sheet with fork dipped in white sugar.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cranberry salad(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Make Jell-O according to package, using only 1/2 amount of water.
Let cool and gel slightly.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in boiling water.
Combine and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Wash 8 large cabbage leaves.
Steam until limp.
Mix remaining ingredients well.
Spoon 1/8 of mixture in each leaf.
Start rolling from core end.
Fold side of leaf to center.
Pour rolls, seam side down, into an 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Dissolve 1 chicken bouillon cube in 1 cup water; pour over rolls.
Cover and cook until fork-tender (about 350° in oven for about 35 to 45 minutes).

title: peach jubilee pie(texas style)
directions: Combine peach filling, 2 tablespoons of sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Let set.
Then combine using mixer, Cool Whip and 1/4 cup sugar.
Whip until stiff; then add sour cream.
Place half of peach mixture into already baked pie shell; then pour all of Cool Whip mixture on top of peach mixture.
Top Cool Whip mixture with rest of peach mixture.
Chill about 2 hours.

title: peach schnapps cake
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a greased tube or Bundt pan.

title: wild rice and chicken casserole
directions: Prepare rice as directed on boxes. Spoon into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: momma's mustard chops
directions: Wash chops thoroughly.
Pat dry with paper towel. Spread mustard over chops (both sides). Sprinkle garlic over each chop. Dip in flour until well coated.
Place in frying pan over medium heat for approximately 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: peanut pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and peanut butter.
Add confectioners sugar; fold in Cool Whip and put in crust.
Freeze.

title: orange fool
directions: Using only 1 1/2 cups milk, cook pudding according to package directions.
Cover pudding surface with waxed paper to keep skin from forming; chill.
Stir peels and juice until well blended. Fold in the whipped cream.
Makes 6 servings.
Contains 172 calories.

title: tomato basil tart
directions: Bake pie shell until brown.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese and cool.
Cut tomato into wedges and drain on paper towel. Arrange wedges atop melted cheese in the pie shell.
In food processor, combine basil and garlic; process until coarsely chopped and then sprinkle over tomatoes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry.
In medium bowl, stir together spinach, sour cream, mayo, soup mix, water chestnuts and green onions; cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Makes 3 cups.
tags: Knorr Swiss mix vegetable soup mix

title: easy beef goulash
directions: Heat oil in a 10-inch skillet over moderately high heat (about 300°).
Add ground beef and cook until lightly browned, stirring occasionally with a fork to break up meat.
Drain off any excess fat.
Sprinkle uncooked noodles over meat.

title: split pea soup
directions: Combine ingredients in slow cooker.
Cover and cook on low 10 to 12 hours.
Remove ham bone; cut meat off, dice and return meat to soup.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fast and easy chili
directions: In a 2-quart microwave dish, combine onion, celery and chili powder.
Add 1 tablespoon water.
Cover and microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and cook on High 6 to 8 minutes, stirring once.
For spicier chili, add hot pepper sauce to taste.

title: italian burger melt
directions: Shape and brown beef patties and drain fat.
Add soup and 1/3 cup water.
Cover and cook 10 minutes or until patties are no longer pink.
Top with cheese and serve on rolls.

title: vegetable beef bone soup
directions: Brown soup meat and bone.
Add onion, salt and pepper and water.
Cover and simmer over low heat until meat is tender, 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Strain off the beef broth.
Add remaining vegetables to the broth and simmer slowly until vegetables are tender, about 1 hour.
Cut cooked meat from bones into small pieces and add to soup.
Serve with crusty bread.
Serves 16.

title: hamburger stew
directions: In a large thick pot, brown crumbled hamburger.
Add all other ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until the raw potatoes and onions are done.
Stir often.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Heat first 4 ingredients to boiling; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add pectin.
Stir well.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Pour into canning jars and seal.

title: savannah red rice
directions: Cook bacon and sausage; saute onions and pepper until tender in drippings.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Combine egg whites and water.
Beat until frothy (puffy).
Add nuts.
Combine sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add sugar mixture to nut mixture.
Stir to coat.
Line a jellyroll pan or cookie sheet with oiled brown paper (shopping bag cut to size will work).

title: green bean salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and pour Italian dressing over mixture.
Chill.
Just before serving, add lettuce and mix well.

title: rich and slim dip
directions: Stir the lemon juice into the cottage cheese, mixing well. Add the buttermilk and the mayonnaise; beat for 1 minute at medium speed with mixer.
This dip is excellent with raw vegetables, and it is a delicious low calorie topping for baked potatoes.

title: butter sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat butter in large bowl until fluffy. Slowly add sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg yolk and extracts.
Combine dry mixture into creamed mixture.
Form dough into ball.
Wrap in plastic.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: no cook banana dessert
directions: Add sugar to buttermilk and stir until sugar is dissolved. Fold in mashed bananas, nuts and Cool Whip.
Freeze.
Thaw slightly before serving.
Garnish with some chopped nuts.

title: aunt reggie's apple cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugar. Add flour, cinnamon and baking soda. Add nuts and apples. Pour into 9 x 13 pan (greased) and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool. Enjoy!

title: noodle beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Brown meat in oil.
Drain and add tomato sauce.
Remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, onions and green pepper and mix well.
Spread 1/2 the noodles in greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover with cheese mixture and top with remaining noodles.
Spread meat mixture on top.
Cover and bake at 350°
for 30 minutes until fluffy.

title: stuffed turkey roll
directions: Follow Stove Top directions as on box.
Place turkey in baking dish and fill with stuffing.
Fold over and seal with a toothpick, then pour gravy over the top and place in oven at 350° for 15 minutes or place in microwave for 7 minutes depending on power.

title: caramel layer choco-squares(cookies)
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In mixing bowl, combine dry cake mix, butter, 1/3 cup milk and nuts by hand.
Stir until dough holds together.
Press 1/2 of dough into prepared pan. Reserve remaining dough for topping.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes. Sprinkle chocolate pieces over baked crusts.
Spread caramel mixture over chocolate pieces.
Crumble reserved dough over caramel mixture.
Return to oven and bake 15 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Refrigerate 30 minutes to set caramel.
Cut into squares.

title: banana-nut salad
directions: Place whole chicken, half of bell pepper, celery and onion in stock pot.	Add water to 3/4 to almost full not to boil over.
Boil until chicken is very tender (1 hour).
Remove chicken bones and skin from the pot.	Return chicken back to the pot with sausage and the remaining of the bell pepper, celery, onion and seasonings. Cook on medium high heat for 15 minutes.
Add the crab and let cook for 15 more minutes.
Add the shrimp and let it cook for 10 minutes.
Add the oysters and turn heat to simmer.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and form balls.
Put in freezer for a few minutes.
When they are firm, put in bags.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together.
Stir in applesauce.
Add dry ingredients.
Add raisins and nuts last.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: pumpkin pie(diet)
directions: Note:
I
heat	the milk in the microwave until boiling for the scalding.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and drain. Saute onion and celery in pan. Cook broccoli as directed on box and drain. Add jar of cheese and soup. Mix well. Add rice, onion and celery. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rosie's super limas
directions: In Dutch oven, saute celery and onions in margarine until soft.
Add water and limas; cook until tender.
Add remaining ingredients except mushrooms.
Stir until thickened, then add mushrooms.
Pour into greased casserole.
Cover and bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: christmas ornaments(nonedible)
directions: Stir in saucepan until smooth.
Then heat to boiling and boil 1 minute or until consistency of mashed potatoes.
Pour onto board covered with cornstarch and knead.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 200° for 2 hours.
Decorate with acrylic paints and using clear glue, add sparkles, metallic yarn, etc.

title: punch bowl fruit cake
directions: Cook cake mix.
Let cool.
Crumble cake in bottom of punch bowl.
Mix vanilla pie filling and milk.
Add cherry pie filling. Add strawberry pie filling to vanilla mixture.
Beat well and pour over cake.
Pur pineapple over this.
Spread Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Add cherries.
Sprinkle with pecans and chill.

title: oven fried zucchini spears
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
On shallow plate, combine all ingredients, except zucchini and oil; set aside.
Slice off ends of zucchini. Cut each zucchini lengthwise into quarters.
Cut each quarter in half.
In large plastic bag, combine oil, zucchini and 2 teaspoons water.
Close bag and shake well to moisten zucchini. Dredge zucchini in bread crumb mixture.
Arrange zucchini in single layer on nonstick baking sheet.
Bake until golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: "big blues"(muffins)
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Grease the cups of muffin tin (12 cup or 8 cup).
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a bowl and set aside.
In a large bowl with mixer at medium speed, combine butter and sugar until well blended.
Add eggs and beat until smooth. Add flour mixture and milk, beating until well blended.
Stir in blueberries.
Spoon into prepared cups.
Sprinkle tops with sugar and bake 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 12 medium or 8 jumbo muffins.
Only 310 calories and 9 grams of fat.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on box.
Drain.
Put broccoli in casserole dish.
Combine and blend mayonnaise, soup, cheese and eggs.
Pour mixture over broccoli.
Top with Pepperidge Farm dressing with herbs.
Melt 3/4 stick of margarine and pour on the top.
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown on top at 400°.

title: asparagus cashew casserole
directions: Thin soup with small amount of milk; heat.
Layer in 1 1/2-quart casserole asparagus, crackers, eggs, cheese soup; add remaining milk and sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: beef and mushrooms oriental
directions: Saute beef, about 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms and broth and peppers; simmer until tender.
Combine soy sauce with cornstarch. Blend until smooth and thickened.
Serve with steamed rice or noodles.
Pork may be used; use beef broth.
Chicken or turkey; use chicken broth.

title: no name shrimp dinner
directions: In saucepan, bring 1 1/2 cups salted water to boil. Stir in rice; cover and simmer over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender and water is absorbed. Remove from heat; stir in egg white and 1 tablespoon of the parsley. Press mixture into bottom of greased 8-inch square baking dish or other shallow heatproof casserole with same volume; set aside.

Meanwhile, in nonstick skillet, melt 1 tablespoon of the butter over medium-high heat. Cook garlic, mushrooms and celery, stirring for about 5 minutes or just until vegetables start to brown. Stir in onions, dill and 1/3 teaspoon each of the salt and pepper; cook over high heat for about 2 minutes or until lightly browned. Transfer to large bowl. Wipe out skillet. Pour in 2 cups water and bring to simmer. Cook shrimp for about 1 minute or just until pink. Reserve 1 cup of liquid; rinse shrimp under cold running water. Shell and devein shrimp; arrange over rice in baking dish.

title: light as feather muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Blend in beaten egg. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to mixture, adding milk as you mix.
Pour into well-greased muffin cups filling 2/3 full.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes in quick moderate oven, 375°.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, syrup, salt and butter in a 2-quart heavy saucepan.
Stir over moderate heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture boils.
Cover and cook slowly five minutes.
Uncover and boil rapidly to soft ball stage, 238°.
Let stand until cold. Add vanilla and beat until candy loses its gloss and begins to hold its shape.
Stir in nuts and turn into a buttered pan.
Cut in squares when set.
Makes about 2 1/4 pounds.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: blueberry pie filling
directions: Put blueberries, sugar, 1/2 cup water, lemon juice and salt in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Add cornstarch that has been dissolved in 1/4 cup water.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Place in uncooked prepared pie crust.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Heat 2 Tbsp. of oil in a skillet.
Fry eggs and reserve.

title: foundation sweet dough
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Scald milk and remove from heat.
Add shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Add yeast, eggs and 2 cups flour.
Beat well.
Add remaining flour or enough to make soft dough.
Knead lightly and place in a greased bowl.
Cover and set in a warm place to rise.
Let rise to double in bulk.
Punch down and shape into rolls.

title: frosting with granulated sugar
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick, stirring constantly, then cool. Cream the sugar, butter and vanilla until very fluffy. Add to first mixture.
Mix until well blended.
It should be the consistency of whipped cream. Frost cake.
This recipe is wonderful to make when you're out of powdered sugar.

title: wendy's chicken curry
directions: In a large kettle, saute onion in oil until clear and brown. Add curry powder and pepper.
Fry for 15 minutes on low.
Add tomato sauce and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add chicken pieces.
Stir to coat.
Cook on low for 20 to 30 minutes, covered, stirring occasionally.
Add vinegar.
Stir.
Serve over rice.

title: beef cream cheese casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, pepper and sugar.
Saute green onions.
Mix softened cream cheese, sour cream, noodles and onions together.
Assemble casserole with a layer of the beef mixture on the bottom, all the noodle and sour cream mix and the rest of the beef mixture.
Heat until bubbly at 325° to 350°, then add cheese to the top and heat until the cheese melts.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and put in crust.
Bake until set and pastry is brown, 40 to 50 minutes in 375° oven.

title: ole timey egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° until set and slightly brown (around 30 minutes).

title: microwave cocoa
directions: Mix together cocoa, sugar and salt.
Add vanilla and a small amount of the milk.
Stir until smooth; add remaining milk
and microwave at High (100%) until almost boiling, approximately 2 minutes.
Stir to blend ingredients well.
Serve immediately.
If desired, marshmallows may be put on top before serving.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice according to package directions. Saute onion in margarine. Mix all ingredients together and place in a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rosemary's round steaks
directions: Place steaks in an ovenproof, covered pan.
Add the ginger ale, onion soup mix and the cream of mushroom soup.
Roast 2 hours at 350°.
It makes its own gravy.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Combine all ingredients except for the cheese until creamy. Shape into 1 inch balls.
Roll in cheese.
Cover and refrigerate until serving.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Melt 1/2 pound butter.
Take off heat.
Add 1 box of 10x sugar, then add 3/4 cup peanut butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Place in buttered dish in fridge.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Mix cocoa in small amount of scalded milk.
Add flour, sugar and salt.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Add egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Cover with meringue and refrigerate.

title: lentil patties
directions: Mix and form patties.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve plain or with gravy.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice and 2 cups water, following package directions.
Set aside.
Saute the onion in a little cooking oil.
Add egg, cooked rice, 1/3 cup water and soy sauce.
Mix well.

title: mamma's peanut pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, eggs and milk.
Cook until thickened, stirring often to keep from sticking.
Add peanuts and vanilla. Pour into cooled baked shell.
Add meringue and brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil.
Sift together dry ingredient, flour baking soda, baking powder, salt, nutmeg cinnamon and add to egg mixture.
Fold in zucchini and nuts. Grease 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk chocolate sheet cake(with buttermilk icing)
directions: Sift together flour and gran. sugar. In saucepan, bring to a boil the butter, cocoa, and water. Combine the two mixtures. Add rest of ingredients, stir together. Pour into greased and floured jellyroll pan. Bake 20 minutes at 400° F. Cake remains in pan and should cool only slightly before WARM icing is poured over it.

title: fresh apricot pie
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Add water, just enough to hold together.
Use a little over half for bottom crust.

title: perfect pasta supper
directions: Melt butter in large frying pan over medium-low heat.
Stir in cream, egg yolks, onion and seasonings until well blended.
Do not boil.
Stir in cheeses until melted.
Add pasta, stirring, until thoroughly blended.
Spoon immediately onto warmed serving plate. Sprinkle with ham.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and peanut butter over low heat to boiling.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let stand until firm, about 1 hour.
Yields 24 servings.

title: sausage and rice
directions: Brown and crumble meats.
Drain and set aside.
Combine broth, water and soy sauce.
Bring to boil.
Add rice.
Cover and let rise 5 minutes.
Remove cover and fluff.
Stir in meat and nuts.

title: holly holiday appetizer balls
directions: Thaw spinach, draining well.
Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into 1-inch balls; place on ungreased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen balls.

title: potatoes mozzarella(serves 8)
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and put half of them into a greased 2-quart casserole.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix kraut, celery, onions, green pepper and pimentos.
Boil sugar and vinegar 3 minutes.
Pour over other ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill overnight.

title: pink frozen dessert
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip thoroughly in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Add cherry pie filling and mix thoroughly.
Add drained crushed pineapple and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Freeze until a short time before serving.

title: beet soup
directions: Boil broth, water and onions, then add beets. Cook 5 minutes. Add lemon, salt, pepper and sugar. Put about 2 cups of beet mixture in blender. Add sour cream. Blend together, Then add back to beet mixture. Will have a light pink color. Serve when cold.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Stir sugar into apples; let set while you assemble other ingredients.
Add oil, egg and vanilla.
Stir together.
Sift flour with cinnamon and soda.
Add dry mixture; stir.
Makes 8 to 9 cupcakes.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until brown on top.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries, pineapple, bananas and chopped nuts.
Pour half of the mixture in an 8-inch mold and let set.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice in water.
Fry celery (remove when done).
In same frypan, fry onions (remove when done).
In same frypan, brown meat (remove when done).
In same frypan, scramble eggs.
Mix all together with rice and use soy sauce to taste.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes; mix through while baking.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Follow directions on box for cake like brownies, adding 1 cup chopped walnuts.
Spread into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Bake or boil the potatoes.
Mash.
Mix in sugar (use 1/2 cup first, more if necessary), butter, eggs, vanilla and milk.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt butter and mix in brown sugar, flour and nuts.
Sprinkle on top of sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: green goddess dressing
directions: Process mayonnaise, yogurt, lemon juice, vinegar, parsley, tarragon, white pepper and garlic in a blender until smooth.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Mix rice, 1/2 cheese and 1 egg; pat into pie pan, sprayed. Layer favorite vegetables, salt and pepper.
Mix eggs and milk; pour over vegetables and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 3 servings.
Each serving counts 1 bread, 2 1/3 protein and 10 optional calories.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Bake uncovered.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Defrost strawberries; drain.
Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and oil; stir until dry ingredients are moistened and well blended.
Fold in strawberries and pecans. Spread batter into 2 lightly greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Let set overnight before serving.

title: stately coconut layer cake
directions: Cream the shortening. Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture; mix well. Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done. Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove and cool completely.

title: gran's tamale soup
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion; drain off excess grease. Add tomatoes, beans, corn and cumin.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes. The last 10 minutes, add tamales.
Serve with grated cheese on top.
Recipe makes a lot, but ingredients can be easily divided for half as much.

title: pecan crescents(wedding cookies)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for 2 hours.
Shape mixture into small balls and then form them into crescent shapes. Bake on ungreased cookie pan at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: benny's tortilla soup
directions: *May substitute 3 pints of water and 7 chicken bouillon cubes.

title: vic's skillet surprise
directions: In wok or skillet, brown onions and green peppers.
Brown steak pieces.
Mix gravy mix with amount of water that package indicates.
Add gravy to steak mixture in skillet.
Cover and let simmer.
Serve over rice.

title: spinach potato bake
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: At high speed beat eggs with sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in oil and pumpkin to blend well.
Sift flour, spices, salt and baking soda together; then at low speed blend flour mixture with batter just until combined.
Pour into ungreased 9 inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy caramel popcorn
directions: Put popcorn in large roasting pan.
Into a large saucepan, mix sugar, oleo, corn syrup and salt.
Stir over medium heat until boiling.
Continue boiling without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and soda.
Stir quickly and pour over popcorn, coating all well.
Bake in preheated 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring several times.
Can be left in oven to cool.
When thoroughly cooled, break into pieces.
Yummy!
Store in a covered container.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Sprinkle garlic salt and cayenne pepper over top.

title: pepper steak
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place oil, beef, onion, tomato and garlic in 1 1/2-quart casserole and cover.
Cook until meat has lost its pink color.
Stir occasionally.
Dissolve cornstarch in water with soy sauce and sugar.
Put over meat.
Add green pepper. Cook until peppers are tender yet slightly crisp.
Serves over rice.
Serves 9.

title: pineapple crumb cake
directions: Mix pineapple, water and sugar in a large baking dish. Sprinkle cake mix on top.
(Do not mix.)
Slice butter on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Mix and store.
Use 2 rounded teaspoonfuls per cup of hot water.

title: strawberry nut bread
directions: Place strawberries in a bowl, sprinkle with sugar and let stand until thawed.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine butter flavor Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until creamy.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda; mix into creamed mixture until just blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecan pieces.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls (about 2 measuring tablespoons of dough) 3 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies (cookies will appear moist; do not overbake) or 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Cool on baking sheet for 2 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack.
Makes 3 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: glazed brie
directions: In small bowl, stir together the sugar, nuts and whiskey or brandy.
Place cheese on ovenproof platter or 9-inch pie plate. Bake at 500° for 4 to 5 minutes, or until slightly softened. Sprinkle top of cheese with sugar mixture.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes longer, until sugar is melted and cheese is heated through.
Brush apple with lemon juice.
Serve with apples, grapes and crackers.

title: never fail yeast rolls
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until light and fluffy.
Add boiling water, mixing thoroughly.
Set aside to cool.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually add sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into crusts.
Add cherries.
Chill until set, 2 hours.

title: chocolate-vanilla rum cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan. Sprinkle nuts over bottom.
Follow directions on box for chocolate portion. Pour vanilla portion over nuts.
Drop chocolate batter by tablespoons over vanilla and run knife around pan to swirl, being careful not to disarrange nuts on bottom.
Bake 1 hour, cool and invert on plate.
Prick top with long toothpick and drizzle over top and sides.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Prepare popcorn; pour into a large buttered bowl.
Heat oven to 200°.
Heat sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt, stirring occasionally, until bubbly.
Continue cooking 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda until mixture is foamy.
Pour over corn; stir until coated.
Divide into two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 5 minutes.
Cool and store in a canister.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix all together and pour in greased pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350°.

title: mediterranean pasta salad
directions: Process oil, vinegar, 2 tablespoons basil, green onion, Parmesan, salt and pepper in blender or food processor until smooth.
Put pasta, bell pepper strips, tomato wedges, nuts and olives in large bowl.
Pour in dressing; toss to mix.
Roll cheese cubes in remaining 2 tablespoons basil to coat.
Add to salad; sprinkle with oregano.
Toss lightly.
Serve at room temperature. Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: old-time spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cream the margarine with sugar and egg.
Add yeast and water to the mixture.
Mix in flour 1 cup at a time to make a spongy batter.

title: pizza by the yard
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread on French bread.
Place in broiler for 10 to 15 minutes at 450° or until meat is done and browned.
Top with tomatoes and cheese slices.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: oreo ice cream cake
directions: Press 3/4 of cookie crumbs into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with vanilla ice cream.
Pour chocolate syrup on top and cover with Cool Whip.
Top with rest of Oreo crumbs.
Freeze.

title: sugar-free banana cake
directions: Boil water and raisins until water is absorbed; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot-oat bran muffins
directions: Mix oat bran, flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt together.
Mix moist ingredients together.
Now mix all ingredients together.
Fill baking cups 3/4 full.
Bake 20 to 22 minutes or until golden brown at 400°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim excess fat from steak.
Partially freeze steak.
Slice across grain into thin strips.
Combine flour and pepper, mixing well.
Dredge meat in flour and set aside.
Spray Dutch oven with cooking spray.
Add oil; heat until medium hot.
Add mushrooms and onions, cover and cook 5 minutes until tender, stirring frequently. Remove vegetables and save.
Add meat to Dutch oven; turn heat to medium high and cook until browned.
Stir in mushrooms and onions and remaining ingredients except yogurt (or sour cream) and noodles.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Uncover and simmer 15 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and stir in yogurt (or cream).
Heat.
Do not boil.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and salad dressing.
Add other ingredients. Chill.
Shape into ball or wreath.
Decorate with parsley flakes or nuts.

title: bisquick coffee cake
directions: Roll out dough in two 8 x 12-inch rectangles 1/4-inch thick. Place on cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Spread any kind of your favorite preserves down the middle of the dough.
Cut dough down each side in strips of 1-inch and brush across the preserves. Can be frosted with powdered sugar frosting.

title: upside-down plum-pecan pie
directions: Cut 15-inch circle from heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Line pie plate, 9 x 1 1/4-inches, with foil circle, leaving 2 inches overhanging edge.
Spread margarine over foil lining.
Place pecan halves, rounded sides down, on foil.
Mix brown sugar and corn syrup.
Drop by small spoonfuls evenly over pecans and buttered foil.
Heat oven to 450°.
Prepare pie crust mix as directed on package.
Roll one round pastry into 11-inch circle.
Ease into pie plate over pecans and brown sugar mixture.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour into pastry-lined plate.
Roll other round of pastry into 12-inch circle.
Fold in fourths; cut slits so steam can escape.
Place over filling and unfold; seal and flute.
Turn up overhanging foil to catch bubbling juices and to prevent crust from excessive browning.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: diabetic oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then mix the liquid.
You can also use crushed pineapple instead of the raisins.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken hash
directions: Saute green pepper and onion until soft.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a casserole and set in oven to heat.
Make a biscuit dough and drop by spoonful on top of chicken mixture. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 425°.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Cover bottom of 11 x
15-inch
pan with crumbs.
Slice ice cream over crumbs and top with
chopped
peanuts.
Freeze
until firm.
Melt chocolate chips and butter.
Add
confectioners
sugar and
evaporated milk.
Cook over medium heat until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add
vanilla. Cool mixture and pour over ice cream.
Freeze until firm.
Before serving, slice bananas and top with Cool Whip.
May be stored in the freezer for several weeks.

title: blueberry-orange bread
directions: Melt butter in boiling water in small bowl.
Add orange juice and rind.
Beat egg with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add sifted dry ingredients, alternately with orange juice liquid, beating until smooth.
Fold in berries.
Bake in a 1 1/2-quart loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Bake at 325° about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Turn on rack.
Mix 2 tablespoons of orange juice, 1 teaspoon rind and the honey.
Spoon over hot loaf and let stand until cool.

title: soup from leftover roast
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and celery in oil.
Add roast and gravy if any.
Add Veg-All, V-8 juice, bay leaves, salt, pepper, sugar, thyme, bouquet garni, Worcestershire powder or sauce and beef bouillon crystals or cube.
Add 2 to 4 cups water.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer 2 to 3 hours, covered.

title: break-away bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; let stand 5 minutes.
Combine boiling water and shortening in a large mixing bowl.
Beat with a wire whisk until shortening dissolves.
Add sugar, eggs, salt and yeast mixture; mix well.
Gradually stir flour into batter. (Dough will be very soft.)
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar, blend well.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each.
Add flour, flavoring and lemon juice.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: grilled veal chops
directions: Preheat an outdoor grill or a broiler.
Place the veal chops in a shallow dish and season with salt and pepper.
Combine the oil with Herbes de Provence and brush lightly over both sides of the chops.
Allow to sit for 15 to 20 minutes at room temperature. Grill the chops for 5 to 6 minutes per side or until the desired degree of doneness.
Serve hot, garnished with parsley or other fresh herbs.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs, then combine them with the rest of the ingredients.
Bake in a floured pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: czechoslovakian goulash
directions: Heat oil in a large stew pot, add sliced onion and minced garlic and cook until tender but not brown.
Add 2 Tbsp. of paprika, blend, and cook few minutes on low heat.
Add meat, brown on medium heat, season with salt and black pepper.
Add dash of marjoram and bay leaves.
Cook on medium heat for few minutes. Add cut up tomatoes with liquid, green and red pepper, and celery chunks.
Cover tightly and cook over low heat for about 1 hour. Occasionally if needed add 1/2 cup of water.
When meat is tender, add cubed potatoes, and about 4 to 5 cups warm water.
Cover and cook until potatoes are soft.
Check seasoning.
Add freshly cut up parsley.
Serve with sourdough bread.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Partially boil potatoes. Cool and peel. Cut potatoes into quarters lengthwise and arrange in a baking dish.
Sprinkle with sugar and butter. Pour hot water over all.
Sprinkle with salt, nutmeg and cinnamon. Cook in a 350° oven until potatoes are soft and syrup is thick, about 30 minutes.

title: lazy day shortcake
directions: Prepare cake mix and bake.
Let cool, then punch holes in top with handle of wooden spoon or large fork at 1/2-inch intervals. Dissolve gelatin and pour over top of cake. Let cool, then spread Cool Whip on cake.

title: cran-apple relish
directions: Quarter and seed oranges and apples. Coarsely grind oranges, apples and cranberries. Add sugar, pineapple and nuts. Mix well. Refrigerate overnight. (Makes 2 quarts.)

title: cocoa krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine or butter in large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows; stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Add Cocoa Krispies cereal; stir until well coated.
Using a buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.
Makes 24 (2 x 2-inch) squares.

title: russian tea
directions: Squeeze juice from oranges and lemons and save juice and rinds. Boil fruit rinds, sugar, spices and water together for 15 minutes. Strain and add strained lemon and orange juice and tea.
Add pineapple juice.
Simmer.
Serve hot.
To serve cold add 1 qt. ginger ale.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream all together brown sugar, white sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in gradually flour, soda and salt.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Roll into teaspoon size balls; bake on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Butter the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle uncooked rice evenly over bottom of pan.
Place chicken pieces over rice.
Mix soups with 1 can of water.
Mix well and pour over chicken, lifting chicken pieces to ensure rice is covered with soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
An inexpensive, easy dish that feeds a large family.

title: spinach calzones
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Roll out dough to 21 x 14-inch rectangle.
Cut out 6 (7-inch) squares.
Squeeze excess water from thawed spinach, until very dry.

title: chinese chicken casserole
directions: Cook the rice.
Cook chicken breasts and cube.
Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.
You may want to add 1/2 cup milk before baking if it seems too dry.
Before baking, cover with Chinese noodles.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour red cabbage
directions: Lightly brown salt pork to remove fat.
Remove pork from pan and lightly brown onion in fat.
Combine pork, onion, cabbage and apple.
Combine juice, water and vinegar and pour directly over cabbage.
Vinegar will eliminate color bleeding from cabbage.
Add remaining ingredients and salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer three to four hours or until tender and flavors are blended.
Add more water or grape juice as needed. Do not drain.
Remove pork rind.
This is better made a day ahead.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: pizza pork chops
directions: Trim excess fat from chops; set chops aside.
In a medium saucepan, cook onion in butter or margarine until tender, but not brown.
Add stuffing mix, water and oregano to cooked onion.
Stir until well combined.

title: pork filet au gratin
directions: Cut the meat in 1-inch long strips; heat up the Crisco in a frying pan.
Lightly brown the meat.
Spice with salt and pepper and put in a heat resistant form.
Clean the mushrooms and cut them in slices.
Fry them in the leftover Crisco from the meat. Spice with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with flour; fry until brown. Pour in water and wine.
Heat while stirring.
Stir in sour cream.
Spice with mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over meat.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Put in preheated oven (400°) for approximately 15 minutes.

title: vegetable bean soup
directions: Heat oil in large kettle.
Cook onions and garlic over medium heat until onions are soft.
Add carrots.
Continue cooking and stirring.
Add water, ham bone, beans, bay leaf and potatoes. Bring mixture to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, about two hours, or until beans are tender.

title: chicken divan
directions: Arrange broccoli in bottom of buttered baking dish.
Put chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice, curry, salt, pepper and cheese.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: 4 step lemon dessert
directions: Combine butter, nuts and flour to make crust.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese with powdered sugar and fold in Cool Whip (except 1 cup).
Spread on cooled baked layer.
Combine pudding mix with cold milk.
Beat, then spread on cake.
Spread on rest of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with more pecans.

title: creamy mexican dressing
directions: Combine ingredients and stir until smooth.
Cover and chill. Makes 2 cups.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10 inch tube pan. Set oven at 350°. Sift flour and soda 3 times. Add 1/2 salt to egg whites and beat until the form a peak. Set aside. Add the rest of the salt and the vanilla extract to well creamed butter and sugar. Add one egg yolk at a time, beating well with each addition. Add flour, soda alternating with the sour cream. Fold in beaten egg whites. Pour into tube pan and bake one hour or until done.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Sift together baking powder, baking soda, flour and salt.
Fold in with lemon juice and enough milk to make 3/4 cups.
Add bananas and black walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test with toothpick.

title: hawaiian rice
directions: Chop onion into fine pieces.
Saute onion and almonds in butter until golden brown.
In a 2 1/2-quart round casserole dish, add consomme, mushroom soup, rice and onion mixture; mix well. Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake, covered, at 425° for 1/2 hour. Remove cover and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Mix.
Great served with barbecued chicken and a tossed green salad.

title: ice cream sauce
directions: In small heavy saucepan, combine syrup with chocolate kisses over very low heat.
Stir constantly until mixture is smooth. Remove from heat. Spoon sauce over ice cream.

title: strawberry chiffon squares
directions: In a small saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in vanilla wafer crumbs.
Pat mixture onto bottom of 11 x 7-inch baking dish. Chill in a large bowl, dissolve Jell-O in the boiling water.
Stir in the Eagle Brand milk and undrained strawberries.
Fold in the marshmallows and whipped cream.
Pour into prepared pan and chill for 2 hours or until set.

title: chicken n cheese enchilada
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Saute onion and margarine in a large skillet. Stir in chicken, 1/4 cup picante sauce, cream cheese and cumin. Cook until thoroughly heated. Stir in 1 cup cheese. Fill each tortilla shell with mixture. Place in baking dish and top with remaining picante sauce and cheese. Bake 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into baking dish.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes.
If appears dry, add small amount of water.

title: classic 7-up pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Heat oven to 300°.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; drain.
Add milk, half and half, onion, salt and pepper. Heat through. Slowly add chunks
of Velveeta, stirring after each addition to melt. Use low heat to avoid scorching.

title: oyster stew
directions: Put oysters in a strainer over stew pot and drain; pour 3/4 cup cold water over oysters.
Heat liquid to boiling point and skim off foam; add milk and cream and when it boils, add flour and butter that has been mixed together and is smooth.
Season with salt and pepper to taste; keep hot until ready to serve.
Before serving, bring liquid to boiling point.
Remove from heat to prevent further boiling and pour in oysters and when they have cooked enough to be plump and the edges begin to curl, serve.
If all milk and no cream has been used, double the amount of butter.
Never allow milk to reach a boil after putting in oysters, as they will be toughened and the quality of the stew spoiled.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt butter and add to brown sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour.
Batter will be stiff.
Stir in chocolate chips and pecans.
Spread in a greased and floured 10 x 15-inch pan. Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Do not overcook. Use toothpick in middle to test.
Store in plastic bag in a covered tin.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: zucchini pie
directions: In large bowl, combine 1 egg, onion and Parmesan cheese.
Stir in potatoes.
Pat mixture into a 9-inch pie plate or a 10-inch quiche dish.
Bake, uncovered, in a 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes until golden.
Cool slightly; reduce oven to 350°.
In large skillet cook zucchini in garlic and butter until just tender. Cool and arrange on crust.
In mixing bowl combine remaining 3 eggs, cheese, milk, oregano, salt and pepper.
Pour over zucchini.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix well the cream cheese and eggs. Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.

title: ranch beans
directions: Brown beef and onion in frying pan.
Mix all ingredients and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, corn syrup, salt and vanilla. Blend well but do not overbeat.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Pour into deep dish 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for about 50 minutes or until done.

title: dill pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers in quart jar.
Mix remaining ingredients; bring to boil.
Pour over cucumbers.
Seal.

title: sauerkraut(mama made this every summer, we eat it all winter.)
directions: Shred cabbage fine.
Put in large container with salt and mix well.
Pack gently in large crock or glass container with potato masher.
Repeat until full (Do not use metal containers).
Weight down with plate, cover with clean cloth.
Remove scum and wash cloth every day.
Takes 10 to 12 days to complete fermentation.

title: corn baked dish
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Add tomato soup and corn with liquid.
Mix and add noodles.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: blender pie
directions: Put ingredients into blender and whip 1 minute.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 325° for 44 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix sugar and flour; add to drained pineapple and mix well. Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with mixture of melted oleo and crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles good.

title: camper's guacamole
directions: I make this when
I
have
no
tomatoes.
It works real good with a blender, but
you
can
make it in the field also. Just mash your avocados
real fine and add enough tomato sauce to make a thick paste.
Adjust the flavor to your taste.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Drain off excess grease.
Add dry ingredients first, then the others, stirring continuously.
Then simmer over low heat for 1 hour.

title: wesson oil pie crust
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix together flour and salt.
Add all at once the Wesson oil and milk.
Stir lightly until mixed.
Round up dough, divide in halves.
Flatten each half slightly.
Roll between wax paper.
Never fails.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, cream of chicken soup and lemon juice.
Blend well, then mix together with remaining ingredients. Spread in baking dish and top with a mixture of the nuts and potato chips.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: hidden valley ranch cheese puffs
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Spread on bread slices.
Broil until puffed and golden, about 3 or 4 minutes.

title: tuna crunch casserole
directions: In a 1-quart casserole dish, blend soup and milk.
Stir in tuna, eggs and peas.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with chips and bake 5 minutes more.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: fruit milk shakes(usa)
directions: For each milk shake use 2 cups milk and either of the fruits you wish.

title: pat in pan crust
directions: Mix ingredients.
Press firmly into ungreased pie plate. Makes two 9-inch pie shells.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: lentil loaf
directions: Add lentils and barley to boiling, salted water.
Allow to boil for a minute, then reduce heat and simmer with lid ajar for about 40 minutes or until most of the water is absorbed.
Add all of the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place mixture in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Allow to cool 15 to 20 minutes before inverting over a platter to serve.
Great cold for sandwiches.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, shape into a ball or log.
Roll in chopped peanuts or pecans.
Chill.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in 3 greased and floured pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: kentucky fried chicken slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, carrot and onion.
Bring to boil other ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.

title: instant cocoa
directions: Mix all together and store in a tight jar.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt butter. Stir all ingredients together. Mix well. Bake for 1 hour and 15 min. at 350.

title: angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift flour and powdered sugar together 3 times; set aside to be used later.
Place egg whites, cream of tartar, salt and extracts in large mixing bowl; beat until foamy. Gradually add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating well after each addition.
Continue beating until egg whites are very stiff and hold peaks when lifted up.
Sift flour and sugar mixture over egg whites.
Gently fold flour mixture into egg whites until flour mixture disappears.
After last portion has been folded in, make 8 to 10 additional foldover strokes.
Use rubber scraper to push batter gently from bowl into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Cut through batter to break air bubbles.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.
When done, turn pan upside down on rack to cool.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine peanut butter, brown sugar, Crisco, milk and vanilla in a large bowl; beat at medium speed until well blended.
Add egg.
Beat just until blended.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to mixture at low speed.
Drop by heaping teaspoonful 2 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten slightly with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until beginning to brown.
Cool 2 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: pralenec grahams
directions: Separate each cracker into 4 sections.
Arrange in a jelly roll pan with edges touching.
Melt butter in a saucepan; stir in sugar and pecans.
Bring to a boil; cook 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Spread mixture evenly over crackers.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes.
Remove on pan and cool on wax paper.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Thoroughly mix shortening, egg, sugar, sour cream and vanilla.
Then add flour, salt, soda and nutmeg that have been sifted together.
Let dough chill 1 hour in refrigerator.
When chilled roll out and cut out with your favorite cutters.
Put on aluminum foil lined cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly brown around edges.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: zuppa tuscano soup(italian potato soup)
directions: Cook sausage in large skillet; drain. Cook onion and bacon; add to sausage in stockpot. Stir in garlic; add broth, water and potatoes. Cook for 25 minutes. Stir in kale and cream and cook for additional 15 minutes.

title: breakfast crunches
directions: Beat margarine, sugar and egg in large mixing bowl.
Add flour and baking soda.
Mix well.
Stir in rolled oats, cheese, peanuts and bacon or raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cooking sheets. Leave space between each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool on wire racks.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter in a double boiler.
Stir powdered sugar, cocoa, and vanilla.
Pour into pan and let set.
After it cools.
Enjoy.

title: hot chicken salad 1
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips.
Put in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole for 30 minutes in a 375° oven.
Top with potato chips.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together.
Drain.
Mix together remaining ingredients and add to squash and onion.
Pour into greased dish. Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top and then sprinkle nutmeg.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: great granny buchanan's boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine for 2 minutes in boiler on top of stove.
Start timing when mixture comes to a boil. Remove from flame.

title: 5 hour beef stew
directions: Combine in a large covered Dutch oven or large casserole dish: beef stew meat, carrots, onion, potatoes, mushrooms, tomato juice, m.s.g. or Accent, sliced celery, Minute tapioca, salt and pepper.
Bake, covered, at 250° for 5 hours.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook egg noodles and drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.

title: artichoke dip with green chilis
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix thoroughly. Pour into oven safe casserole dish. Top with additional Parmesan, if desired. Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm with "Scoop Fritos," tortilla chips or bread rounds.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping and remaining ingredients.
Spoon into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Freeze until firm.

title: norwegian pancakes
directions: Combine the eggs and light cream and beat.
Sift in flour, sugar and salt.
Let stand for 2 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Fry bacon.
Pour the batter onto a greased skillet. Add a strip of bacon in the middle immediately.
When cooked, serve topped with sugar or lingonberry jelly.
Roll up and enjoy.

title: cucumber dill sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients; refrigerate.
Serve with fish.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add flour and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add broth, broccoli and spices. Cook until broccoli is tender.
Add milk and simmer 5 minutes.
To cream, put in blender 1/4 at a time.

title: peach marmalade
directions: Cook all ingredients, except jello, for 15 minutes.
Add jello and stir.
Pour into jars.
Must put way on top to seal or you may freeze.

title: shrimp red rice
directions: Stir rice, tomato sauce, salt and pepper into rice steamer and let steam for 30 minutes.
While rice is steaming, fry bacon and brown onion in bacon grease.
Break up crisp bacon.
Pour grease, sauteed onion, shrimp and bacon into rice.
Fluff up and steam for another 30 minutes.

title: dirt pie
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and set aside.
Soften cream cheese and butter.
Mix milk with instant pudding.
Add confectioners sugar, cream cheese and butter to pudding.
Mix well.
Alternate layers of pudding and cookies in a 9 x 13-inch dish with cookie layer on bottom and top.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: baked beans
directions: Soften beans completely; drain.
Add 1 cup water.
Put beans in and add all remaining ingredients along with the water.
Mix well.
Cover and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours.

title: apple torte
directions: Cream together egg, sugar, butter and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients; add to mixture, then add apples and nuts and stir lightly.

title: swiss bliss
directions: You also need 20-inch sheet of heavy-duty wrap.

title: braised red cabbage
directions: Saute onions in oil.
Add garlic when onion is tender.
Fold cabbage into onions, along with all other ingredients.
Cover saucepan and boil 10 to 15 minutes, stirring occasionally until cabbage is just tender.
Add a little more broth or water, if liquid evaporates before cabbage is done.
Toss with parsley and serve.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a large plastic bag or bowl, add all ingredients.
Close bag and toss or shake until potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty into a shallow baking dish.
Discard bag. Bake, stirring occasionally, for 40 minutes or until golden brown. Garnish with parsley.

title: low-fat banana pudding cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonfat cooking spray.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake using Egg Beaters.
Pour in pan and bake until done.
While cake is baking, mix sugar and pineapple in saucepan.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove cake from oven.
Prick the top of cake with fork.
Pour the pineapple mixture over the top of the cake.
Cool completely.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Grate zucchini, carrots and onion.
Add pimento with liquid, soup and sour cream.
In another bowl, pour melted margarine over stuffing.
Layer vegetable mixture and stuffing to fill a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. This may be divided and frozen before baking.
Thaw and heat uncovered in microwave if you bake it first.

title: am i bleu cheese dip
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well.
Serve with assorted crackers or vegetables.

title: cheese cake tassies
directions: Cream cheese and sugar; beat well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Use tassie pans and papers and fill to top of papers.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool.
Garnish with pie filling.
Refrigerate. Makes 36 servings.

title: corn bread topped ham loaf
directions: In bowl, combine beaten eggs and milk.
Stir in soft bread crumbs and onion.
Add ground ham.
Mix well.
Pat meat mixture into 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove meat loaf from oven; drain off any fat.
Spread apricot preserves over top of ham loaf.
Increase oven temperature to 400°.
Prepare corn muffin mix according to package directions. Pour over preserves covered ham loaf.
Bake in 400° oven about 20 minutes more or until the corn bread layer is done.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Cook and stir chicken in hot oil until browned; add water, broth and vegetables and bring to boil.
Stir in rice and parsley. Return to boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 7 servings.

title: hershey's 5 minute brownies
directions: Stir cocoa and baking soda in mixing bowl.
Blend in 1/3 cup of oil, adding boiling water.
Stir until mixture thickens.
Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining 1/3 cup oil.
Stir until smooth.
Add flour, vanilla and salt; blend completely.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: jello fingers
directions: Mix Jell-O and gelatin; add boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Add lemon juice.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish. Chill at least 1 hour.
Cut into finger size strips.
Serve.

title: yummy dough(kid's recipe)
directions: Measure brown sugar and peanut butter into bowl.
Squeeze with hands.
(Hint:
If sticky, add brown sugar.
If dry, add peanut butter).
Add Granola (optional).
Explore dough freely.

title: oatmeal drops
directions: In skillet, brown oatmeal in melted margarine.
Mix other ingredients and add oatmeal.
Drop onto cookie sheet (ungreased) and bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Add shortening, half of buttermilk and mashed bananas.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add eggs and rest of buttermilk.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Fold in nuts.
Grease and flour two 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost with favorite frosting.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Stir in Lipton beefy mushroom soup mix and scant water and simmer for a few minutes.
Pour ground beef mixture in casserole dish.
Pour vegetables on meat.
Pour and spread cream of chicken soup.
Arrange Tater Tots on top and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: barbara's potatoes
directions: Mix together first 2 ingredients.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together Cheddar, sour cream and soup.
Pour over potatoes.
Mix together cornflake crumbs and butter.
Spread over top of casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes, covered, at 350°. Continue 30 more minutes, uncovered.
Can be made 3 days ahead and refrigerated.

title: mystery casserole
directions: Brown beef, onions and celery together.
Add all other ingredients.
Place in casserole.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn puff
directions: Butter a 5 cup souffle dish or a 1 1/2-quart round casserole. Cook corn as directed on package.
Drain.
Mix Bisquick, milk, egg and salt.
Stir in corn and cheese.
Pour into prepared dish. Bake 1 hour or until knife inserted half way between edge and center comes out clean.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook and cube chicken.
Chop up onion, green pepper, tomatoes and black olives; combine in a bowl.
Mix sour cream and cream cheese together.
Pour 1/2 of taco sauce and 1/2 of picante sauce in bottom of baking dish.
Spread sour cream/cream cheese mixture on tortilla shells.
Place some chicken on that with some chopped veggies on top (add chili peppers at this time) and then sprinkle Monterey Jack cheese on top.
Fold tortilla shells and place side by side in baking dish.
Pour leftover sauces over tortillas. Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Remove dish from oven and sprinkle taco mix cheese over tortillas and place back in oven until melted.

title: texas cake
directions: Bring to a boil:
2 sticks margarine, 1 cup water 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Mix eggs and sour cream.
Add flour, sugar, soda, and salt.
Add cocoa mixture while hot.
Pour into greased jellyroll pan. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: camp stew
directions: Peel and chop onion and potatoes.
Add water, boil until tender.
Chop meat and add.
Add all other ingredients except corn.
Bring to a boil.
Add corn.
Cover and leave on lowest heat until ready to serve.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate a few hours before serving. Serve with fresh vegetable strips.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil, peel and cook potatoes.
Fry bacon.
Cook onion in bacon grease until yellow.
Add remaining ingredients and cook until boils for approximately 1 minute.
Pour this over potatoes and bacon pieces.

title: sausage & cheese casserole
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll 1 can rolls into 2 long rectangles. Place in ungreased 13x9 inch glass baking dish.
Press over bottom and 1/2 inch up the sides to from crust.
Brown sausage in large skillet over medium heat until thoroughly cooked.
Remove sausage from skillet discard drippings.
Add cream cheese to the skillet by spoonfuls until it is all in the skillet and melted (very low heat).
Add sausage back to skillet with cream cheese.
Stir to coat.
Spoon evenly over crust in baking dish.
Sprinkle 2 c. of cheddar cheese over mixture.
Unroll second can of rolls onto work surface.
Press out to form 13x9 inch rectangle.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Carefully place over cheese.
Press edges to seal.
Sprinkle the rest of cheese over top.
Bake 21 -26 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas very fine.
Add sugar and beaten egg.
Mix flour sifted with soda to the banana mixture.
