Add melted butter and vanilla and chopped nuts.
Bake 1 hour in moderate oven.

title: trifle for the woman on the go!
directions: Put the frozen raspberries in a bowl and bring to boil.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, stirring frequently, until melted.
Prepare other ingredients while raspberries are cooking; wash fruit, open cans, cut pound cake into 1-inch slices and pour some liqueur onto a pie plate.
Remove raspberries from stove and strain into a bowl. Make vanilla pudding.
Make whipped cream with 1 tablespoon sugar. Smoothly stir in 2/3 whipped cream to pudding.
Line up ingredients in order:

pound cake, liqueur plate, raspberry sauce, fruit cocktail, oranges, fresh fruit, pecans and pudding mixture. In a glass bowl, layer in ingredients in this order 2 to 3 times: pound cake quickly dipped into the liqueur on both sides; raspberry sauce; fruit cocktail including some of the fruit juice on each layer; sprinkle oranges/raspberries/blueberries on top and on side in a pattern; sprinkle pecans and pudding mixture.
Put remaining whipped cream on last layer and top with raspberries/blueberries/pecans.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all and cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pie filling as directed.
Add Cool Whip and sour cream. Mix together.
Place a layer of cookies and bananas, then a layer of pudding mixture in bowl.

title: orange-cream fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, combine fruits; set aside.
In small bowl, combine dry pudding mix, milk and orange juice.
Beat with rotary beater until blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Beat in sour cream.
Fold into fruit mixture.
Cover and chill.
Makes 10 servings.

title: easy casserole
directions: In oiled baking dish, layer (in order) potatoes, corn, pepper, onion and carrots.
Crumble ground beef over the top.
Sprinkle marjoram over beef.
Top with tomato sauce, spreading evenly. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: pineapple and apricot salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water in bowl. Add cold water and 1 cup pineapple-apricot juice. Chill until partially set.
Add pineapple, apricots and pecans. Pour into 9 x 9-inch dish. Chill until firm.

title: laura's steam bell peppers
directions: Slice bell peppers into slices.
Place strips into frying pan with butter or vegetable oil.
Pour can tomato sauce into pan. Cover pan and simmer until tender.
Serves 2 to 3 people.

title: confetti biscuits
directions: Set aside 1/2 cup cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Should be stiff enough to drop from spoon onto Chicken and Mushroom Casserole.
Add rest of cheese to top and bake until biscuits are done, about 20 minutes.

title: spring delight salad
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin.
Add marshmallows; stir until melted.
Chill.
Mash cream cheese with vinegar until smooth.
Add pineapple with juice and blend thoroughly.
Add nuts.
Chill.

title: tropical pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Blend in fruit juices and bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes; remove from heat.
Stir small amount hot mixture in egg yolks.
Return to hot mixture; bring
to
a
boil
for
minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla; cool.

title: nut cups
directions: Mix thoroughly and refrigerate for at least 2 hours (can be made the night before).
Ball 24 pieces and press into small nut cups (can be in smallest paper cups).
Use fingers to form the sides and bottoms in cup.

title: homemade apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples and put in unbaked pie crust.
Add sugar and slice 1/2 stick butter on top and place second pie crust on top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: baked pears
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cut slice off bottom of pear so it will stand upright.
Place, with stem up, in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over pears.
Bake, uncovered, about 1 1/2 hours, basting 3 or 4 times.
Serve cool with syrup.

title: pineapple-rhubarb jam
directions: Remove top from pineapple; cut into wedges.
Remove rind and eyes from wedges.
Remove core.
Cut unpeeled orange and lemon into quarters; discard seeds.
Grind pineapple, orange and lemon in food chopper.
Combine fruit and sugar.
Cover and refrigerate at least 5 hours.
Cook in large kettle.
Heat to boiling, stirring frequently.
Boil gently over medium heat 25 minutes until thickened.
Fill prepared jars.
Seal jars.
Cool before storing.

title: shrimp with saffron
directions: Preheat the broiler.
Shell the shrimp and remove the vein down the back.
Rinse under cold water and dry on paper towel.
Place the shrimp in bowl and add the lemon juice from lemons and saffron. Place the parsley on a chopping surface and chop.
Add the thyme and garlic and continue chopping.
When the herbs are chopped together, add the bay leaf, finely chopped.
Add this to the shrimp and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Stir until the shrimp is well coated with the mixture.
Place the butter in a saucepan and heat thoroughly; transfer the shrimp to another pan and pour the remaining marinade into the hot butter.
Do not boil.
Broil the shrimp about 4 inches from source of heat.
As liquid accumulates in the shrimp pan, pour it into the butter mixture.
Cook the shrimp, turning once, until they are red and cooked, 4 to 5 minutes.
Do not overcook or they will toughen.
Arrange the shrimp on a warm serving dish.
Stir the butter sauce with a wire whisk while heating.
Pour the butter sauce over shrimp and serve.

title: gramma's fish batter
directions: Cut fish in 2-inch squares.
Salt and pepper to taste.
(Soak fish in salt water first.)
Mix batter and coat fish.
Fry in deep oil for 12 minutes.

title: potluck dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together; drain.
Melt cheese with soups, Ro-Tel and beans over low heat or use a crock-pot.
Use no water with soups.
Add hamburger and onion mixture.
Can be served with most any kind of chips.

title: rolls
directions: In a bowl, dissolve the yeast in 1/2 cup of water.
In a pan, melt together the water, butter, sugar and salt; mix with yeast. Add egg.
Add flour (dough will be sticky) and store, covered, in refrigerator until chilled.
Roll out dough to about 1/4 inch thick.
Cut and fold over.
Dip each in melted butter and let rise 3 hours.
Bake at 400° until lightly browned.

title: 18-hour salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order listed into a large bowl.
Spread out each layer evenly (including mayonnaise).
Cover and "marinate" overnight.

title: savory corn stuffing
directions: In large skillet, cook celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Add water and bouillon; cook until bouillon dissolves. In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Add celery mixture; mix well.
Stuff chicken or turkey loosely, or place in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until hot.

title: plain cake with fudge candy icing
directions: Sift flour with sugar into large bowl.
Add shortening and 3/4 cup of the milk.
Beat for 2 minutes on low speed, then beat at medium speed.
Add remaining milk, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into 3 (8-inch) pans, well-greased and lightly floured.
Bake in a medium oven until golden brown.

title: stir-fried beef and vegetables
directions: Trim and discard excess fat from steak.
Cut steak into very thin slices; set aside.
In small bowl, combine soup, cornstarch and soy sauce; stir to blend.
Set aside.
In 10-inch skillet or wok over medium-high heat in 2 tablespoons hot oil, stir-fry beef strips and garlic until meat is browned.
Remove from skillet. Add remaining 1 tablespoon oil to skillet.
Add green onions and broccoli; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add bamboo shoots; stir-fry 30 seconds more.
Return the beef to skillet.
Stir in soup mixture; heat to boiling.
Cook 1 minute more.
Spoon over rice.

title: southern pecan fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, heat sugar, butter, cocoa, milk, vanilla and salt over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Stir in nuts.

title: raspberry parfait pie
directions: Mix raspberry jello with water, then add the ice cream.
When it is partially jelled, add fresh or frozen raspberries.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill.

title: imperial cookies
directions: Mix together. Spoon onto cookie sheet. Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: cheesy ham 'n broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare sauce mix, noodles and broccoli according to package directions.
Then combine all ingredients in 2-quart greased casserole.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more or until heated.

title: esta berry's spice cake(1926)
directions: Mix together your ingredients in order and bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan, for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: tacos
directions: Drop tortillas in hot oil, one at a time.
After a few seconds, turn, fold in half and fry to desired crispness.
Drain well on paper towels and keep warm in low heat oven.
To serve, open each torilla gently and insert filling.
Yield: 12 servings. Carbohydrate 16 g, protein 6 g, fat 4 g, calories 124.
One serving without the meat or chicken filling, 1/2 meat high fat exchange, 1 bread starch exchange.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: In medium bowl, combine 1 cup water and 2 teaspoons salt to make salt water mixture.
In medium bowl, combine remaining ingredients except spareribs.
Mix well.
Place ribs on grill sprayed with Pam, about 5 to 7 inches above low temperature coals. Cook about 45 minutes, turning and brushing frequently with salt water mixture.
Continue cooking 15 minutes or until done, turning and brushing with maple syrup sauce.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: brown sugar sauce
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add water and butter.
Bring to a boil and cook 2 minutes.
Add vanilla.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions, garlic and salt.
Cover with ice and mix in.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly and remove garlic.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut and set aside.
Chop onion and celery very fine; grate carrot and mix all vegetables with sauerkraut.
Mix sugar and oil and mix with sauerkraut mixture.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: potato soup
directions: Place potatoes and onion in a large soup kettle.
Add water just to cover and bring to a boil.
Simmer until potatoes are just tender.
Add remaining ingredients and season to taste.
Heat through and serve at once.
Serves 4. Preparation Time:
1 hour.

title: stuffed pepper soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain. Add water, bouillon cubes and crushed tomatoes. Heat on high until boiling. Reduce heat and add all remaining ingredients, except rice. Cook for 1 to 2 hours until peppers are done to taste. Cook rice and add to soup. Cook an additional 20 minutes.

title: tuna patties
directions: Mix tuna, Egg Beaters, onion, pepper, parsley, salt and 1/2 cup bread crumbs.
Shape by 1/2 cupful into patties.
Roll in 1 cup bread crumbs and brown in hot oil, then turn heat down and put a lid on until done.
Mix soup, evaporated milk and peas.
Heat until hot.
Place tuna patties on prepared noodles and cover with mushroom sauce.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine crumbs and butter (1/2 cup) in bowl.
Press in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Drizzle syrup evenly over crumbs. Combine sugar and other 1/2 cup butter.
Beat until light; add eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Spread onto crumbs.
Arrange bananas over mixture.
Top with pineapple.
Cover with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with nuts and garnish with cherries.
Chill.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk and pepper.
Arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onions and sauce in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Dot top with butter; sprinkle with paprika.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes more.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
You may double recipe and use a 9 x 13-inch dish for larger crowd.

title: candy cane bread
directions: Stir together the flour, brown sugar, baking powder and salt. Cut in the butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add nuts.
Mix egg and milk; stir into dry mixture until moistened. On a lightly floured surface, pat dough to a 10 x 7-inch rectangle, 1/2-inch thick.
Cut crosswise into 1-inch strips. Twist each strip by holding both ends.
Bend 1 end to form a candy cane.
Place several inches apart on greased baking sheet. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, or until light brown.
Carefully transfer to rack and cool.
Coat each cane with powdered sugar icing.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo; bring to a full boil and boil 1 minute (stir until comes to a boil).
Add the vanilla, Quaker oats and peanut butter to the mixture.
Mix and drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper until firm.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen, according to size of cookies.

title: apricot salad
directions: Cook pudding, jello and water until thick.
Cool.
Beat with electric mixer.
Add fruit and topping.

title: swiss chicken quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pastry shell 8 minutes; remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Meanwhile, in medium bowl, toss cheese with flour and bouillon; add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until set. Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: holiday fruitcake dessert
directions: In a bowl, combine the cherries, pineapple, walnuts and raisins; set aside.
In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Combine the flour, baking powder and salt; add to the creamed mixture and mix well. Pour over fruit mixture and stir to coat.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan to a wire rack to cool completely.
Wrap tightly and store in a cool place.
Slice with a serrated knife; bring to room temperature before serving.
Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: magic oven stew
directions: Grease 11 x 7 1/2 x 2 pan lightly.
Line bottom with meat. Arrange carrots and potatoes on top of meat; then onions and celery.
Combine salt, pepper, tapioca and sugar and sprinkle over all.
Add tomato sauce.
Cover pan tightly with heavy foil.
Do Not Peek.
Bake 4 hours at 275 degrees.

title: apple cheese crisp
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place in a shallow, buttered baking pan.
Pour water and lemon juice over apples.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, flour, shortening, salt and cheese; sprinkle over the apples.
Bake at 350° until apples are tender and the top crust is crisp (about 30 minutes).

title: sausage and cheese dip
directions: In double boiler melt cheese with a little milk.
In skillet brown sausage, stirring until crumbly.
Mix with cheese.
Serve with your favorite chip.

title: best baked beans
directions: Slice bacon into 1/2-inch pieces, then fry.
Mix all remaining ingredients and add bacon pieces.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add milk and dry ingredients to egg mixture.
Beat 3 minutes.
Add 1 can poppy seed filling and 1 cup chopped nuts.
Put into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and empty onto cake plate.
Dust with confectioners sugar.
Serves 16.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Put shortening, sugar and milk in pan and scald. Cool to lukewarm and add the yeast.
Mix well. Add enough flour to make batter.
Let rise until double in bulk (about 1 to 2 hours).
Add soda, baking powder and salt. Roll out and cut.
Place on lightly greased pan.
Let rise until double in size or refrigerate until ready to use.

title: salmon with black bean sauce
directions: Cut peppers, carrot and squash into julienne strips.
Trim tops of scallions off to one inch above white parts.
Place one salmon fillet in center of each of 4 large aluminum foil squares. Coat each fillet generously with black bean sauce.
Top with 1/4 of each vegetable.
Fold up salmon packets securely.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes, until salmon is flaky.

title: watergate cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in a tube pan for 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until rice is tender.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Add cranberries and chopped apples. Add sugar and orange juice. Mix thoroughly. Place in the refrigerator. Will keep more than a week. Better after it sets a day.

title: mallow-whip sweet potatoes
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup marshmallows.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Spoon into 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with reserved marshmallows and broil until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix ground round, bread crumbs, egg, garlic and chopped onion. Shape into balls.
Brown evenly.
Add the remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: corn souffle
directions: In small casserole, beat egg.
Add all ingredients and stir to blend.
Microwave 5 minutes.
Stir often.
Cook just until set. Remove from oven; let rest a few minutes before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Allow cheese to soften and mix well with all ingredients. Roll into a ball and cover with chopped pecans.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: green chilie corn
directions: Melt cream cheese and oleo together in casserole in microwave. Stir to mix thoroughly.
Add corn and chilies.
Mix well.
Heat through.

title: fruit swirl breakfast cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan or 2 square 9 x 9 x 2-inch pans.
Mix all ingredients, except pie filling and glaze.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Spread 2/3 of the batter in jelly roll pan or 1/3 of the batter in each square pan.
Spread pie filling over batter.
(Filling may not cover batter completely.)
Drop remaining batter by tablespoons onto pie filling.
Bake until light brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Drizzle with glaze while warm.
Serve warm or cool.

title: hamburger bundles
directions: Mix the ground beef with evaporated milk and salt and pepper. Form into 5 large, thin patties.
Make the Stove Top dressing according to package directions, adding 2 tablespoons water.
Put dressing on each patty. Fold meat up around the dressing, leaving a small opening at the top.
Mix mushroom soup, water, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over top of each bundle.
Bake about 1 hour in a 350° oven. Serves 5.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix brown sugar, white sugar and flour.
Add eggs, vanilla and melted butter.
Beat well.
Fold in pecans. Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve slightly warm.
Top with ice cream or whipped cream, if desired.
Super good.

title: shanghai beef
directions: In a large skillet, saute beef in oil until brown.
Add cornstarch and blend well.
Add broth, water chestnuts, red pepper, scallions, soy sauce and pepper. Bring to a boil; stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together and season more or less if you like it hot or mild.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Melt butter; add stuffing and set aside.
Cook onion and squash for 5 minutes in boiling water, drain and then add soup, sour cream and carrots.
Line half the stuffing on bottom; then add squash mixture.
Put other half stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: apple squares
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Add a mixture of the flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Add the apples and nuts. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread evenly. Sprinkle top with mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 3/8 teaspoon cinnamon. Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: "chewy" brownies
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in large bowl. Add melted margarine. Add eggs one at a time; stir in after each egg. (Do not beat with mixer.) Add flour, vanilla and nuts. Bake in jelly roll pan (approximately 11 x 13 x 1-inch) for 20 minutes at 325°. (Shake pan while brownies are baking to make them fall. This makes them chewy.) Top with marshmallow cream while hot, then make a chocolate confectioners icing to spread on top.

title: mini meat loaves and vegetables(ready to bake in 10 minutes)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Great for company coming from the North.

title: turkey casserole
directions: In a greased 2-quart casserole dish, place 2/3 cup stuffing. Use box instructions.
Add turkey, beans and almonds.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over mixture.
Top with remaining filling.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or microwave for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: toffee nut bars
directions: Mix the shortening or butter, 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 cup sifted flour.
Press and flatten with hand to cover bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch oblong pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Into a large skillet, place olive oil.
When simmering, add scampi and allow to cook until golden brown.
Reduce heat and add butter, garlic, salt and pepper.
When you think you have too much salt, add more.
This is one dish you cannot oversalt.
When well blended, raise fire to very hot.
Add lemon juice and dry vermouth; cook for about one minute, constantly stirring.
Serve as an appetizer or an entree.

title: diabetic applesauce
directions: Core and cut apples.
In large pan place apples and 1 can diet cream soda.
Cover and cook until soft.
Run through sieve. Combine apples, margarine and cinnamon.
Enjoy!

title: jumbole chicken with sausage
directions: In a large pot or wok, saute onion and bell pepper until onion is clear.
Meanwhile, brown chicken. To onion and pepper add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 40 to 60 minutes until chicken is done and water gone. No peeking!

title: finger paint
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in cold water.
Stir in cool water.
Heat in saucepan until it boils.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatine.
Mix well.
Add detergent.
Stir.
Divide into small jars.
Color and seal.

title: easy chili
directions: Heat oil; add onion and cook 2 minutes.
Add ground beef and garlic and cook 5 minutes.
Add kidney beans, tomatoes and chili powder.
Simmer on very low heat 1 hour.
Season to taste with salt, pepper, paprika and chili powder.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese at medium speed on mixer until creamy, about 2 minutes. Gradually add sugar, beating 5 to 7 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating each just until the yellow disappears. Add vanilla, mixing well.

title: corn pudding *
directions: Put oil in 13 x 9-inch baking
dish and heat for a few minutes in oven at 350°.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour in dish.
Bake for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells in boiling water until they are soft.
Rinse in cold water and set aside.
Mic Ricotta cheese, egg, Parmesan cheese and nutmeg in a bowl.
Pour enough spaghetti sauce in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish to cover bottom (approximately 1/3 jar).
Use teaspoon and stuff shells with mixture of cheese. Place in baking dish.
Cover with remaining sauce and bake approximately 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Delicious and easy. Serve with salad and favorite garlic bread.
Sprinkle stuffed shells with Parmesan cheese at serving time.

title: turtle cake
directions: Make cake according to package directions. Pour 1/2 batter into greased & floured 9 X 13 pan. Bake 15 minutes at 350 degrees. Melt caramels with margarine & canned milk. Pour caramel mixture over cake. Sprinkle pecans & chocolate chips over caramel mixture. Pour remaining batter over this. Continue baking for 20 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: orange bread
directions: Wash and cut orange into pieces, rind and all.
Combine with juice in the blender.
Blend until almost smooth.
Combine sugar, egg and oleo.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add orange and dry ingredients to sugar mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Place on rack to cool, after removing from pan.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray small baking dish with Pam in preparation for baking.
While oven is heating, use a large skillet on stove top and heat olive oil.
Break up sausage and brown in skillet.
When sausage is fully cooked, lower heat and add spinach; stir until wilted.
Add beaten eggs (or Egg Beaters).
Add Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and scrambled until eggs are slightly firm.
Place the egg, spinach and sausage mixture into baking dish.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Cook for 25 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix cheese, butter, salt and pepper.
Add flour and roll out 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with small cutter.
Put half of pecans on top.
Bake at 350°.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: caramelized small onions
directions: Boil onions for 15 to 20 seconds to loosen the skin; drain. Run under cold water.
Cut a small piece from both ends of each onion.
Peel.
Cut an "X" in the root end of the onions to keep them from separating.
Put onions in a small pan with 1 tablespoon butter, water and the sugar.
Bring to a boil, then simmer uncovered for about 15 minutes, or until the liquid evaporates and the onions are tender.
Stir in the vinegar, green onions and remaining butter.
Serve at room temperature.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Layer 1/2 of each ingredients, then other half.
Top with croutons.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix baking soda with hot water. In large bowl combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, ginger and salt; add molasses, butter, egg, soda water and vinegar; mix until batter is smooth. Pour batter into a lightly greased 8 x 8 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 - 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: mexican squash puffs
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep hot fat.
Fry until brown.
Serve hot.

title: heavenly pecans
directions: Beat egg white to a soft peak and add sugar and flavoring. Dip pecan halves and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 250° until brown, about 30 minutes.
Turn oven off; let set 5 minutes.
Use sharp knife to remove from pan.

title: fried onion rings
directions: Make a batter by combining flour and beer in a large bowl; blend thoroughly.
Cover the bowl and allow the batter to sit at room temperature for no less than 3 hours.
Preheat oven to 200°. Carefully peel the onions and cut into 1/4-inch thick slices. Separate the slices into rings and set aside.
Melt enough shortening in a 10-inch skillet to come to a 2-inch depth.
Heat the shortening to 375°.
Dip onion rings into the batter and place in hot fat.
Fry rings, turning once or twice, until they are a golden color.
Drain on paper towels.
To keep warm, place on middle shelf of preheated oven.

title: chipped beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package only using 1/2 the water and salt.
Blend together soup and milk.
Stir in cheese, onion, macaroni and chipped beef.
Fold in eggs and pour into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake 30 minutes.

title: surprise salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in refrigerator for several hours before serving.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg. Add dry ingredients and milk as needed.
Add vanilla.
Drop by spoon.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients like
pie
crust.
Mix well with hands.
The more they are	mixed,	the
more
aggressions	are released and the better the
cookies
taste.
Roll	into walnut sized balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten balls with bottom of glass dipped in
granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: golden punch
directions: Mix first
ingredients together.
Pour in punch bowl over ice or frozen ring.
Add ginger ale.

title: stove top apple butter
directions: In large kettle, bring apples and water to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until apples are tender.
Press apples through a colander or food mill.
Discard peels.
Return pureed apples to kettle.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer uncovered, stirring frequently until very thick and dark brown, about 8 hours.
Freeze in containers.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Prepare cake mix by package directions.
Cool layers.
Prepare pudding mixes.
Cut cake layers into 1-inch cubes.
Place cubes from one cake layer in bottom of punch bowl.
Place one box of prepared pudding evenly over cake cubes.
Top with half each of fruit cocktail, pineapple, cherry pie filling, nuts and coconut. Spread 1 container of whipped topping evenly over coconut layer.

title: puppy chow
directions: In a large microwave-safe bowl, melt chocolate on High for 1 minute.
Stir and heat an additional 30 seconds on High or until melted.
Stir in peanut butter and nuts. Pour mixture over cereal. Place powdered sugar in a 2 gallon storage bag.
Add coated cereal to sugar and close bag tightly. Toss bag until cereal is thoroughly coated with sugar. Store in airtight container.
Yields 8 cups.

title: stir and go salad
directions: Empty jello powder into bowl.
Stir in pineapple and cottage cheese.
Mix until jello is dissolved.
Carefully stir in mandarin oranges to prevent breaking them.
Gently fold in Cool Whip near serving time and refrigerate.
Serves 6 generously.
Delicious!

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix cornstarch with sugar in saucepan.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Cook and stir constantly over medium heat until thick.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pie shells or into 1 large deep dish pie shell.
Top with meringue and chill.

title: fun finger jello
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, microwave orange juice, water and lemon juice on High (100% power) for 4 minutes.
Mix flavored gelatin and unflavored gelatin with boiling liquid until dissolved.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill; cut into squares or shapes.
At holiday time, may use cookie cutters.

title: tomato soup salad
directions: Bring soup to boil.
Add jello, stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Cut cream cheese into small pieces and add to soup mixture.
Cool.
Then add mayonnaise, celery, cucumber and cabbage.
Pour in mold.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Put sliced berries into pie shell.
Mash 1 cup berries in saucepan.
Add sugar and cornstarch; mix.
On medium heat, stir and cook until thick.
Cool to lukewarm.
Pour over berries in pie shell.
Refrigerate.
Spread with Cool Whip.

title: amish cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Flour 9 x 13-inch pan, but do not grease.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients with enough liquid to make a soft dough. Drop from teaspoon in deep fat.
Fry until golden brown.

title: delectables
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, sugar and vanilla until blended. Stir in flour and nuts. Shape into crescents or 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets. Bake in oven for 10 minutes or until firm, but not brown. Gently roll crescents in additional powdered sugar. Cool on wire racks.
Drizzle cookies with melted chocolate.
Let stand on waxed paper until chocolate is firm.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix and pour in pie crust. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter ball
directions: Mix peanut butter and melted oleo.
In another pan, mix cracker crumbs and powdered sugar.
Put peanut butter mixture into cracker crumb mixture until it all sticks together.
With hands, make 1-inch balls.
Melt chocolate morsels.
Stir until melted.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Combine butter and brown sugar.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until sugar dissolves.
Add milk and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Add salt, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Beat to spreading consistency.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: date pudding
directions: Bring dates and water to boil. Let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cherry supreme
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk and powdered sugar.
Spread mix over (cooled) crust.
Spread walnuts over mix.
Spread Cool Whip over walnuts.
Refrigerate for 3 hours.
Then spread 1 can cherry pie filling on top.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Wash well the cucumbers.
Do not peel.
Trim ends.
Cut cucumbers into thin slices.
Place into a bowl, having a fitted cover.
Peel 1 large onion and cut into very thin vertical slices. Mix with cucumbers.
Add granulated sugar and vinegar.
Cover bowl tightly.
Shake.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving.
The cucumbers will stay fresh for a long period of time.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain on paper toweling, crumble and set aside.
Drain fat from pan, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
In bacon drippings, cook onion and green pepper until tender.
Stir in the next 9 ingredients; cover and simmer for about 30 minutes or until rice is done.
Add a little water if needed.
Be sure to dice the tomatoes up, but use all juice.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until foamy.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add oil and vanilla; beat well.
Fold in apples and nuts.

title: strawberry-banana tropical punch
directions: In a blender or food processor, blend bananas, 1/2 of the strawberries, orange juice and lemonade until smooth.
Remove 1/2 of mixture; set aside.
Add 1 cup water to mixture in blender; blend until smooth.
Place in Bundt pan.
Repeat with remaining strawberry-banana mixture and water; add to Bundt pan.
Slice remaining strawberries and place neatly around the mixture in the Bundt pan.
Cover and freeze until solid.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies.
Reserve 1/2 cup for garnishing.
Add margarine to crushed cookies and press in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar; beat well.
Fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread on top of cookie crust.
Chill for 30 minutes.

title: lemon whip
directions: Line a loaf pan with foil and lapped vanilla wafers.
Mix the condensed milk with the lemon juice and Cool Whip.
Cover with foil.
Freeze 4 hours or overnight.
Remove and slice.

title: quick apricot dessert cake
directions: Mix together and cook until thick and clear.
Add 1/2 teaspoon almond flavoring.
Break an angel food cake apart in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour hot mixture over cake.
Cool.
Cover with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with ground pecans or slivered almonds.
Chill.
Cut in squares.

title: spinach squares
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan in oven.
Beat eggs well with beater; add flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Spoon into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 45 minutes. Cut into bite size 3/4 to 1-inch squares.
May be frozen.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all well.
Store in airtight container.
Mix 1/3 c. with boiling cup of hot water.

title: la vera's fluff
directions: Mix dry Jello, cottage cheese and Cool Whip until smooth. A mixer works best. Fold in fruit. Allow to stand in refrigerator several hours or overnight.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and cheese mix as directed on box.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter; blend in flour and stir in milk slowly.
Add cheese; stir until melted (or put in microwave and melt).
Add salt and pepper.
Stir into macaroni.
Pour into any casserole dish; combine melted butter and bread crumbs and sprinkle on top. Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: mallow fruit dip
directions: Mix the ingredients until well blended.
Makes 2 cups.
Serve with fresh fruit, such as strawberries, grapes, apple wedges, bananas or blueberries.

title: beef-noodle casserole
directions: Cook beef in butter until crumbly.
Add garlic, salt, sugar, pepper and tomato sauce.
Cook over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes. Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain.
Mix onions, cream cheese and sour cream.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Add coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Mix by spoon, as batter will be heavy.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 10 minutes.

title: best pecan pie
directions: Stir together syrup, sugar, salt, flavorings, cool butter and beaten eggs.
Makes 2 shallow pans or 12 tarts.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes and then at 325° until done.
Put foil over if it browns too fast.

title: double batch fudge
directions: Stir together margarine, sugar and milk in heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan; bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir in chocolate until melted.
Add remaining ingredients; mix until well blended.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch (at least) pan.
Cool at room temperature; cut into squares.
Makes 6 to 8 pounds.

title: clam dip
directions: Put ingredients in mixing bowl and mix with mixer until smooth (of course there will be clam bits).
Serve with fresh vegetables (sliced) such as cuke, squash, celery sticks, mushrooms (halved), chips or party crackers.

title: egg dumplings
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix water and egg with flour using spatula.
Have broth boiling.
Drop by teaspoonful and let them rest on the meat.
cover tightly and boil gently for 20 minutes without lifting lid.
Makes very light and tender dumplings.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook hamburger and onion until brown.
Add garlic, salt and chili powder.
Add tomato juice.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add rice.
Let cool.

title: meatball stew
directions: Mix ground beef with 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, pepper, egg, minced onion and soft bread crumbs.
Form into ball (size of a walnut). Brown in hot oil.
Remove meatballs from skillet.
Pour off all fat except 3 tablespoons.
Transfer fat to Dutch oven.

title: candied dill pickles
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar and pickling spices in a saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Drain pickles, discarding juice in which they were packed.
(If not using sliced pickles, cut pickles in 1/4-inch slices.)
Repack pickles in quart jar.
Strain out pickling spices and pour warm syrup over pickles.
Store in refrigerator 1 week before using.

title: warm pineapple punch
directions: Combine all ingredients. Heat to simmer. Serve hot with orange slices studded with cloves.

title: microwave chocolate frosted bars
directions: Mix together the oatmeal, brown sugar, margarine and syrup. Press mixture evenly into a large flat baking dish.
Bake until the mixture bubbles on top.
Turn dish frequently as it bakes. Cool in refrigerator.

title: egg in a frame
directions: Cut center of bread with cookie cutter to make a hole in bread.
Melt butter in frying pan.
Place bread in butter and break egg in the hole in the bread.
Fry until egg is done. Butter round piece and serve with frame.
Kids love this one!

title: pistachio pudding dessert
directions: Mix flour, margarine, nut meats and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: moss cake
directions: Cream butter and egg; add sugar all at once.
Add flour sifted alternately
with
baking
powder,	salt and milk.	Add vanilla and
nuts.	Fold
in
egg whites and grated chocolate. Save a little
chocolate for top of cake.	Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 9	x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.
Frost with powdered sugar and butter frosting and sprinkle grated chocolate on top.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Beat eggs. Add evaporated milk and garlic salt to eggs.
Add chicken breast strips.
Marinate overnight, then drain.
Flour marinated chicken and drop into hot cooking oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: white chocolate macadamia nut cookies
directions: Beat butter and shortening at medium speed with an electric mixer until soft and creamy. Gradually add sugars, beating well. Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well. Combine flour, soda and salt. Gradually add to butter mixture, beating well.
Stir in white chocolate and nuts.

Drop dough by spoonfuls (rounded teaspoons) 2-inches apart onto lightly greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool slightly on cookie sheets. Remove to wire racks and let cool completely. Yields 5 dozen.

title: pear honey preserves
directions: In a large pot, cook pears until soft.
Drain juice off.
Mash up remaining pears.
Add pineapple and sugar.
Bake in a 350° oven about 2 hours in open pan.
Stir occasionally.
When desired thickness and color, put in jars and seal.

title: scratch corn bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt together. Cut in shortening, milk and egg.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir only long enough to mix.
Pour into greased pan (8 x 8-inch) and bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
Butter top when done.
Serves 6.

title: baptist cocktail
directions: Blend all ingredients together in blender. Serve immediately.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients with a mixer until smooth. Serve with your favorite fruit.

title: inside out pigs in a blanket
directions: Fill bottom of baking dish with thin sliced potatoes; add salt and pepper to taste.
Dip pork chops in flour, salt and pepper and brown in hot oil.
Place on potatoes.
Leave dripping in skillet; add 1 can mushroom soup and 1/4 can water.
Bring to a boil; pour over pork chops.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together in roaster (will be soupy).
Put chicken breasts on top of rice mixture.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 2 hours.
(Add more milk if more rice is used.)

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Place brown sugar, butter, flour and salt in saucepan on low heat.
Mix well.
Add milk.
Cook until it thickens.
Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Top with meringue. Bake pie until meringue is lightly brown.
Bake in 350° oven.

title: baked mashed potatoes
directions: Blend cream cheese and sour cream in bowl and set aside.
Mash potatoes until smooth.
Add cheese mixture and beat well.
Stir in chives, salt and pepper.
Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with grated Cheddar.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Place beef in shallow dish.
In medium saucepan, bring wine, water, lemon juice, onion, peppercorns, bay leaf and clove to a boil.
Pour over meat; cool.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 days, turning several times.
Drain; reserve marinade.
Pat meat dry.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Stir Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice together; it will be thick.
Drain all fruit and mix with milk and lemon juice.
Add Cool Whip; mix well.
Spoon into pie shell.
Add nuts, if you want.
This freezes well.

title: bear mountain salad
directions: Drain pineapple; add cottage cheese, marshmallows and cherries (halved).
Stir in Cool Whip and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: beef stew
directions: Mix together wine, water and tapioca.
Add other ingredients and put into heavy roaster with lid or 9 x 13-inch pan, covered with foil.
Bake 5 hours at 250°.
Do not peek while cooking!

title: parmesan rosemary pinwheels
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Separate dough into 4 rectangles on smooth side of cutting board. Press seams to seal. Place cream cheese in bowl. Grate Parmesan cheese into bowl. Snip rosemary; add to cheese mixture. Mix well. Spread each rectangle with about 2 tablespoons cheese mixture to within 1/4-inch of edges. Start at short side; roll up each rectangle. Pinch edges to seal. Cut each roll crosswise into 6 slices for a total of 24 slices. Place slices, cut side down. Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Remove; serve warm. Yield: 24 pinwheels.

title: chicken, black bean and barley soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cover beans with water.
Bring to a boil and cook for 3 minutes. Remove from heat, cover and let stand for 1 hour. Drain.

title: cheddar cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter over medium-low heat in medium saucepan.
Stir in flour, salt and cayenne pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat; stir in mustard and cheese, stirring until cheese is melted and mixture is smooth.

title: gingerbread boys
directions: Cream together the shortening, sugar and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Roll 1/8 inch thick.
Bake on greased sheet at 375°.

title: russian butter buds dressing or dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Good on salads, snacks, or as a dip.

title: honey tarts
directions: Beat 2 eggs.
Blend in 1/2 cup honey, 1/4 cup sugar, 1/4 teaspoon salt, 1 teaspoon vanilla, and 2/3 cup broken pecans. Pour into 4 to 6 unbaked pastry tart shells.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: tuna ball
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.
Roll into ball and store (wrapped in Saran wrap) in the refrigerator until ready to serve.
Remove from refrigerator.
Pat on parsley flakes to cover.

title: vegetable base(microwave)
directions: In 3-quart casserole dish, place butter, onions, green pepper and carrots.
Cover with lid.
Microwave on High 6 minutes or until vegetables and tender-crisp, stirring once during cooking.
Stir in broth and water.
Cover; microwave on High 6 minutes or until hot and bubbling, stirring once during cooking.
Use to make Pasta Soup and Cheese Potato Bake.

title: apple-acorn squash
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut washed squash in halves, lengthwise.
Remove seeds.
Brush cut surface of each half with melted butter.
Arrange cut side down in shallow pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until tender.
Now scoop squash from shells; reserve 4 shells.
Mash squash; add applesauce, butter and nutmeg.
Lightly heap mixture into shells.
Bake until brown.
Serves 4.

title: best-ever pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour and beat into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool; mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar, Cool Whip and spread on top of baked mixture.
Beat instant pudding with 3 cups milk until thick.
Spread on top of cream cheese.
Top with rest of Cool Whip (1/2 of carton).
You may use chocolate, lemon, butterscotch, or any flavor you choose.

title: ham and cheese roll-ups
directions: Combine cheeses and margarine until well blended. Spread mixture on ham slice.
Roll up, jelly roll style.
Chill for several hours or wrap and freeze.

title: sweet potato medallions
directions: Peel sweet potatoes and slice 1/4 inch thick.
Cook, covered, in 2 inches of salted, boiling water 10 minutes; drain.
Peel and core apples.
Cut into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Combine brown sugar, butter, ginger and nutmeg.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together in casserole dish and top with a thin layer of Pepperidge Farm herb dressing mix.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and mix with dressing.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring the water to a boil.
Add butter.
Let butter melt completely, then stir in flour and soda.
Stir until it leaves the side of the pan; beat until smooth.
Cool slightly; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Don't open oven during the first 20 minutes.
Remove puffs; cut near the bottom to let out steam.
Fill with Cream Filling.

title: raw cranberry salad
directions: Pour hot water over jello and sugar.
Stir until dissolved. When it begins to thicken or jell, add remaining ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain. Mix the 2 salad dressings together; blend well. Add the vegetables and then the pasta. Mixing with hands is best. Refrigerate for at least a couple of hours before serving. Better to refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: party dip
directions: Combine yogurt and cottage cheese; stir until smooth.
Stir in spinach, onion, chili powder, dill weed and lemon juice.
Place in a serving dish.
Cover and chill until ready to serve with fresh vegetables, crackers or bread sticks.

title: lazy day biscuits(pull apart loaf)
directions: Place 20 biscuits in a Bundt style cake pan.
Melt butter and pour over the biscuits.
Bake in 400° oven until done (10 to 12 minutes).

title: cream of taco
directions: Brown beef; drain off fat.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer for at least 15 minutes.
Stir.

title: zucchini skillet
directions: Boil sliced zucchini for 5 to 8 minutes until tender.
Saute green pepper in butter until tender.
Drain zucchini using 1 cup of the water to mix with the tomato paste.
Mix together all ingredients except 1/2 cup of the Mozzarella.
Sprinkle the remaining cheese on top.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil the chicken and cut into chunks.
Mix chicken, soup, salt and pepper to taste and just enough milk to make soupy (not too thin).
Pour into baking dish.
Prepare stuffing as directed on package.
Spread on top of chicken mixture and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and make into balls.
Place in pan.
Mix last 4 ingredients together and pour over meat balls. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: ranch salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and confectioners sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar and mix well.
Add to sugar mixture; mix well. Shape by teaspoon into balls, roll in sugar and place on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 250° for 6 to 8 minutes.
(Dough may be stored in refrigerator if desired for a few days.)

title: diet fluff
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Add pineapple, oranges and nuts.
Stir in jello until you reach desired color (usually 1/2 pack).
Stir well.
Refrigerate.
Serves 10 to 15 according to serving size.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Layer cooked macaroni alternately with grated cheese in greased one-quart ovenproof casserole.
Beat eggs with milk and pour over macaroni-cheese mixture.
Top with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° or until custard is set and top is crispy brown. Makes 4 servings.

title: seven-minute frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except the vanilla in top of double boiler.
Beat 1 minute to blend, then place over boiling water and beat with a sturdy egg beater or at high speed of electric mixer for 7 minutes or until stiff peaks will form.
(Stir frosting up from bottom and sides of pan occasionally.)
Fold in vanilla. Makes enough to frost two 9-inch layers or a 10-inch tube cake or 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, marshmallow topping, butter and salt in saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until blended.
Bring to full boil over medium heat, then continue to boil over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add chips and vanilla.
Stir until chips are melted.
Pour into a buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Cut in 1-inch squares.
Makes about 81 squares.

title: peachy delight
directions: Mix all together and spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook, drain and cool ground meat.
Mix with next 5 ingredients.
When ready to serve, crunch nachos in bag.
Add crumbled chips and Catalina dressing.

title: chicken vatel
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
In chicken broth, boil spaghetti. After spaghetti is cooked, drain.
In pan, mix soup, cheese, margarine and Worcestershire sauce together until cheese is melted.
Stir and fold in spaghetti.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Over shortening, sugar and
salt,
pour
boiling water; blend to cool.
Add eggs, sprinkle yeast in lukewarm water and stir until dissolved.
Combine with egg mixture, add flour and blend well.
Cover and place in refrigerator in large bowl for at least 4 hours.
Will keep for 1
week
or
10 days.

title: lace cookies
directions: Melt butter over oatmeal.
Sift dry ingredients together; mix with oatmeal.
Beat eggs and add vanilla.
Mix with oatmeal.
Add nuts.
Cover cookie sheets with foil; drop by teaspoons and bake 11 minutes at 325°.
Let cool before removing from foil.
A thin, crispy cookie.

title: pineapple joy cake
directions: Bake in a long cake pan, the cake mix as directed on the box. After cake is cooled, punch holes in cake and spread pineapple over it.
Mix instant pudding and cream cheese.
Spread over pineapple. Spread Cool Whip on top.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients except soup and butter.
Shape into bite-size balls.
Brown in butter, cook until done.
Heat soup. Pour over meatballs.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Mix bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese; set aside.
Make a batter with the egg, garlic, basil, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in batter and roll it in bread crumbs; set in pan, skin side up. Sprinkle with parsley and dot with butter.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: bean soup
directions: Rinse and sort beans.
Place in large, heavy soup kettle. Cover with water and start to cook over low fire.
Saute ham, celery, onion and garlic in oil; add to beans and cook about 2 hours.
If necessary, add water while cooking, then add other ingredients with the exception of the mashed beans and cook 10 minutes more.
If the soup is not thick enough, remove some of the beans and mash them and stir in.
Regardless, cook 10 minutes more. Makes 8 to 10 servings.
Freezes well.
Serve with green salad and corn bread.

title: punch mix base
directions: Dissolve water and sugar.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Blend bananas with part of liquid so they will mix in well.
Mix all liquids.
Freeze in any kind of containers you have.
It makes so much.
I usually freeze some in ice cube trays because it's so easy to add a few cubes to a glass.
Use ginger ale or 7-Up.

title: holiday cookies
directions: Beat egg whites and vanilla until stiff peaks form.
Add sugar. Add chopped pistachio nuts.
Drop onto cookie sheet lined with brown paper bag.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Allow to cool in off oven.

title: caraway slaw
directions: Combine all; stir and chill.
Keeps well in the refrigerator.

title: fruit dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften and then mix all ingredients together.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onion, drain grease.
Add soup, milk, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Simmer until heated through; stir in sour cream.
Serve over noodles.

title: cookies that taste like candy
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk.
Remove from heat; add marshmallows, peanut butter, rolled oats and vanilla.
Mix until rolled oats are covered with cocoa.
Spoon onto wax paper; let sit until cookies harden, 5 to 8 hours.
Makes approximately 36 cookies.

title: oatmeal-carrot cookies
directions: In a small bowl, cream together sugar, margarine, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add carrots and mix well.
In another bowl, thoroughly stir together flour, baking powder, oatmeal and wheat germ.
Stir the dry ingredients into the creamed mixture.
Fold in the raisins.
Pour mixture into a vegetable oil sprayed 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Cut into bars or squares.

title: meatballs and gravy
directions: In bowl combine beef, eggs, salt, pepper, cheese, parsley, onion and Waverly wafers.
Form into 1-inch balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
In 12-inch skillet, combine soup and milk.
Add meatballs.
Heat.
Serve with noodles, mashed or boiled potatoes.

title: spicy candied yams
directions: Mash in 2-quart casserole.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Top with mini marshmallows.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice in chicken broth. Mix all ingredients except almonds and put in large baking dish. Top with sliced almonds. Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple fritters
directions: Sift flour and salt into medium size mixing bowl.
Make a well in the center and add eggs and oil.
Mix eggs and oil slowly with a wooden spoon into flour, gradually adding milk.
Beat well, then cover and keep cool for 30 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake layers; cool completely.
Prepare instant pudding according to directions on package; refrigerate to set up.

title: avocado mousse
directions: Lightly oil a 1 1/2-quart ring mold.
In a large bowl, soften the gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Add 1 cup boiling water and the lemon juice to the gelatin mixture.
Chill until slightly thickened.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries; add sugar.
Let stand for several hours. Dissolve Jell-O in water and cool.
Add to cranberries.
Grind celery and nuts and add with pineapple to Jell-O mixture.
Keeps for at least 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: green beans
directions: Put green beans in dish.
Pour soup and milk over beans.
Add cheese on top.
Cover when cheese melts and beans are bubbling. Put onions on top and leave about 5 minutes or more.
Bake at 400°.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread according to package.
Let cool.
Crumble cornbread in bowl.
Mix all other ingredients with cornbread.
Add just enough mayonnaise to moisten.

title: congo bars
directions: Bake in 11 x 13-inch pan.
Melt margarine and pour on brown sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs, baking powder, salt, flour and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Add pecans and chocolate chips; mix. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: vegetable mushroom rice
directions: Mix ingredients together and heat in microwave for about 5 minutes or regular oven at 350° for about 20 minutes, until vegetables are hot and steaming.
Use a 1 1/2-quart casserole or 13 x 9-inch dish.
Serve with a little soy sauce.
A favorite dish for us.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars.
Add vanilla, water and eggs. After thoroughly mixing, add chocolate chips and nuts.
Then, by hand, stir in flour, baking powder and soda.
When all ingredients are thoroughly mixed, you can either drop by spoon onto ungreased cookie sheets or press into lightly greased jelly roll pan and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
(If you use the jelly roll pan, the cooking time needs to be extended 5 to 10 minutes longer.)

title: pineapple cranberry bars(makes 36 bars)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish in a medium saucepan.
Combine cranberries, 3 tablespoons cornstarch and pineapple.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes, until cranberry skins pop and mixture thickens, stirring occasionally.

title: rhubarb chiffon pie
directions: Combine rhubarb and sugar. Cook until tender. Add gelatin which has been softened in 1/4 cup water.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved. Chill.
When mixture has thickened, add beaten egg whites and whipped cream.
Pour into cooked pie shell. Chill before serving.
May top with more whipped cream.

title: teriyaki chicken with ramen noodles
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat until hot.
Add chicken, cook and stir 3 to 4 minutes until chicken is no longer pink.
Add frozen sauce from meal starter, water and 1/2 teaspoon seasoning mix from soup mix, stir well.
Discard remaining seasoning mix.
Cook about 3 minutes or until sauce is thawed, stirring frequently.
Break noodles from soup mix into pieces. Add noodles and frozen vegetables to skillet; cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring frequently.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Peel and cube potatoes; cook until tender.
Place cooked potatoes in mixing bowl; beat together with cream cheese until smooth.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour mixture into lightly buttered casserole dish; sprinkle with paprika, if desired.
Place casserole in refrigerator; let marinate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: peanut and green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans; mix in soup.
Cube cheese; add to mixture. Pour into
greased
casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Sprinkle peanuts on top.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Bake 10 minutes at 400° and 30 minutes at 300°.
Be sure center is set.

title: curried lentil soup(heart healthy)
directions: Rinse lentils under cold running water. Drain well. In a large pot, melt butter over medium heat. Stir in vegetables except lentils. Add garlic and curry. Saut, stirring occasionally, until onion is soft, about 3 to 4 minutes. Stir in broth and lentils. Turn heat to high and bring to a boil. Skim off any foam. Stir occasionally. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer until lentils soften and soup thickens, about 30 minutes. Add pepper, lemon juice, coriander/parsley and salt, if needed.

title: german beef stew
directions: Combine ingredients in a crock-pot.
Over medium heat, cook slowly throughout the day.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add pineapple juice. Cool.
Add marshmallows, pecans and pineapple.
Fold in cream. Chill until firm.

title: california walking salad
directions: Remove grapes from stems, core and cube apple; toast the slivered almonds.
Combine these ingredients.
Rinse, drain and chill lettuce.
Carefully remove lettuce leaves from head, one at a time.
Put 1/2 cup of fruit mixture in each lettuce cup.
Serve out of hand.
Makes 6 to 8 salads.

title: plantation almond tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: prune bread
directions: Simmer prunes slowly 30 minutes. Pour juice from prunes and cool and chop prunes.
Cream sugar, egg and shortening.
Sift salt, soda, baking powder and flour together.
Add with prune juice and spices.
Add nuts and prunes.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: five-in-one fruit salad
directions: Mix together well and chill 4 hours in a covered dish before serving.

title: red cabbage
directions: Add all ingredients to the cabbage; bring to a boil and simmer.
Tastes great with ham or sauerbraten.

title: muffin biscuits
directions: Mix together in bowl.
Fill greased muffin pans 1/2 full. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken with mushrooms
directions: Slice chicken breasts in strips. Season with salt and pepper. Heat oil. Saute chicken. Add garlic powder; this will help chicken brown and will make a basis for your gravy.
When chicken is brown, add onions.
When almost clear, add bell pepper and minced garlic. Cook for about 5 minutes.
Add chicken broth and wine. Simmer for about 20 minutes or so until gravy has reduced that it has some body to it.
Add pimiento, mushrooms and parsley. Season to taste.
May be served over angel hair pasta or rice.

title: souper rice
directions: Pour cans of soup over rice in 3-quart Pyrex dish and stir. Cover with foil and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve with soy sauce.
Cut up pieces of chicken may be added.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs in mixing bowl.
Add salt, soda, vanilla and flour.
Stir in buttermilk and bananas.
Mix well and pour into 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 325°
for 1 hour.

title: tomato and onion pickles
directions: Prepare tomatoes, onions and pepper.
Add the salt; stir thoroughly.
Let stand overnight.
Next morning, drain off the liquid and pour water over mixture 2 or 3 times.
Be sure to drain thoroughly to get out salt.
Add the vinegar and sugar that has been dissolved.
Let mixture cook until tender.
Can in sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 3 quarts or 10 pints.
Delicious with cooked vegetables.

title: broccoli noodle salad
directions: *I put them in Ziploc bag and roll it with rolling pin.

title: fat free oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Spray cookie sheets with nonstick cooking spray.

title: the best cookies in the world(renamed the $5,900 cookie)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter; add egg and sugars and mix well.
Add flour alternately with salad oil, then add rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Dip fork in 1/2 cup water and press down on each cookie.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until browned.
Remember, make no substitutions or they will not turn out right.

title: quick chocolate fudge
directions: Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Melt butter and chocolate over low heat.
Stir in Karo syrup, water and sugar.
Remove from heat. Stir in remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour into greased pan to cool.

title: zucchini pancakes
directions: Grate raw zucchini coarsely.

In a bowl, beat eggs. Add milk, then add zucchini, onion, salt and pepper. Sift flour and baking powder together. Add enough milk to egg mixture to make batter on the stiff side. Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil and fry until done. Serves 4.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut round steak into strips and brown in skillet.
Saute onion in butter.
Add onion, sour cream, soup, water, salt and pepper. Heat to a boil and simmer 45 minutes, covered, stirring occasionally.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: microwave potatoes(boiled)
directions: Peel 4 or 6 medium potatoes.
Cut into 1-inch cubes or slice thin.
Make sure there is 1/2 inch water in bottom of dish.
Stir halfway through cooking.
Heat 4 medium potatoes 8 to 10 minutes on High or heat 6 medium potatoes 12 to 14 minutes on High.
Use small, covered mixing bowl or large, covered mixing bowl.

title: fruit candy
directions: Mix fruit and nuts with 10x sugar.
Roll in granulated sugar.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook whole potatoes in skin; cool and slice after taking off skins.
In skillet, fry bacon; drain.
Cook and stir onion in bacon drippings until golden brown.
Stir in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring until bubbling.
Remove from heat.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Crumble bacon.
Carefully stir bacon and potatoes into hot mixture.
Stir lightly to coat potato slices.

title: salsa
directions: In olive oil, saute onions, pepper and garlic until tender, but not brown. Add all other ingredients. Refrigerate. Serve with tortilla chips. Yield: 3 quarts.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix together.
Put in buttered casserole.
Top with buttered corn flake crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: meat loaf(with sauce)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, green pepper, salt, pepper, egg and tomato sauce in a mixing bowl. Mix thoroughly.
Place in a shallow baking dish in shape of a loaf. Mix catsup, brown sugar and mustard together.
Pour over meat loaf. Bake at 350° until meat loaf tests done.

title: beef roast
directions: Place roast in cooking bag.
Add vegetables around roast.
Add one cup water.
Close bag as directed.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes per pound.
tags: beef stew seasoning mix with bag

title: broiled open-faced crab sandwiches
directions: Combine green pepper, onion, white pepper, man. and lemon juice.
Gently stir in crab.
Spread 1/2 cup mixture on each slice of toast.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Broil 5-inches from heat source for 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: busy day chicken
directions: Sprinkle rice in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay chicken over rice.
Mix soup together and pour over chicken.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: kentucky wonder pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except
nuts
and
egg
whites. Beat well.
Add nuts and stiffly beaten egg whites.
Mix well. Pour into tube cake pan that
has
been
greased
and floured. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: crusty cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs alternately with flour.
Add salt and vanilla.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Put batter in large tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Put cake in oven and turn temperature to bake at 325°.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes without opening oven door.
When done, remove from oven and let stand in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add other ingredients as listed; stir until well mixed.
Let stand at room temperature, covered with cloth, until double in bulk.
Punch down and wait 5 minutes.

title: recipe to cut baking time of potatoes
directions: Wash 1 medium potato per person.
Cut in half lengthwise and brush cut surfaces with melted butter, margarine or vegetable oil. Dip in a mixture of Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Place cut side down on a greased baking sheet and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: scripture cake
directions: Sprinkle raisins, figs and almonds with small amount of flour. Cream the butter; blend in molasses. Sift baking powder, flour and salt together twice.
Beat eggs. Add milk and honey.
Stir well. Add milk
mixture and flour mixture alternately to creamed butter; mix well. Stir in spices, raisins, figs and almonds.
Pour into cake pan. Bake for 1 hour at 325° to 350°.
Serves 15 to 18.

title: blender hollandaise sauce
directions: Heat butter in saucepan until bubbly, but not browned.
Put egg yolks, lemon juice, salt, pepper and mustard in blender container.
Cover and turn on low speed about 5 seconds.

title: macadamia cheese bites
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Blend butter and biscuit mix until mixture is coarse crumbs.
Stir in egg, nuts, cheese and pepper.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes.
Store in containers lined with paper towels.
May be reheated.
Makes 4 dozen balls.

title: brownie pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Add flour and melted butter.
Mix well.
Add chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla, stir well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: bourbon pecan chicken
directions: Whisk together mustard, sugar, molasses, bourbon, and soy and Worcestershire sauces; set aside.
Mix pecans and bread crumbs; press chicken breasts firmly into crumbs, coating well.
(Note: Chicken can be pounded with mallet to tenderize.)
Heat 2 tablespoons butter in skillet until bubbly hot; add chicken.
Cook to a nice brown on both sides.
In small saucepan, bring bourbon mixture to a low simmer (watch carefully).
Add 6 ounces butter, 1 piece at a time; allow each piece to melt before adding the next. Do not reheat.
Arrange chicken on platter or plates.
Pour sauce over chicken and sprinkle with sliced scallions.

title: old fashioned cooked chocolate frosting
directions: Cook!
Bring mixture to full boil and allow to cook for a few minutes, stirring constantly.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Roll dough to desired thickness.
Spread with soft butter and sprinkle generously with brown sugar and cinnamon. Roll dough and cut in about 1-inch slices.
Let raise in pans until double.
Bake in moderate oven until rolls are done.

title: sante fe soup
directions: Brown beef and onion, drain. Add: ranch dressing, taco mix, and water. Mix and let sit. In large pot mix beans, tomatoes, and corn. Add meat mixture. Heat and simmer for 2 hours. This recipe is better if cooked on top of stove instead of crock pot. To serve, place 2 tablespoons of sour cream in each bowl. Fill with soup and top with shredded cheese and corn chips.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Chop meat and onion in blender; drain.
Mix with dash of Worcestershire sauce and roll in nuts.

title: pizza sauce meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Pack into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cottage pudding cake
directions: Add vanilla flavoring to taste. Cook until thick and serve over warm cake.

title: apple peanut butter crumb pie
directions: Spoon apple pie filling into the pie shell.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Cut peanut butter and margarine into mixture of flour, brown sugar, spices and lemon peel.
Spread over surface of pie.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until topping is bubbling hot.

title: momma's rolls(with milk and cheese)
directions: Proof yeast:
Put 1/2 cup water (110°) in glass.
Sprinkle in 2 packages yeast; stir with a fork until well dissolved.
Stir in sugar and cover with paper towel.
Set aside for 5 to 20 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Pour soup into small pan.
Cook, covered, for 1 1/2 minutes. Stir well.
Beat in cream cheese, lemon juice, paprika and garlic powder.
Keep warm over a candle warmer.
Serve with crisp vegetables.

title: snowflake salad
directions: When Jell-O is partially set, beat until fluffy.
Add cheese and pineapple in which sugar has been dissolved.
Stir in nuts, then fold in whip cream.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch pan and chill until firm.
Cut in squares.
Serve on crisp lettuce plain or sprinkled with nut meats.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add tuna, mushroom soup, cream, toast and eggs.
Bake in 375° oven about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: one of those days chicken
directions: Place rice in buttered casserole dish.
Add fryer pieces. Sprinkle soup mix over chicken.
Spoon on cream of chicken soup. Pour chicken broth directly from the can over all carefully. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk, marshmallows, margarine and salt over medium heat.
Boil and stir for 5 minutes.
Take off heat; stir in 6 ounce package chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla.
Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool and cut.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Mix with corn, crackers, salt and pepper. Place in a buttered casserole and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together, including sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until smooth.
Apportion batter among three loaf pans which have been greased and floured.

title: ginger creams
directions: Mix first four ingredients together thoroughly.
Stir in soda dissolved in hot water.
Mix together flour, salt, ginger, nutmeg, cloves and cinnamon.
Add to first mixture, mixing thoroughly. Chill dough.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven 7 to 8 minutes.
Ice while still warm.

title: spaghetti sauce and meatballs
directions: Heat oil and saute onion and garlic about 5 minutes.
Add tomato paste, tomato sauce or canned tomatoes, salt, pepper, sugar, oregano, bay leaves and water.
If too thick, add a little more water.
Add meatballs and simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Serve over cooked spaghetti with garlic toast.

title: christmas wassail
directions: Simmer all together a couple hours and serve warm.
Wassail simmering on the stove adds a delicate aroma to the Christmas season and has long been a favorite in our Holiday Open House.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 325° to 350° for glass baking dish.
Microwave chocolate and margarine in a bowl on High for 2 minutes or until melted.
Stir sugar into chocolate until well blended.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts until well blended. Spread in greased, foil-lined, 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes 24.

title: cranberry cream dessert salad
directions: Combine 1/2 package (1 1/2 cups) miniature marshmallows with well-drained crushed pineapple.
Break cream cheese into small pieces and mix with whipping cream and remaining 1/2 package (1 1/2 cups) miniature marshmallows.
Place both pineapple-marshmallow mixture and marshmallow-cream mixture in the refrigerator for several hours or overnight until marshmallows are well softened.
Shortly before serving, beat marshmallow-cream mixture until like whipped cream.
Fold in the pineapple-marshmallow mixture and 4 cups chopped fresh cranberries.
Place in serving dish or dishes and refrigerate until served.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce to low and cook 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Put the margarine in an 11 x 13-inch dish. Let melt in oven.
Remove dish.
Combine the last five ingredients and mix well.
Pour over the dish of melted margarine.
Do not stir. Spoon the peach mixture over the margarine and batter mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake for 50 minutes or until lightly brown in a 350° oven.

title: bean soup for 6
directions: Rinse beans.
In a large pot, cover beans with 2 quarts cold water.
Bring to boil; boil gently for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; let stand 1 hour.
Add seasonings.
Boil gently until beans are tender (3 to 3 1/2 hours).
Add onion the last 1/2 hour.
Cut ham off beans and return to soup.
Serve hot with hot cornbread or corn muffins.

title: bannertown broccoli salad
directions: In a small bowl, combine the mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar. Chill the dressing for at least 1 hour before serving.
In a salad bowl, layer broccoli, bacon, cheese and onion.
Pour the dressing over the salad and toss before serving.
Serves 6.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix as you would any other batter.
Put into cake pan.

title: creamy pepper dip
directions: In medium bowl stir cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Refrigerate until serving time (2 hours).

title: shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar in large mixing bowl until fluffy. Gradually add flour and salt and mix well.
Press dough into two ungreased 8 x 1-inch round baking pans.
Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes.
Slice into wedges and poke all over with a fork prior to cooling.
When cooled, dust with powdered sugar and remove from pans.
Makes 16 wedges.

title: easy tamale pie
directions: Cook meat and drain. Add onion and garlic. Cook 2 to 3 minutes.

Add corn, tomato sauce, salt and pepper to meat mixture. Layer in greased casserole, alternating with meat mixture, tamales and olives. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly, approximately 25 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix nuts and coconut and press in bottom of 9x13 pan.
Mix cake as directed on package and pour over nut mixture.
Combine cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar and drop on top of cake. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: german potato salad
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Add bacon, celery seed, salt and pepper.
Set aside.
Saute onions in bacon drippings until clear. Add flour and mix well.
Add vinegar, sugar and water, stirring until mixture thickens slightly.
Pour over potatoes.
Stir well. Best if allowed to sit 1/2 hour.

title: lee's peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugars.
Add egg and peanut butter.
Sift together the flour, salt and baking soda; add to creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts.
Roll into small balls; press down with sugar coated fork.
Bake at 400° for about 8 minutes.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: beef stew
directions: Heat oil in 4-quart pot.
Brown meat completely.
Remove meat. Saute onion in remaining oil, then add flour and stir well. Return the meat to pot.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Also add Worcestershire sauce, bouillon cubes and water.
Stir well.
Bring to boil and stir until liquid thickens.
Reduce heat to medium. Add potatoes and carrots.
