Cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add peas 15 minutes before serving.
Serve over biscuits.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain off all water.
Place in baking dish and mix in carrots and onion (chopped).
Put salt, pepper and dots of butter on top.
Add chicken or mushroom soup mixed with sour cream.
Mix all together.
Place Pepperidge Farm stuffing on top.
Sprinkle on cheese.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Drop by teaspoonfuls. Bake 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Combine in saucepan and melt and stir over medium heat just until morsels and margarine are melted.
In large bowl, combine 2 cups dry roasted peanuts and 1 (10 1/2 ounce) package miniature marshmallows.
Pour chocolate mixture into nut mixture.
Mix well. Spread into wax paper-lined 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 2 hours.
Cut in squares.

title: sam's easy bake apple pie
directions: Mix apples and spices.
Spread in greased pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Beat next four ingredients and 1/2 cup Bisquick 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour over apples.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly and sprinkle on top.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 65 minutes at 350°.

title: top of stove cookies
directions: Stir together sugar, peanut butter, butter and milk in large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cook 1 minute after reaching boiling point.
Remove from heat; add coconut, cocoa, vanilla and oats. Mix well and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and meal in a large bowl.
Toss lightly with fork.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° or until top is golden brown.

title: fruit squares
directions: Work butter and flour like for a pie crust.
Add remaining ingredients, except for the pie filling.
Place about 1/2 to 3/4 cup of the batter in a small bowl.
Spread the rest of batter into an ungreased jelly roll pan.
Add flour to reserved batter to make a rollable dough.
After spreading pie filling over batter, crisscross strips of the "pie dough" over the fruit filling.

title: tangy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a small saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Discard bay leaf.
Use as a basting sauce for chicken, pork or beef.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Spread hash browns evenly in shallow baking dish.
Scald milk; add oleo and seasoned salt.
Sprinkle green onions and cheese over potatoes.
Pour seasoned milk over all and bake covered in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine salmon with salmon liquid.
Add all other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Form patties and fry in butter until nicely browned.
Makes 2 to 4 servings.

title: summer fruit drink
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.

title: tacos
directions: In a skillet, cook meat, onion and garlic; drain.
Stir in steak sauce, tomato sauce, chili powder and salt.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon mixture into taco shells.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes. Garnish with shredded mild Cheddar cheese, diced tomatoes, shredded lettuce and taco salsa if desired.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Place a 1/4-inch bed of drained sauerkraut in a roasting pan. Sprinkle with seasoned salt and brown sugar.
Arrange chops on top.
Cover pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Uncover and pour over dry sherry.
Bake 20 minutes or until browned.
Serve chops topped with vegetables.

title: crunch bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir together flour, chopped nuts, cocoa, baking powder and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Stir and put into greased glass pan (12 3/4 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows over top.
Bake for 3 minutes more.
Cool.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Stir in Karo, egg yolk and flour. Chill.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip in slightly beaten egg white. Roll in nuts.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Press thumb in center of each cookie.
Bake in 325° oven about 20 minutes.
While warm, fill with jelly.
Makes 24.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add eggs; beat slightly.
Add oleo and coconut.
Pour into crusts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.
Can be frozen after cooking.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Prick eggs with toothpick.
Add beets.
Boil other ingredients together and pour hot mixture over beets and eggs.
Refrigerate. Ready in 2 days.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef strips very slowly.
Add onion soup and 1 cup water.
Cook, covered, about 1 hour.
Stir in mushroom soup and mushrooms.
Cook 15 minutes.
Stir in sour cream (just before serving).
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes.
Peel, cool and mash.
Mix well with all ingredients.
Pour into pie shell (unbaked) and bake at 350° until done.

title: shrimp appetizer
directions: Mix.
Spread on English muffins.
Place under broiler until brown.
Cut into bite size pieces to serve.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix the water, sugar, cornstarch and Karo syrup; boil.
Remove from heat.
Add 3 large tablespoons strawberry Jell-O (dry). Cool.
Put fresh strawberries into baked crust.
Pour filling over berries.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Cook chicken in nonstick skillet until done and juices evaporate, stirring often. Add soup and salsa and heat through. Spread about 1/3 cup soup mixture on half of each tortilla to within 1/2-inch of edge. Moisten edge with water. Fold over other half of tortilla and seal. Place on 2 baking sheets. Bake 5 minutes or until hot. Serve with fiesta rice.

title: pineapple nut cake(side dish served with meat dishes)
directions: Mix all ingredients in order by hand.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 45 minutes.
To be served as a side dish with meat dishes.

title: rolling r zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients. Add eggs and oil to flour mixture. Stir sour cream and vanilla into batter. Press some of the excess water out of grated zucchini and stir into batter. Add raisins and/or nuts. Combine well. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: special "k" cookies
directions: Melt together sugar, Karo syrup and peanut butter but don't boil.
Add mixture to Special "K" in large bowl.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
In double boiler, melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips with powdered sugar.
Spread over hot bars. Cut into squares when cool.

title: 666 bread
directions: Add altogether to make a batter and pour into a greased skillet.
(I use Pam to grease skillet.)
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until brown.

title: molly cheese sauce
directions: In blender bowl, combine cream cheese, flour, 1/2 cup milk, Molly McButter, paprika and pepper.
Blend on medium speed 2 minutes until smooth.
Add remaining milk.
Blend to mix.
Pour into a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat; continue cooking and stirring 2 minutes until thickened.
Makes 1 cup (8 ounces).
Use as a vegetable dip or serve hot over broccoli, cauliflower or macaroni.

title: mulled wine
directions: Bring the ingredients to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes. This mixture can sit on the stove and make the house smell great all afternoon.
Before serving, add 1 quart Port wine.
Simmer. Strain and serve.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Add broccoli and onion to 6 cups hot water and boil 10 to 12 minutes.
Add seasonings and cheese until cheese melts.
Add milk, half and half and butter.
Stir and heat to boil.
Mix 1/2 cup water and 1/3 cup flour.
Add to hot mixture.
Cook and stir until soup is consistency of heavy cream.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown meat lightly.
Drain off fat.
Season with taco seasoning. Pour out on paper to absorb the rest of fat.
Toss all together in a big bowl.
Add Doritos, add dressing last.
Serve.

title: pumpkin surprise
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs,1/4 c sugar, and butter.
Press into dish.
Set aside.
Combine cream cheese, eggs, 3/4 c sugar. Beat until fluffy, spread over crust.
Bake at 350 for 20 minutes. Let cool.
Combine pkgs of vanilla instant pudding mix and milk. Beat for 2 minutes, then add 1 can pumpkin, a dash of cinnamon and pumpkin pie spice.
Mix until well blended.
Fold in 1 c of cool whip.
Spread all this over baked layer after its cooled.
Cover with remaining cool whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and refrigerate. Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: dino's cream cheese cake
directions: Mix well.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 320° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until well done.

title: microwave french dip
directions: Combine onions and margarine in
a small glass bowl. Cover with plastic wrap. Cook on High 3 to 4 minutes or until tender, stirring once.
Next, slice
bread in half lengthwise and then cut into 4 equal sandwiches. Top each sandwich with roast beef and then with onions. Season to taste.
Close sandwiches and wrap in paper towels.
Heat gravy. Cook sandwiches for 2 to 3 minutes or until warm.
Serve with gravy for dipping.

title: christmas porridge(risengrynsgrot)
directions: Put all 4 of the ingredients together in top of a double boiler.
Cover and cook over simmering water 2 1/2 to 3 hours, or until rice is entirely soft when a kernel is pressed between fingers and the mixture is quite thick.
Remove cover for last 10 minutes if mixture is not thick enough.
Serve with cool milk, sugar, cinnamon or serve with a fruit sauce.

title: norma todd's apple butter
directions: Core apples; do not pare.
Cut into pieces.
Cook and put through a food mill.
Mix sugar and water.
Cook in electric roaster.
When cooked down until thick, add oil of cinnamon.
Mix well.
Put in scalded jars.
Seal.
Makes about 16 pints.

title: monkey bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; set aside. Mix shortening, sugar, salt and boiling water. Mix well. Add beaten egg. Add flour and yeast mixture alternately until complete. Let rise in a warm place until doubled. Knead dough well. Pull off pieces about the size of a walnut; dip into butter and place in loaf pan or Bundt pan. Continue filling until pan is 2/3 full. Cover and let rise.

title: reduced fat parmesan chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, parsley and cheese in small bowl.
Coat both sides of chicken in crumb mixture.
Melt margarine in baking dish; add lemon juice.
Coat both sides of chicken with margarine and lemon mixture.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Makes 4 servings, 215 calories; 8 grams fat; 75 mg. cholesterol per serving.

title: 8 hour salad
directions: Tear lettuce in small pieces and place in bottom of pan or dish (with a tight lid).
Layer rest of ingredients in order.
Add sugar to mayonnaise and spread on top like frosting.
Top with grated cheese.
Refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.

title: cranberry mousse
directions: Drain pineapple well, reserving all juice.
Add juice to jello powder in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in water.
Heat to boiling, stirring to dissolve jello.
Remove from heat and blend in cranberry sauce.
Add lemon juice and peel.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in sour cream and pineapple.
Pour into a 2-quart mold; chill until firm.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Brown ground meat; season to taste with salt, pepper and garlic; drain fat.
Return to heat and add soup and green chilies. Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Then dip tortillas in mixture; line a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with tortillas.
Add 1/2 of the meat sauce and 1/2 of the cheese.
Repeat layers as before; top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on. Peel and slice 5 cups. Fry bacon, take out of skillet and saute the onions in the same skillet.
Put potatoes and onions in bowl.

title: sweet buns
directions: Soak together the yeast, 1/2 cup warm water and 1/4 cup sugar. Add the remaining ingredients.
Let rise.
Using flour on a board, form into round, flat buns (sandwich meat size).
Let rise again on the pans.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: german slaw
directions: Grate cabbage and onion.
Add 3/4 cup sugar.
Cover.
Set aside.
Bring to boil, 2 minutes, mustard, celery seed, oil, vinegar, 1 teaspoon sugar and salt; pour over cabbage mixture. Let set 12 or more hours; refrigerate.
Makes 1 to 1 1/2 quarts.

title: herbed barbecued ribs
directions: Cut ribs into serving size pieces.
Place in large, shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over ribs. Cover and marinate in refrigerator 2 hours.
Drain, reserving marinade.
Grill ribs over medium hot coals for 30 minutes, turning frequently.
Grill an additional 15 to 30 minutes, turning and basting frequently with reserved marinade.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: party meatballs
directions: Make meatballs to your own taste, using a mixture of ground beef, egg, bread or cracker crumbs, tomato juice or tomato sauce. Form into small balls and brown in skillet.
Put into dish.

title: onion cheese bread
directions: Saute onion.
In mixing bowl, blend Bisquick mix, egg and milk.
Add onions and 1/2 cup cheese.
Spray pie pan with nonstick spray.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Sprinkle poppy seed. Drizzle melted oleo.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken breast supreme
directions: Whisk sour cream, chicken bouillon, paprika, sage, rosemary, thyme, garlic and pepper.
Coat chicken in mixture, then roll in cracker crumbs.
Bake in baking dish sprayed with nonstick spray at 350° until chicken is done.

title: broccoli and ham quiche
directions: Place ham in partially baked pie shell.
Top with cheeses. Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain.
In mixing bowl combine eggs, flour, whipping cream, salt, pepper, lemon juice and melted butter by stirring with rotary beater or wire whisk.
Add broccoli.
Pour over ham and cheese.
Sprinkle with finely ground bread crumbs if desired.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until set.
Let set a few minutes prior to serving to allow cheese mixture to set.

title: chocolate-chip cake
directions: Heat oven to 350° (325° glass pan).
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan. In large bowl, combine first 9 ingredients.
Blend 1 minute at low speed.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour 1/2 the batter (2 1/2 cups) into greased pan.

title: green bean salad
directions: Combine the beans and green peppers in a bowl.
Mix the last 5 ingredients and pour over the vegetables.
Chill overnight.

title: quick caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add brown sugar.
Cook over low heat 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk, cook until mixture comes to boil.
Remove from heat, cool.

title: hot fruit punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in 4-quart glass bowl.
Microwave 12 to 16 minutes on High or until hot.
Serve in punch cups or coffee cups.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Combine ingredients; add enough flour to make dough stiff. Chill overnight.
Roll out, cut and bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni and cool.
Cut broccoli into small flowerets and steam until crisp.
Drain, rinse and combine.
When cool, add vinegar or white Italian dressing and mix.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Wash and cut squash into chunks; add onion.
Cook in pot of water until squash is tender; drain off water and add all other ingredients.
Stir over low heat until butter or margarine melts. Add 1/2 cup of cheese and 1/2 cup of potato chips.
Mix good; pour half of mixture into cooking dish and top with half of cheese and half of chips.
Add rest of mixture and top with 1 cup of cheese and 1 cup of chips.
Bake at 250° until golden brown.

title: toffee bars
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add flour, egg yolk and vanilla, beating well.
Spread evenly in greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Brush top with egg white.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake at 275° for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from oven.
Cut into bars immediately and cool on wire rack.
Store, tightly covered, at least 3 days before serving.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: three hundred dollar chocolate cake
directions: In a saucepan, combine water, butter, Wesson oil and cocoa; bring to boil and cook for 1 minute. Add buttermilk, beaten eggs and soda; mix thoroughly. Bake in an oblong pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: dishwater cake
directions: Beat sugar, shortening and eggs together.
Add soda to buttermilk.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt together; add alternately with milk, beating well after each.
Add water and vanilla; stir well.
Bake in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package; drain and cool.
Use some of the oil to grease casserole dish; put the rest on the bread crumbs.
Arrange cooked broccoli in dish.
Mix soup, milk, cheese, beaten egg and margarine and pour over broccoli.
Top with oiled bread crumbs and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: herb-butter sauce
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan over medium heat; stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook for 1 to 2 minutes.

title: spinach stuffed shells
directions: Prepare stuffing shells according to package directions; drain.
Whip together Ricotta, egg, Parmesan, salt and pepper. Stir in spinach.
Fill shells equally with cheese mixture.
Pour half of the pasta sauce in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Arrange shells on sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over shells.
Cover; bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Uncover and top with Mozzarella.
Cover; return to oven 5 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Sift flour and soda.
Add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Roll and cut with cutter or glass.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: mikey's biscuits
directions: Add all of dry ingredients.
Sift with hand.
Add in butter. Knead it through the dough.
Add milk.
Knead.
Dust with flour as needed for proper consistency.
Roll out and cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mashed potato crust
directions: Grease pie plate.
Prepare potatoes and 1 slightly beaten egg and green onion.
Spread in pie plate evenly.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until light brown.

title: peanut butter balls candy
directions: Mix all ingredients well and shape into balls.
Melt dipping chocolate and use 2 spoons to dip.
Place on wax paper until cool.

title: special meat loaf
directions: Combine.
Shape the mixture into a loaf about 8 x 4 x 1 1/2-inch and place in a lightly greased shallow baking pan. Brush top with additional Heinz, if desired, and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Allow meat loaf to stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chatters(crab melt-aways)
directions: Let butter and cheese soften.
Mix with mayonnaise and seasonings.
Add crabmeat.
Spread on muffins.
Freeze for 10 minutes, then broil until bubbly.
Cut into quarters like pie slices.
May be made and frozen a couple of weeks in advance.
No thawing necessary.
Makes 5 dozen.
Great for holiday appetizers!

title: cheesecake
directions: Grease the
sides of a 9-inch spring pan.
Put a cookie sheet in
the
middle
of
the oven and heat the oven to 350°. Get creamed cheese to room temperature and set aside.
Process eggs and
sugar.
Add
vanilla.
Put
in
the
softened
cream cheese. Mix
well.
Pour
into spring pan.
Set on the cookie sheet and bake
40 to 50 minutes.
Cool before removing sides of spring pan.

title: linda's easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together; mix with sugar.
Stir in milk, then pour the batter over the melted butter.
Do not stir.
Pour sweetened peaches over the batter.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until golden brown on top.
Serve hot or cold.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: mock boursin cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill.
Remove from refrigerator 1 to 2 hours before serving with celery sticks or crackers.
Best if made a day ahead of time.
Freezes well!

title: golden glow salad
directions: Dissolve jello with boiling water, add marshmallows and stir until they are melted.
Add 7-Up, chill slightly.
Add bananas and pineapple and pour in 14 x 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Refrigerate until congealed.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss broccoli, bacon, raisins, onion and toasted pine nuts in a large bowl. In a small bowl, combine mayo, sugar and vinegar. Fold into broccoli mixture. Store covered in refrigerator.

title: maple cream pie
directions: Blend the milk and the cornstarch, the salt and the maple syrup.
Cook until thickened.
Add beaten eggs and cook one minute more.
Stir in butter and pour into shell.
Whip cream, slowly adding 2 tablespoons maple syrup.
Spread over cooled pie.
Top with toasted nuts, such as thinly sliced almonds.

title: white mountain frosting
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients in microwave on High power for 6 to 7 minutes, until soft ball stage.
Add slowly to beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla; beat until stiff.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and sprinkle nuts and coconut over bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix and pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix confectioners sugar, margarine and cream cheese. Add enough milk to make this the consistency of icing.
Pour over cake and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mother's party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, seasoned salt (optional hot sauce or garlic salt).
Add cereal and nuts. Mix to coat cereal.
Heat in oven 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Store in an airtight container to preserve crispness.
Great munchie for a crowd.

title: flameless cookies
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in saucepan and bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Add cornflakes.
Stir only to coat flakes. Drop on waxed paper.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except cheese. Grease muffin pans and heat "hot".
Pour each pan approximately half full of batter.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Top with remaining batter, then with cheese.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Mix all dry ingredients together, then add to creamed mixture.
Add carrots and nuts.
Pour into two 9-inch greased pans or 9 x 13-inch sheet pan.
Bake for 50 minutes or until done at 350°.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Sprinkle
greased
quiche pan with bacon, cheese, onion and milk.
Mix	remainder
of ingredients in blender and pour over. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 400°.	Cool for 5 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix soup and milk in a casserole dish.
Add drained tuna and 3/4 cup potato chips.
Mix well.
Sprinkle remaining chips on top and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In saucepan, stir together all ingredients.
Stirring frequently, bring to a boil; reduce heat and boil gently 15 minutes to thicken.
Brush on meats, during last 20 minutes of cooking.
Turn frequently.
Makes 2 cups.

title: dorito salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding chips last.
Good with your favorite dressing, Italian, Thousand Island, etc.

title: clam dish casserole("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Beat eggs and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In mixing bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add the onion juice followed by the vinegar.
Use whisk and mix until all the sugar is dissolved.
With a mixer on low speed, slowly add the oil.
You are making an emulsion and it will take a while for the mixture to accept the oil.
Add poppy seed and mix a few moments more.
Makes around 3 1/2 cups.
Cover and keep refrigerated.
This dressing is delicious on fresh fruit.

title: ninja turtles
directions: Place Karo and sugar in large saucepan.
Mix well and heat until boiling.
Stir in peanut butter until well blended.
Remove from fire.
Add cornflakes and mix until cereal is coated. Immediately drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Makes 4 dozen. Store in airtight container.

title: bran muffins
directions: Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Blend jello with boiling water.
Blend in sour cream and fold in blueberry pie filling.
Let set in fridge until ready to serve. Top with Cool Whip when ready to serve.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: lamb, red beans and tomatoes
directions: Mix together the onion, parsley and garlic.
Cut cooked lamb into small pieces.
Brown meat in small amount of oil or in its own fat.
Add onion mixture and saute 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, chili powder and salt (if needed); stir in beans.
Simmer about 20 minutes.
Very good with cornbread.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate coconut candies
directions: Mix mashed potatoes, powdered sugar and extract; stir in coconut.
Drop by rounded teaspoon onto waxed paper or shape into balls (this gets messy).
Refrigerate or freeze until ready to coat with chocolate.
Refrigerate before shaping if too soft and won't hold shape.

title: angela's white enchiladas
directions: To make the sauce, mix together chicken soup, sour cream and 1 can diced chiles.
Set aside.
Mix together cooked chicken, 1 can diced chiles, sliced olives, onion and Jack cheese.
Fry tortillas slightly to soften.
Put some sauce in bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Fill each tortilla with filling and roll up, seam side down.
Pour remaining sauce on top and additional cheese.
Bake in 350° for 30 minutes.
May use Cheddar cheese instead of Jack if preferred.

title: chopped meat and corn bread
directions: Sprinkle salt in an iron frypan (do not grease).
Add the chopped meat and brown.
Add onion, green pepper and tomato sauce. Cook until tender.
Sprinkle top with cheese and cover with corn bread (make according to box directions).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown chicken in pan.
Stir in chicken soup with milk. Transfer to casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over chicken/soup mixture.
Prepare stuffing according to package.
Spread on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: lima beans and franks
directions: Cook beans until tender; drain.
Place beans in an ungreased baking dish (11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch).
Combine tomato sauce, onion, catsup, brown sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and mustard. Pour over beans.
Add franks and cheese.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: burnt spaghetti
directions: Put pan of water on to boil.
Add dry spaghetti.
Keep turned on high.
Leave house and play basketball with kids.
When smoke alarm begins to ring, you know your spaghetti is over ready.
Add Ragu.
In order for this to work, be sure you do do this at Pastor Valimont's home.

title: drunken beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Add chopped onions and saute a few minutes.
Add all other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes. Serve with cornbread.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage and onions until meat is done; drain.
Arrange in layers in large pan as follows: Rice Krispies, sausage, rice, cheese, eggs, soup and milk.
Cover with crushed potato chips. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: dutch oatmeal cake
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water on oats.
Let cool.
Cream brown sugar, sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add oatmeal mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon Dutch Oatmeal Frosting over cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: best chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour baking pan, 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 (9-inch) or 3 (8-inch) round layer pans.
Measure all ingredients into large mixer bowl; blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat for 3 minutes on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour evenly into pan(s).
Bake the oblong pan for 40 to 45 minutes or layers for 30 to 35 minutes, or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients, except oil and celery seed; blend until smooth, on low speed. Continue blending while slowly adding oil. Stir in celery seed. Chill to blend flavors for several hours. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: mystery pudding cake
directions: Mix together; pour into ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: baked bananas
directions: Sprinkle bananas with rum, cinnamon and ginger in shallow baking dish.
Dot with margarine.
Cover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until bananas are tender.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.

title: icing
directions: Mix flour and milk together and cook until thickened.
Cool to lukewarm.
Mix oleo, Crisco, and sugar; beat 4 minutes.
Add flour and milk mixture.
Beat 4 minutes more.
Add vanilla.

title: special fudge cake
directions: Melt chocolate with butter and sugar in double boiler; mix well.
Allow to cool.
Beat eggs and add with flour, vanilla, nuts and baking powder.
Pour into greased pan, 12 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 2-inches or sheet cake pan.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.
Cool before icing.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve with chips and crackers.
Frozen cooked shrimp may be used or cooked fresh shrimp.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Soak yeast in warm (not hot) water for 5 minutes.
Pour milk over sugar and salt in a bowl.
Stir until dissolved.
Beat in eggs, shortening, 1 cup flour and yeast mixture.
Add remaining flour to make a soft dough.
When dough leaves sides of bowl, turn onto a floured board.
Knead until becomes smooth and elastic. Place in lightly greased bowl and grease top of dough.
Cover with wax paper and a damp cloth.
Place in refrigerator immediately. Punch down as it rises; also keep cloth damp.
Shape dough directly from refrigerator into the number of rolls.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Cover; let rise in a warm place for 1 to 2 hours. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen rolls.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt oleo and cocoa.
Add milk, sugar and salt.
Boil for 1 or 2 minutes or until forms soft ball in cold water.
Add oats and nuts.
Drop from spoon on wax paper.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients. Shape into a ball and roll in pecans to cover. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: rice salad
directions: Toss lightly; sprinkle with oil and vinegar.
Add mayonnaise and seasoning.
Let stand a few hours.
Serves 6.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Heat cranberry sauce and strain it.
Mix cranberry liquid, boiling water and gelatin, stirring until completely dissolved. Add the lemon juice and salt.
Chill mixture until slightly thickened, then add the mayonnaise and beat until fluffy.

title: ham casserole
directions: Mix cream of celery soup and milk. Heat over medium heat; stir until warm enough to melt cheese. Add cooked rice and ham. Let stand at least 2 hours to blend flavors. Pour into oiled casserole dish. Dot with butter. Top with crushed corn flakes. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cranberry satin
directions: Chill the juices and 7-Up.
Dissolve the sugar in the juice of the lemons.
Combine these ingredients with care in a pitcher. Add ice cubes, or try it hot.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Put onions in bacon grease and simmer with lid on.
Add all ingredients, except beans, and cook 10 minutes.
Add beans and bake in oven at 400° uncovered for 1 1/2 hours.

title: coconut and oat cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and butter.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cookie press cookies
directions: Cream shortening, adding sugar gradually.
Add unbeaten egg, sifted dry ingredients, flavoring and a few drops of food coloring.
Mix well.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: superb french toast
directions: In a small bowl with rotary beater, beat eggs, milk, sugar and salt until smooth and blended.
In a 9-inch square baking dish, arrange bread in a single layer.
Pour egg mixture over the bread. Turn to coat evenly.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix everything together and place in buttered casserole dish. Bake for 1 hour. Meat loaf should be approximately 1/2-inch from edge.

title: creole doughnuts(beignets)
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, sugar and salt.
Add milk and cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in the half cup lukewarm water and add to cooled mixture with the beaten egg.
Stir in 2 cups flour.
Beat.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Place in greased bowl; grease top of dough; cover and chill until ready to use.
Roll dough to 1/4 inch thickness.
Cut into squares and fry a few at a time in hot oil, brown on both sides.
Do not let dough rise before frying.
Drain and roll in powdered sugar.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream oleo.
Sift together the flour, 1/4 cup powdered sugar and baking powder.
Add gradually to creamed mixture.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
With fingers, shape into crescents and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes, or until brown.
While still hot, roll in powdered sugar. Makes 3 to 4 dozen, depending on size.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box and add bananas and chopped nuts.
Bake in layers.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach to thaw 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain spinach; squeeze out excess moisture.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
In large bowl, cream shortening and sugars. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture, oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet 3-inches apart.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.
Transfer to wire rack to cool.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: italian squash
directions: Slice squash.
Put layer of squash, then layer of tomatoes. Add salt and pepper.
Put hunks of butter on it.
Sprinkle each layer with Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes until almost done, then top with Velveeta cheese.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: parmesan breaded chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a shallow bowl.
Dip chicken in milk and roll in bread crumb/herb mixture.
Coat a baking pan with cooking spray.
Place chicken (bone side down) on pan.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 25 minutes; remove cover and bake another 20 minutes or until done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dilled okra
directions: Boil together vinegar, water and pickling salt.
Put dill and garlic, sliced, in bottom of pint jar.
Add okra and 1 pod hot red pepper.
Pour vinegar mixture over and seal jars.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots (not too soft).
Mix other ingredients and cook until thick, about 15 minutes.
Add hot carrots and marinate 24 hours.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: In a bowl, mix sour cream, soup, butter and onions.
Salt and pepper to taste.
In 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish or 3-quart casserole, layer half of the potatoes, half of the cream mixture and 3/4 of the cheese.
Repeat until all the ingredients are used up.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Add coconut and toss together lightly with 2 forks.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, Crisco, sugar and salt with pastry blender.
Beat egg.
Add the water and vinegar and mix well.
Combine the two mixtures, a little at a time, until all dry ingredients are moist. Mold together with your hands.
(You can't handle too much.) Chill before rolling, or keep in refrigerator up to a week or you can freeze.
Prick shell well before baking.

title: squash muffins
directions: Mix together squash, butter and vanilla.
Set aside.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Add to squash mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes until golden brown in a 375 degree oven.

title: spaghetti sauce(germany)
directions: Dice and cook in oil green pepper, onion, celery and garlic. Add bay leaf, whole clove, parsley and tomatoes or puree.
Simmer slowly until sauce is thick.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Mix in beaten eggs and oil.
Fold in bananas, pineapple and nuts until well mixed by hand.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan.
Fold in batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: oven chicken and rice
directions: Place rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Place fryer parts on rice.
Sprinkle on soup mix, seasoning, pepper and paprika.
Mix celery soup and water; pour over all.
Cover and bake in preheated oven at 325° for 2 hours.

title: a~b~c - almond, broccoli, chicken
directions: Cut broccoli into florets.
Boil for 2 minutes until soft but still green.
Drain and put into ice water; set aside.
Spread almonds on cookie sheet; put into 350° oven and toast.
Put 1 tablespoon olive oil in nonstick saut pan.
Heat to just smoking. Dust chicken strips in flour and place in pan away from you.
As the strips brown, turn.
About 2 minutes, remove chicken; discard oil and wipe pan clean.
Return to stove; add 1 teaspoon olive oil and onions.
Cook until opaque.
Add garlic but don't brown.
Add white wine or stock; reduce by 1/2 and add heavy cream.
Stir occasionally over low heat until it coats wooden spoon.
Add chicken, broccoli and almonds; let simmer 1 minute.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add the fettuccini (previously cooked, cooled and set aside).
Toss all ingredients lightly in pan until pasta is hot.
Turn out onto serving dish; sprinkle with cheese and enjoy.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine over low heat; remove from heat and stir in milk.
In a large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Beat in one egg at a time.
Add vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Gradually blend in chocolate mixture.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Combine coconut and pecans.
Sprinkle over top of filling.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Filling will set as pie cooks.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend Crisco and sugars.
Beat in vanilla, water and egg until creamy.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together.
Add the creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in M&M's and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baked string beans
directions: Lightly mix green beans, soup and 1/2 can onions. Season with soy sauce and pepper. Spoon into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° until sauce is bubbling (20 to 30 minutes).
Top with remaining onions. Bake 4 minutes longer. Serves 6.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Mix
together and put in 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: tang pie
directions: Mix Tang and milk together. Add sour cream and vanilla; mix well. Add Cool Whip and mix. Pour in pie crust and refrigerate until firm.

title: delicious chicken dish
directions: Mix the dry oxtail and vegetable soup powders. Roll each chicken portion in the mixture until well covered. Place the portions in a casserole. Mix the water and chutney.
Pour over the thighs.
Cover casserole and cook for 45 minutes on the center shelf of the oven. Remove the lid and bake until the thighs begin to brown.
Remember no salt must be added as the soup powders already have salt.

title: country chicken n' biscuits
directions: In greased oblong cake pan, combine first 3 ingredients and 1 cup cheese.
Blend soup and 3/4 cup milk in saucepan, pour over casserole.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine Bisquick, 2/3 cup milk and 1/2 cup onion rings; mix.
Drop by spoonfuls 6 biscuits around edge.
Bake, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: microwaved baked apples
directions: Core apples (any variety except Red Delicious), leaving blossom end intact.
Peel away skin from top (about 1/4 way down), to prevent bursting.
Fill apples with butter, sugar and raisins. Add cinnamon dash on top.
Add 2 tablespoons of water to dish. Microwave covered on High 5 minutes.
Cook until tender.
Serve with cream or ice cream.

title: party roll-ups
directions: Blend dressing and cream cheese and spread on tortillas.

title: eggplant enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onions and garlic in olive oil in a large skillet.
Add salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally for about 5 minutes.
Add eggplant.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Mix. Cover and cook about 10 minutes or until eggplant is soft.
Add green peppers, almonds and black pepper.
Cook another 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and add cheese. Mix.

title: shrimp mold
directions: In double boiler, melt cheese.
Mash soup in and blend Knox gelatine.
Let cool.
Add one cup mayonnaise, celery, onions, green peppers and shrimp.
Pour in buttered mold.
Refrigerate.

title: sesame chicken
directions: In a nonstick skillet toast sesame seeds over medium to high heat.
Set aside.
Cut chicken breasts to 1/4-inch thickness (or pound to 1/4-inch thickness).
Heat oil in nonstick skillet over medium to high heat.
Add chicken; cook for 3 minutes each side or until lightly brown.
Combine sesame seeds, honey, soy sauce and ginger; pour over chicken and cook 4 minutes, turning chicken to coat with sauce.
Serve sauce over chicken.
Serves 4.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Cook hamburg and onions. Spread in dish. Sprinkle with cheese. Stir remaining ingredients together and pour on top. Bake 25 minutes at 375°.

title: avocado and chive sandwiches
directions: Peel and remove seed from a ripe avocado.
Mash with a silver fork and mix into it 2 tablespoons chopped chives and lemon juice. Season with salt.
Spread between thin slices whole wheat bread (or use one slice whole wheat and one white).
Trim and cut into triangles.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles with points toward center in a greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Press bottom and sides to form a crust.
Seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over dough.
Sprinkle with hash browns and Cheddar cheese. Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage mixture. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: golden apple cake
directions: Core and slice 1 apple.
Arrange slices in bottom of well-greased Bundt type pan.
Pare, core and finely chop remaining apples to 1 1/2 cups.
Cream margarine and sugars until light. Beat in eggs, orange juice and peel.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Fold in chopped apples.
Spoon over apple slices in pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until pick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Turn onto plate.
Serve warm or cold.

title: beef stew casserole
directions: Combine
the
soup, soup mix and sherry and spread over the meat
in a prepared casserole dish.
Bake, covered, for 3 hours at
Mushrooms
may
be
added and are very good. This dish is very, very good and easy to make!

title: green chili casserole
directions: Dip tortillas in melted margarine and place 4 in bottom of casserole dish.
Separate cheese, chilies and onions into 3 portions.
Spread 1/3 of each over tortillas.
Repeat process until ingredients are all used.
Mix soup with milk; pour over casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: goody grape salad
directions: Wash and dry grapes.
Place in medium bowl.
Blend sour cream, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over grapes; stir.
Scatter brown sugar on top.
Marinate overnight.

title: uncle willard's brownies
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt; set aside. In large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla. Beat until creamy. Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour mixture and mix well. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Spread in 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Cool and cut into 2-inch squares.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg yolks and add granulated sugar, melted butter, flour and juice of lemon and also use lemon rind (grated).
Add milk and add beaten egg whites.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in oven at 450°.
After 10 minutes in oven, reduce heat for rest of the time.

title: "j-kids" favorite two handed oatmeal cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar, peanut butter, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Drop dough from an ice cream scoop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 14 to 16 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: individual taco salad shells
directions: Heat oil in deep fryer to 375°.
Place one tortilla in oil. Let float 5 to 10 seconds.
Press center of tortilla down with a metal ladle.
Tortilla will form a bowl shape around ladle.
Hold down and fry 1 to 2 minutes longer or until a golden brown color. Drain upside down on paper towels until completely cooled before filling.

title: butter rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Dissolve butter, sugar and salt in 3/4 cup of hot water.
Allow to cool.
Beat egg and add to lukewarm butter mixture.
Add yeast water.
Add flour and mix well. Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Take out; knead a little. Roll out; cut and let rise at room temperature for about 2 1/2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: bushel basket cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add the rest of ingredients and mix well.
Drop with teaspoon and bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Makes 1 bushel of cookies.
Freezes well.

title: no bake million dollar pie
directions: Mix peaches and pineapple.
Pour over condensed milk.
Fold in juice of 2 lemons, coconut and pecans.
Then fold in Cool Whip. Pour in pie shells.
Chill for an hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: nine day pickles
directions: Wash pickles and slice.
Add 1 cup salt to every gallon and add boiling water.
Let stand 3 days.
Take out and wash.
Put 3 tablespoons alum in plain water; let stand 3 days.
Take out and wash pickles.
Heat vinegar, spices and sugar (1 cup sugar to 1 cup vinegar). Pour over pickles and let stand 3 days.
Put in jars.
Heat vinegar mixture and seal.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Blend butter and flour in saucepan.
Gradually stir in half and half; cook until thickened.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat until mixture is thoroughly heated, being careful not to burn bottom of saucepan.
Serve over toast or pastry shells.
Serves 4.

title: cabbage au gratin soup
directions: Saute cabbage and onions in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, caraway, salt, pepper and paprika.
Remove from heat; gradually stir in milk.
Bring to boil over medium heat and add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Return to heat if necessary to melt cheese but do not boil.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Saute vegetables in oleo until tender.
Add crawfish and soups.
Heat well until bubbly. Stir in rice and bread crumbs. Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Top with additional bread crumbs. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
You may add 1/2 pound crab meat.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: Mix well and leave at room temperature for 8 to 12 hours. Pour off 1 cup of Starter to make bread and return remaining Starter to refrigerator.
To keep Starter going, feed every 5 to 7 days.

title: french oven beef stew
directions: Combine beef, onion, celery and carrots in a 4-quart casserole. In a small bowl, combine tomato or V-8 juice, tapioca, sugar, pepper and basil.
Pour over meat and veggies.
Cover; bake in a preheated 300° oven for about 2 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes.
Cover. Cook 1 hour longer.
Stir occasionally during last hour.
Serves 6.

title: deluxe sugar cookies(5 dozen)
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg.
Add flavorings.
Sift flour, soda and cream of tartar and add to mixture.
Drop and cook in 375° oven for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: meringue
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in cold water.
Add 1/2 cup boiling water. Cook until thickened on low flame, stirring constantly.
Set aside to cool.
Beat egg whites for meringue.
Add sugar, little at a time.
Add cornstarch mixture.
Bake at 325° or 350° for about 15 minutes (until a little brown).

title: artichoke dip
directions: Defrost artichokes and drain well.
Cut into small pieces or put into a food processor to chop.
Mix in mayonnaise, grated cheese, lemon juice and garlic powder.
Bake at 350° until bubbly. Serve warm with crackers or vegetables.

title: crockery barbecue beef
directions: Mix cola, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, garlic, bouillon, mustard, chili powder and red pepper; reserve 1/2 cup sauce. Place meat in a slow cooker with onions; pour sauce over.
Cook 10 to 12 hours on low.

title: flour frosting
directions: Mix Flour and milk, cook until it is a smooth thick paste, cool well.
Add remaining ingredients and beat together until fluffy, the longer the better.

title: low-fat lime jello salad
directions: Empty can of pineapple with juice into a saucepan.
Add jello; mix and heat on low until dissolved.
Cool.
Mix in Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Put mixture into jello mold or bowl; refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: greek-style eggplant sauce(with fusilli)
directions: In a medium saucepan in 2 teaspoons oil over medium heat, cook the chopped onion and garlic until vegetables soften, about 5 minutes.
Add the chopped ripe tomatoes, basil leaves, salt, pepper and hot red pepper flakes to taste.
Bring to a boil. Cover; reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients and combine with corn meal.
Mix eggs and milk and add with melted shortening.
Beat until smooth.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes.
Cool and dice.
Place in baking dish.
Fry bacon with minced garlic.
Stir in flour and sugar.
Add mixed vinegar and water slowly.
Stir until sauce is formed, then add onion.
Pour hot sauce over potatoes and season to taste.
Bake at 300° for 1/2 hour.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Beat on medium speed the flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, mixed with bananas, salt, shortening and 1/2 cup milk for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and 1/3 cup milk.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 to 35 minutes for layers or 45 minutes for oblong cake.

title: strawberries romanoff
directions: This is an old fashioned dessert to serve your special guests.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook noodles partly done, according to directions on box.
Fry hamburger, onion and pepper.
Mix spaghetti sauce into cooked hamburger and onion.
Spread thin layer of sauce in bottom of pan. Next layer noodles, thin layer of sauce mix, then cheese.
Continue to layer in this order.
Finish top with remaining sauce mix and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: husband pleasin' beans
directions: Brown beef and onions in margarine and combine with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: divinity
directions: Cook first four ingredients over medium heat until soft ball forms in water.
Take out 1/2 cup of mixture and pour over egg whites.
(Mix thoroughly and set aside.)

Continue cooking sugar mixture to hard ball stage or until it spins a thread when held up on spoon. Add to egg white mixture, beating constantly. Add vanilla and/or nuts, cherries, walnuts, etc. for variety.

title: macaroni pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions together (drain).
Mix with macaroni. Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
Toss well.
Top with cheese and pepperoni (optional).
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: zucchini casserole(microwave)
directions: Microwave sliced zucchini a few minutes or until slightly cooked, not mushy.
Combine with rest of ingredients and cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, in the microwave oven.
This can also be cooked in the crock-pot or in the oven.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare 2 loaf pans, grease and flour. Mix ingredients and pour into pans.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: sour cream-noodle bake
directions: Brown beef in butter; add seasonings and tomato sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, scallions and noodles.
In a 2-quart casserole, alternate layers, starting with noodles and ending with meat.
Top with cheese; bake until cheese melts and browns at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: turkey and apple sausage patties
directions: *In a blender or food processor, process bread until fine crumbs form.
Three slices = 1 cup.

title: creamed green and wax beans
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Blend in flour and gradually add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture comes to boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add salt and drained beans.
Pour in baking dish and top with cheese and corn flakes.
Bake.

title: fruit topping (green stuff)
directions: Combine all ingredients (do not drain fruit).
Refrigerate until served.
Can be served over pound cake, angel food cake or plain.

title: fantasy fruit bars
directions: Combine mix, oats, margarine and egg.
Save 1 1/4 cups.
Press remaining mix in a 15 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.
Heat Starburst and milk in heavy pan over low heat. Pour over semi-baked crust leaving 1/2-inch around edge.
Combine reserved crumbs nuts and coconut.
Sprinkle over candy mixture. Bake 18 to 22 minutes or until golden.
Cool and cut.

title: butterscotch krispies
directions: Melt butterscotch and peanut butter over hot water.
Stir in Rice Krispies; pour into 12 x 9-inch dish.
Chill in refrigerator about 1 hour, until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: baked onion custard
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add onion and 1/4 cup cream. Cook over low heat until onions are tender (5 minutes).
Measure 1/4 cup onion mixture into 9 (5 ounce) custard cups.
Beat eggs, remaining cream, salt and pepper until light.
Pour an equal amount (2 1/2 tablespoons) over each cup of onions and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Set custard cups in a pan of hot water and bake in a preheated oven at 350°
for 25 to 30 minutes or when custard is "set" or firm.
You may use one larger baking dish, but cooking time will be longer.
Serve hot.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all except butter and Ritz crackers.
Put in greased baking dish.
Melt butter and mix with crumbs.
Spread on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: crawfish fettucini
directions: Saute seasonings in butter for 20 minutes. Add crawfish tails and cook for 15 minutes. Dissolve flour in half and half and add to cheese. Add parsley.
Mix all ingredients into crawfish mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: venison in sauce
directions: Sear meat quickly in hot oil in skillet.
Remove from skillet and drain.
Put in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well and cook at least 3 hours.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins.
Cool, peel, then dice.
Cook eggs; cool in cold water, then peel.
Slice into potatoes.
Cut bacon into pieces; fry until brown.
Drain grease; add bacon to potatoes.
Using 2 spoons of bacon grease, fry diced onion until golden brown.
Add onion and grease to potatoes.
Add mustard, sliced pickles, 2 spoons pickle juice and 1 spoon water.
Add 4 spoons (or amount desired) mayonnaise.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower into bite-size pieces.
Dressing is a mix of mayo and sour cream until it doesn't taste like either one.
Add onion, 2 tablespoons of bacon bits and seasoning.

title: lemon meringue pie(easy)
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in microwaveable bowl. Add 1 1/2 cups water. Stir, then add egg yolks, butter, lemon juice and rind. Mix with mixer about 2 minutes. Cook in microwave oven on High 2 minutes. Take out and stir well. Place in microwave 2 minutes. Stir. Repeat until mixture thickens; cool. Pour in pie shell. Top with meringue. Heat conventional oven to 400°. Place pie in oven until meringue lightly browns. Cool.

title: sweet pickle chips
directions: Heat last 4 ingredients, stirring to dissolve the sugar and bring to a boil.
Pour boiling mixture over hot cukes.
Makes approximately 6 pints.

title: maple praline cookies(makes 4 dozen)
directions: In large bowl, cream sugar and shortening until light.
Beat in eggs.
Stir in milk and maple flavoring.
Mixture will appear curdled.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in cereal.
Drop dough from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet, about 2-inches apart.
Flatten with bottom of tumbler, dipped in sugar.
Top each with pecan half.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Make cookie mix as directed.
Put in pizza pan.
Cook about 8 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Put on top of cookie layer.
Add pineapple, then bananas.
Mix fruit cocktail and glaze together and pour on top of pizza.

title: never fail caramel icing
directions: Put 2 cups sugar and the milk in a boiler to cook.
Brown the other 1/2 cup sugar in a separate container.
When it is light brown, add the water; then add the first mixture.
Cook until it forms a soft ball.
Take from heat and add oleo.
Beat until creamy.

title: jiffy rolls
directions: Add water to yeast and sugar and set aside.
Scald milk.
Pour over shortening and salt.
Add egg, yeast mixture and flour.
Beat smooth.
Let rise until double in size.
Roll out and let rise again.
Bake in oven at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
These are ready for oven in about 1 hour or 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: green bean-mushroom casserole
directions: Cook beans according to package.
Drain and place in a baking pan.
Add mushrooms.
Add soup and milk.
Top with French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a graham cracker crust or a vanilla wafer crust.

title: orange jello mold
directions: Mix both packages of jello with the boiling water.
Add pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Let it set until it thickens. Whip the package of Dream Whip.
Add salad dressing to Dream Whip. Add part of the jello to Dream Whip mixture, then add all to jello. Put in mold and let set.

title: beefed up casserole
directions: In large frying pan, brown ground beef, onion and green pepper; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, chili powder and garlic salt.
Simmer while preparing dough.
Separate biscuit dough into 10 biscuits; pull apart each into 2 layers.
Press 10 biscuit layers over bottom of ungreased 8 or 9-inch square baking pan. Combine 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream and egg; mix well.
Remove meat mixture from heat; stir in sour cream mixture.
Spoon over dough. Arrange remaining biscuit layers on top; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, until biscuits are deep golden brown.

title: oat bran muffins(low-fat)
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins.
Add all other ingredients and mix.
Do not overmix, just enough to moisten well.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes in muffin pans sprayed with Pam.
This batter can be stored in refrigerator and baked as needed.
It will last for 2 to 3 weeks.
Muffins freeze well also.
Will make 36 large muffins.

title: aunt shirley's apple crisp
directions: In 10 x 6-inch baking dish layer apple slices.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, salt and water.
In medium bowl combine flour, sugar and oleo.
Mix with hand until crumbly.
Cover apple slices evenly with crumble mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with milk or ice cream.

title: fruit salad
directions: Any other fruit you would like to add may be added.

title: thrifty pound cake
directions: Pour into tube pan and bake at 325° for one hour.

title: casserole of chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Wash and dry the chicken pieces and lightly dust with flour.
Heat oil in skillet and quickly brown the chicken pieces.
Put chicken into casserole with lid; add the remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake 1 hour.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream together butter, peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar. Add to mixture the egg and vanilla and mix well.
Then add the remaining ingredients.
Preheat oven to 375°; bake for 8 minutes and then add Kisses and bake again for 2 to 5 minutes.

title: mexican soup
directions: In Dutch oven, cook ground beef and onion until meat is browned and onion tender. Drain. Add rest of ingredients (do not drain). Stir together and simmer about 1 hour. Top servings with grated cheese and Fritos. If too thick, add V-8 juice.

title: nancy lee's broccoli, cheese and rice casserole
directions: Grease 4-quart casserole, 15 x 10 x 2-inch.
Put a layer of rice.
Mix soup with some milk and pour over rice.
Next layer the cooked broccoli.
Put remaining rice over the broccoli, then pour the remaining soup mixture.
Top it all off with slices of Cheddar cheese.
If necessary, add milk so it will not bake dry. Bake in moderate oven until mixture bubbles and cheese melts.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks; beat well.
Add milk, flour, salt, lemon juice and grated rind.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 375° until set, about 35 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: *Can substitute with cream of mushroom soup.

title: pasta primavera with a twist
directions: Prepare macaroni per package directions.
In 2-quart saucepan, combine soup, milk, cheese, garlic powder and pepper.
Add broccoli and carrots.
Bring to boil over medium heat.
Cover; cook over low heat 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring often.
Add chicken; heat thoroughly, stirring often. Serve over macaroni; toss before serving.

title: pumpkin pie recipe(makes one 9-inch pie)
directions: In large bowl, combine eggs, pumpkin, sugar, salt, cinnamon, ginger, cloves and evaporated milk.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake for an additional 40 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Top with cooled pie as desired.

title: beef and rice fiesta
directions: Brown the sirloin in skillet.
Add the onion, garlic and garlic powder.
Cook over medium heat until tender.
Add water, mushroom soup, corn, salt and chili powder; bring to a boil.
Stir in Minute rice.
Add tomato and bell pepper.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Fluff with fork.
Makes approximately 6 cups.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Mix gelatin, boiling water and lemon juice; set aside to cool slightly.

title: quick pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: aunt ethel's corn casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package. Add corn and can of soup. Stir in cheese and chopped chicken.
Pour in casserole dish. Sprinkle with grated cheese and heat in microwave until cheese melts.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Melt cheese with milk in double boiler.
Saute onion and celery in little oleo until color turns clear.
Add:

title: dill pickles made sweet
directions: Mix all ingredients except pickles and pour over pickles in jar; let sit for one week, stirring or shaking occasionally.

title: avocado-grapefruit salad
directions: Place grapefruit in a casserole dish.
Arrange slices of avocado in a circular design on top of grapefruit.
Pour some Catalina on the top.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Spread the chicken and vegetables evenly in prepared dish.
Stir together soup, broth and pepper in small mixing bowl.
Pour evenly over chicken mixture.
Combine Recip-Ease baking mix, milk and margarine in separate bowl, stir until smooth.
Pour the flour mixture over ingredients in baking dish.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: garlic dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate 24 hours before using. Increase garlic to desired taste.

title: diet mexican dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place the beans, taco seasoning and olives in a large saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring until ingredients are blended and hot.
Pour mixture into 8 x 12 x 2-inch casserole.
Spread the taco sauce over the bean mixture. Place the casserole in the freezer for 1 hour or until taco sauce is somewhat solid.

title: baked chicken souffle
directions: Cut crusts off bread and cube.
Dice chicken.
Drain mushrooms and slice.
Drain water chestnuts and slice.
Layer these ingredients, mayonnaise and cheese.
May freeze this.
Mix the eggs, milk and soup.
Pour over thawed layers and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Add 2 cups buttered bread crumbs and return to oven for 15 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: raspberry cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour bottom and sides of spring-form pan.
Combine flour and 3/4 cup sugar.
Cut in oleo until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup of mixture.
To remaining mixture, add baking powder, baking soda, salt, sour cream, 1 egg and almond extract.
Blend well.
Spread this mixture on bottom of pan and 2-inches up the sides.
Mixture is thick.
Blend softened cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 egg. Pour into center of dough and spread evenly.
Spoon raspberry jam over cheese mixture.
Sprinkle the cup of reserved crumbs over top. Top with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Spread butter all around the bottom and sides of a 13 x 9-inch cake pan and set aside.
Shake out any excess flour.
Put 6 ounces of butter and the sugar into a medium-size bowl and cream until well blended and smooth.
Scrape down sides with rubber spatula.
Crack 1 egg at a time and drop directly into the batter. Beat well after each addition and continue to beat until batter is smooth.	Add lemon peel, lemon juice and vanilla and mix well.

title: lollipop sugar cookies
directions: You will also need 24 to 30 flat ice cream sticks.

title: decorator's frosting
directions: Cream softened margarine and Crisco together until light and fluffy.
Gradually add vanilla and sugar, about 1 cup at a time, beating slowly.
Scrape bowl often.
Add milk and coloring.
Beat until smooth.
Keep covered with damp cloth.
Makes 3 cups frosting.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown meat lightly in melted oleo or oil. Combine water, sugar, vinegar, cornstarch, salt and pineapple juice. Cook in saucepan until clear and slightly thickened. Pour sauce over meat. Cover and cook 30 minutes on medium heat. Add pineapple chunks, green peppers and onions. Cook 2 minutes longer. Serve with fried rice or plain cooked rice. Makes 7 servings.

title: homemade turkey pot pie
directions: Mix soups, veggies and turkey.
Get nice and hot.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Bake at 375° until crust is brown. Spread egg on top of crust when pie is just about done.

title: oriental green beans
directions: Prepare sauce by cooking
onion with ginger in hot oil. In 1 quart saucepan over
medium heat cook until tender, about 5 minutes.
In cup blend
broth
and
soy
sauce smoothly with cornstarch.
Add broth
mixture
to
saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.

title: baked beans
directions: Put 1 tablespoon of margarine in a black skillet.
Allow this to melt; add 1 chopped small white onion and 1 medium green bell pepper.
Saute these and set aside.
Brown 1 pound of ground beef, stirring it to separate as it cooks.
Drain the oil from the meat and then add this to the onion and pepper.
Add 1 large can beans, stir in 1 packed cup of brown sugar and 1/2 cup barbecue sauce.
Stir so that the sugar and sauce is mixed into the beans and meat.
Turn heat to low and let the ingredients simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: easy french bread
directions: Soak yeast in water 5 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and beat with electric mixer.
Work on board and knead until smooth. Place in greased bowl and cover.
Let raise 1 hour.
Roll dough to 15 x 8-inch oblong roll up like jelly roll taper ends.

title: baked potato elegante
directions: Rub potato with oil; split lengthwise.
Place onion slice between halves.
Wrap bacon around potato and then wrap with foil. Bake at 400° for about 1 hour.

title: italian pepper bread
directions: Combine
onion and
water;
let
stand	10
minutes
to soften.
Grease 8-inch round
cake	pan.
Prepare hot roll mix according to package directions;
set
aside
5 minutes.
On a floured board, shape dough	into 7 inch circle.
Place in pan. Let rise in warm place	until
doubled	in size, 30 to 60 minutes. Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake until bread is golden brown and sounds hollow when
tapped with fingers, about 25 minutes. Remove from pan; cool on a rack.
Makes 10 slices.

title: sweet potato croquettes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except flour, bread crumbs and oil. Shape mixture into rolls measuring approximately 1 x 2. Roll in flour, then in bread crumbs. Fry in very hot oil until brown. Drain on paper towels.

title: quick and easy lasagna
directions: Prepare 9 to 12 lasagna noodles as directed on package.
Cook hamburger; drain; then add sauce and cheeses.
Layer hamburger mixture and then noodles; repeat until finished.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Easy, but delicious.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Scald milk and let cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 cup sugar, shortening and salt.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dissolve the milk powder in water. Combine the sugar, salt, flour, cornmeal and baking powder in mixing bowl and blend well.
Stir in the water mixture, oil and eggs.
(You may need to add a bit more water for a smooth consistency.)
Fold in diced peppers, cayenne pepper and the cheeses.
Add the corn and a drop or 2 of Tabasco sauce if you like a really spicy cornbread.
Spoon into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake 1 hour.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.
tags: fresh from the cob corn kernels

title: mattie's pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease Bundt pan.
Beat butter, sugar, flour, soda, salt, pineapple yogurt, eggs and vanilla on low speed in large bowl.
Sift the flour twice.
Blend well.
Increase speed to medium and beat 3 minutes.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
When cake is cool, mix together confectioners sugar and lemon juice in a small bowl until smooth. Drizzle over cake.

title: garlic bubble
directions: Thaw and soften dough.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Cut off pieces of dough the size of walnuts.
Dip into butter mixture. Place pieces into greased loaf pan until all dough is used.
Cover with cloth until the dough is double in size.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Brush with butter.

title: italian sausage bread
directions: Remove sausage from casing and brown well.
Drain and cool on paper towel.
Mix sausage, both cheeses and 1 egg.
Roll dough on floured surface to approximately 10-inch round.
Fill with mixture and pinch ends together to form a loaf shape.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Paint top with beaten egg white.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake 10 minutes at 450° and then approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook
beans
on
top
of stove in lightly salted water. Mix with other ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole and bake
15 or 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Before placing casserole in oven cover with slivered almonds.
Do not overcook beans in salted water as they will cook more in oven.

title: angel date balls
directions: Combine dates, sugar and eggs.
Cook until thick on medium heat.
Cool, stir in cereal and nuts.
Shape into balls about one inch in diameter.
Roll in coconut.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Combine cauliflower, broccoli and onion; toss well.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Stir in seasoning mix and water.
Place rolls in ungreased 9 to 10-inch pan to form a crust.
Line crust with half of chips.
Add meat; spread sour cream over meat.
Cover with American cheese slices and shredded Cheddar.
Sprinkle top with rest of chips.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: shrimp party sandwiches
directions: Mash cream cheese; add lemon juice, onion, celery and salt. Stir in shrimp which has been broken into small pieces.
Let stand at least 1 hour before serving between buttered bread rounds. (Could be used as dip on favorite chips.)

title: chocolate pie deluxe
directions: Bake pie shell.
Heat marshmallows, milk and chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly, just until chocolate and marshmallows are melted and mixture is smooth.
Refrigerate, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in skins for 30 minutes; peel and slice 1/2 of the potatoes in the bottom of ovensafe dish.
Layer with 1/2 the chopped onion, mushrooms, garlic powder, salt, pepper, cream of mushroom soup, sour cream and cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: iron skillet chocolate pie
directions: Melt butter in iron skillet.
Add sugar, flour and cocoa. After these ingredients have been mixed together, beat egg yolks and add milk.
Add to mixture in skillet.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Put in cooked pie shell.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Beat together shortening, sugar and salt.
When creamy, add boiling water. Stir well. When lukewarm, add well beaten eggs and yeast dissolved in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Add remainder of water. Stir in flour. Beat well. Cover and place in refrigerator. When ready to bake, shape into rolls.
Let rise 2 to 3 hours. Bake at 450° until done.

title: chocolate pie(sugar-free)
directions: Make 2 layers of chocolate pudding.
Put Cool Whip on top.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, salt, spices, milk and butter to mashed potatoes.
Mix well and pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
I use three shallow pie shells.

title: mince meat bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix only until combined.
Spoon into greased loaf
pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Freezes well.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Cream butter until smooth. Gradually add sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating 3 minutes after each at highest speed (it helps to have a good book or great music on loud to get through this part). Add cooled chocolate and vanilla. Beat well. Pour into pie shell. Chill 2 hours. Top with whipped cream and nuts. Very rich. Serve in small pieces.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: In a 5-quart kettle or Dutch oven, cook beef and onion over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until beef is browned, 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain off any fat.
Stir in celery and cook 3 minutes. Mix in crushed tomatoes, broth, water, 3 cups Swiss chard, rice, basil and thyme.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to medium; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in remaining 3 cups Swiss chard and salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook 5 minutes longer.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, butter, eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla. Pour into buttered casserole.

title: tomato soup
directions: Mix tomatoes, broth, margarine, onion and sugar. Simmer 1/2 hour. Pour hot mixture SLOWLY into half and half and then pour slowly back into cooking pan and heat. Do not boil.

title: amish apple pie
directions: Place apples in unbaked pie crust.
Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Add cream, egg and vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour over apples.
Bake on lowest rack of oven for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Put chicken in buttered oblong casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken. Crush the crackers and mix with poppy seed and oleo. Sprinkle on top
of casserole mixture.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350° until bubbly.

title: vegetable cheese casserole
directions: Cook vegetables and drain.
Melt butter.
Add garlic powder and 1/2 of the crushed crackers.
Mix with vegetables.
Cut up Velveeta cheese into vegetable mix.
Sprinkle top of casserole with the other 1/2 of the crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil noodles until soft and set aside. Cook together soups, milk and cheese.
Steam broccoli until soft. In a large bowl, combine all ingredients and pour into sprayed 9 x 13 dish.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple-orange cake
directions: Add cake mix, oranges, oil and eggs.
Mix together well.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes in 2 round layer pans.
Let cool.
Cut each layer in half; mix remaining ingredients and spread on layers.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Mix dissolved yeast, sugar, eggs and 1 cup warm water.
Add oil, salt and flour.
Let stand 8 hours or overnight.

title: tofu parmigiana(serve with tossed salad and crisp bread.)
directions: Drain tofu, then cut in 12 even slices.
Arrange in a flat pan or dish.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients together.
Toss bread crumbs with butter and put on squash.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
(Cook onion and bell pepper a little before mixing with other ingredients.)

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix and press into 9-inch spring-form pan, about 1/2-inch up sides of pan.
Chill until set.

title: hash
directions: (I let stew meat, onions, salt and pepper cool and remove any fat from meat.)
Mash with potato masher.
Add vinegar, sugar, catsup and chili powder.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve over rice or in buns as sandwiches with barbecue slaw.

title: super skillet pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt margarine	in large skillet and brush up on sides. Sprinkle
the
brown
sugar
over
margarine.
Place pineapple rings over bottom and put cherries in the middle of the rings. Sprinkle
pecans
over all.
Spread the crushed pineapple over the nut layer.

title: rolled sugar cookies(diabetic)
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar, vanilla and egg.
Add the flour, orange juice and baking powder, and mix until dough is workable but not sticky.
Roll out onto a floured surface and cut into shapes.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: cookies
directions: In a medium mixing bowl combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and oats.
In a large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine and peanut butter until smooth.
Beat in sugars until blended.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture by hand; mix well.
Shape into 2-inch balls.
Place 6 balls on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten each to 3-inch diameter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 17 minutes or until golden.

title: anne pepper's cheese pudding
directions: In a greased baking dish place a layer of cracker crumbs, moisten with half of the white sauce, next add layer of cheese, then a layer of pimentos and eggs.
Repeat these layers.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
