Bake, covered, at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: carol's cookies
directions: You will need a 1-sided cookie sheet.

title: puppy chow
directions: In a saucepan, melt chocolate bits, peanut butter and butter. Pour mixture over Rice Chex and stir so that all the cereal is covered.
Put one cup of confectioners sugar in a paper bag and put in the cereal mixture.
Top with the other cup of sugar and shake the bag to thoroughly coat the cereal.
Serve in a dog dish.

title: crescent streusel strip
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
On ungreased cookie sheet unroll dough into 2 long rectangles.
Overlap long sides by 1/2-inch.
Firmly press edges and perforations to seal.
Roll to form a 13 x 19-inch rectangle.
Combine brown sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Blend in butter until well mixed.
Spread over half of lengthwise dough to within 1/2-inch of edge.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Fold dough in half lengthwise over brown sugar mixture.
Firmly press edges with fork to seal.
Brush with milk and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake 16 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes before serving. Yields 12 strips.

title: hot fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine.
Add the rest of the ingredients; boil for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Drain juice from pickles and save.
Slice pickles in spears and put back in jar. Add a little sugar as you put the pickles in jar.
When jar is about half full, put in Tabasco sauce and tarragon vinegar, then put the rest of the pickles and sugar in jar.
Put back the juice that was saved.
Leave on cabinet for 12 hours, shaking jug every so often to dissolve sugar. Store in refrigerator to keep crisp.

title: lemon lust
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and pecans and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and let cool completely. Mix sugar and cream cheese well, then fold in nondairy whipped cream and spread on crust.

title: chicken potato casserole
directions: Combine margarine and cracker crumbs, set aside.
In a large greased casserole dish layer in the following order: potatoes, carrots, onion and chicken.
Make 2 layers.
Combine soup and milk.
Pour over top.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, corn syrup, salt, whiskey and vanilla.
Stir well.

title: rutabaga casserole
directions: Cover rutabaga with water.
Cook until tender, drain and mash. Add the remaining ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole. Set in a pan of hot water. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: spicy chocolate bars(large recipe)
directions: Cream shortening and sugars until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients; add chocolate chips.
Spread into ungreased pans, 1 (9 x 13-inch) and 1 (10 x 15-inch).
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.
Cut into bars.
Cool slightly.
While still warm, remove from pans.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together sugars, eggs, milk, flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add apples.
Bake in floured and greased dish. Sprinkle with pecans and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: easy beef burgundy
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and bake for 4 hours in a 250° oven.
Serve with noodles.

title: pineapple cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
If there's not enough juice, add water to make 1 cup.
Heat juice to boiling and add sugar, salt, beaten egg and cornstarch.
Cook until thick; add the butter.
Let cool.
Add nuts, cheese, pineapple and whipped topping.

title: creamy nachos
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain well.
Add beans.
Simmer for a few minutes on low flame.
Add grated cheese.
Heat until melted. Put Fritos on plate.
Top with meat mixture, lettuce, tomatoes and green onions.

title: mud pie
directions: Place desired amount of soil in a bucket.
Add water slowly, stirring until mixture reaches desired consistency.
Use spoons, forks, knives and containers of various shapes to create "fun food".

title: how to make confectioners sugar
directions: Process in food processor on High for 2 minutes.
Store in airtight container.

title: doug's authentic maryland crab cakes
directions: In a bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Knead with your hands until mixture stays together.
Make into patties.
Spray a baking pan with PAM.
Broil until golden brown, turning once.
Do not overcook.
Makes 6 to 8 crab cakes, depending on size that you prefer.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook raisins in boiling water to cover for 5 minutes; drain. Reserve 6 teaspoons liquid.
Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Add salt, soda and spices to flour; mix with oatmeal.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with raisin juice.
Add dates and raisins.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.

title: haystacks
directions: Mix ingredients and drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: tuna cones
directions: You will need an ice cream scoop and a bowl.

title: zesty spinach soup
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Empty bag into a 1 1/2qt. mizing bowl.
Stir in all the seasonings, mint leaves, and scallions while the spinach is still hot.

title: bachelor buttons
directions: Mix as listed.
Roll into balls.
Press with fork.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Brown ground beef.
Add tomato paste, sauce, water, wine, oregano, sugar, salt and pepper. Simmer for several hours.
Whip an egg and add to Ricotta.
Layer noodles, meat sauce, Ricotta and Mozzarella in large deep lasagne pan.
Top with Mozzarella and Parmesan.
Can be frozen.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: cinnamon pull-apart bread
directions: Melt stick of butter in saucepan.
Mix cup of sugar with cinnamon and pecans.
Pour 1/2 of melted butter in a Bundt pan. Roll 1 package of frozen yeast rolls in butter, then in the sugar mixture and drop in Bundt pan.
Cover pan with a towel and set in refrigerator for 10 to 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and remove from pan.
Mix powdered sugar with milk and drizzle over bread.
Great at breakfast.

title: ople's cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on box.
Bake in two 9-inch layer or three 8-inch layer pans, greased and floured.

title: italian green beans
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook for about 20 minutes on low heat or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: gypsy rabbit
directions: Shake rabbit pieces, several at a time, in paper or plastic bag with flour, pepper, salt and parsley.
Saute onion and garlic in olive oil or butter in heavy frypan until soft.
Then, piling the onions and garlic to one side, brown the rabbit.
Pour in boiling water to cover; add rice, seasoned salt and paprika. Cover tightly and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Wash and cut unpeeled zucchini and peeled onions in very thin slices into crock or bowl.
Cover with water and add salt.
Let stand 1 hour; drain.
Mix remaining ingredients; bring to a boil. Pour over zucchini and onion.
Let stand 1 hour.
Bring to a boil and cook 3 minutes.
Pack in 3 hot sterilized pint jars and seal. Process 5 minutes.

title: fire house meatballs
directions: In a 2-quart bowl, combine ground beef, cornflakes, evaporated milk, onions, chili sauce, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and hot pepper sauce; mix well.
With wet hands, shape mixture into 16 meatballs.
Place meatballs in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 400° oven 20 minutes, or until lightly browned on the outside and cooked medium on the inside.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Stew the chicken.
Cool and bone.
But chicken into small pieces and place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix soup, milk and 1/4 cup broth.
Pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing mix, 1 cup broth and butter; put mixture on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (1/2 hour covered with foil and 1/2 hour uncovered).

title: baked fish and vegetables
directions: Put the carrots, celery, onions, garlic and milk into casserole.
Have the fish cleaned and dip into melted butter. Place fish over vegetables and season with salt and pepper.
Mix the bread crumbs with remaining butter and spread over the top. Bake in moderate oven, tightly covered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Use 2-quart casserole.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with the peel on. When done, cut in small pieces. Chop the remaining vegetables and eggs; add to the potatoes. Mix in the Salad Dressing. (Miracle Whip or mayonnaise may be used instead of the Salad Dressing.)

title: banana cream pie
directions: Scald milk.
Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add hot milk slowly.
Cook 20 minutes.
Beat egg yolks and add slowly.
Cool and add vanilla.
Put in pie crust after adding sliced bananas. Top with whipped cream.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain off fat.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
(High 4 hours.)

title: cake topping
directions: Beat and mix ingredients.
Spread on cake while warm.
Let cool before cutting cake.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Put zucchini, onions and peppers through food grinder.
Mix well with 5 tablespoons salt.
Let stand overnight.

title: rice balls
directions: Stir vinegar, sugar and salt over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Soak carrot and celery mixture in vinegar-sugar solution an hour or so.
Squeeze out excess liquid.
Pour vinegar mixture evenly over hot rice in a flat pan and mix.
Dip hands in cold water, to ease the rice handling.
With about 1/4 cup of rice in your hands, pat into half sphere.
Stuff with 1/2 teaspoon carrot-celery mixture and then "close the ball."
Squeeze tightly to shape the ball and set on platter or cookie sheet to cool. Soaked salted plums or other delicacies can also be used for the centers.
Refrigerate and serve when cooled.
Makes about 20 rice balls.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chips and almond bark together until melted. Mix in peanuts and drop on wax paper.

title: bohemian spareribs
directions: Cut spareribs into individual servings.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix caraway seed with sauerkraut and place in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Arrange onion on top of sauerkraut and pour tomatoes on top.
Place spareribs on top.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except the stuffing mix; toss lightly to mix well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle herb stuffing mix over top, covering evenly.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Halfway into cooking time, gently push down herb stuffing mix with a wooden spoon so that it stays moist.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: marinated chicken(serves 1)
directions: Combine 1/2 package of chicken soup, pepper and garlic powder, then marinate chicken for about 20 minutes.
Cook in frying pan until almost done.
Dissolve remaining chicken in water, then pour over chicken.
Cook until sauce becomes thick.

title: stir 2 go salad
directions: Empty dry gelatin into bowl.
Stir in cottage cheese and crushed pineapple.
Carefully stir in mandarin orange slices (try not to tear).
Fold in whipped topping and refrigerate until serving time.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 6 to 8. Any flavor gelatin may be used.

title: chocolate pixies
directions: In large saucepan, melt margarine and chocolate over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Lightly spoon flour into cup.
Stir in remaining ingredients except powdered sugar.
Blend well.
Chill dough for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Wash figs.
Mix sugar and figs; bring to a boil.
Add lemon juice; boil for 12 minutes.
Add the jello; boil for 3 minutes. Put into hot, boiled jars and seal.

title: greens
directions: Wash green thoroughly.
Wash ham hocks.
In a large pot, place greens and ham hocks; add enough water to completely cover them. Cook about 2 hours or until desired tenderness.
Stir occasionally during cooking time.
Add hot peppers (optional).
Season to taste.

title: alamo fajita salad
directions: Heat salad shells according to directions.

title: better than anything cake
directions: Bake cake according to sheet cake directions on box.
Boil pineapple and sugar for 4 minutes.
Leaving cake in pan, pour pineapple over it.
Mix pudding as directed and spread over cake. Spread Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Top with coconut.
Chill before serving.

title: oriental vegetable stir-fry
directions: In 2-quart microwave casserole dish, blend Italian dressing, soy sauce, brown sugar and ginger.
Add remaining ingredients and toss to coat.
Microwave, uncovered, at High for 6 minutes or until crisp-tender.

title: fiesta corn
directions: Cook onion in
margarine, then blend in flour.	Stir in Velveeta cheese
and
tomatoes;
cook
until the cheese melts. Add corn, pepper
and
salt.
Continue	to
cook for another 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together, shape into patties, cook on medium hot skillet turning once until brown on both sides.

title: zucchini puree
directions: Saute onion in oleo until tender.
Add all ingredients except parsley.
Cook 5 minutes or until zucchini is tender.
Pour into blender, add parsley and puree.
Cover and watch out for leakage, it's hot!
Serve hot or cold.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in tube pan.

title: chicken crunch
directions: In a shallow dish, combine 1/3 cup soup and 1/4 cup milk.
Set aside.
On waxed paper, lightly coat chicken with flour.
Dip in soup mixture on another piece of waxed paper. Coat chicken with stuffing.

title: rice dressing
directions: Brown ground meat with white and green onions, garlic and 1 tablespoon cayenne and bell pepper and seasons of salt or your choice.
Drain grease if necessary after browning.
Add chicken broth and Kitchen Bouquet and bring to a boil.
Simmer on low heat for about 45 minutes.
During simmering, stir occasionally.
Then add cooked rice, mixing in thoroughly and more salt, pepper and Accent to taste, if needed.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli about 4 minutes and drain.
Add all ingredients. Pour in pan and put cornflake crumbs on top.
Bake at about 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together until mixture is smooth and creamy, about 4 minutes.
Pour into two loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rich and creamy macaroni salad
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Combine macaroni, shrimp, crabmeat and seafood salad together and mix in salad dressing.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix altogether.
Chill and store in the refrigerator.

title: creole sauce(this is the best.)
directions: Saute onion, garlic and green pepper lightly in vegetable or olive oil in a deep skillet or wok.
Add the remaining ingredients and cook for 15 minutes.
Sauce may be simmered longer but should cover it while doing so.
Serve over stuffed pepper, noodles, eggplant, rice or seafood.
Yields 5 cups.

title: enchilada dish
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add beans; mix well and set aside.
In medium bowl, mix soup and sauce with 1 can water; set aside.
In an 11 x 13-inch baking dish, place a layer of tortillas.
Cover with a layer of meat mixture; sprinkle with cheese.
Pour part of the soup mixture over this layer.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Cover and bake in a 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Before serving, sprinkle liberally with lettuce. Pass dressing of your choice.

title: linguini-basil salad
directions: Cook first three ingredients per package directions.
Drain and cool.
Add tomato, basil, onions and olive oil.
Chill for 1 hour and serve on lettuce leaf.
Serves 4.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cool.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: Mix Bisquick and water; knead 20 times.
Pat into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown meat and drain grease.
Saute meat with onion, garlic and salt.
Mix in tomato sauce and seasoning.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes, adding a little water if necessary.
Pour mixture over the dough.
Add mushrooms and pepper; top with cheese.
Bake about 20 minutes in a 425° preheated oven.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling
water
and add pineapple and blueberry pie filling.
Put in
refrigerator and let set until firm.
Mix the cream
cheese
(softened),
sour
cream, sugar, vanilla and nuts. Spread atop the jello mixture.

title: cherry ice cream
directions: Scale 1 quart milk.
Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add beaten eggs.
Add this mixture to milk and cook until it coats a spoon. Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Add vanilla.
Let cool.
Add evaporated milk and half and half.
Add cherry pie filling and freeze.

title: pizza fondue(a fun kids meal)
directions: Brown onion and meat on high.
Reduce heat to medium.
Mix cornstarch and seasonings into pizza sauce and add sauce to mixture.
Stir well.
When mixture thickens and bubbles, add cheese by thirds, mixing well.
Cut up chunks of French or sourdough bread.
Stick these cubes on a fork and dip in.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Mix together.
Drop on a cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 10 minutes; then turn down to 325° for 20 to 35 minutes, just until golden brown.

title: tuna surprise
directions: Mix the ingredients well and serve with crackers.

title: beef dip with pumpernickel
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread.
Cut center out of loaf and fill with dip.
Use center of loaf to dip into beef dip.

title: jam cake
directions: Soak raisins in pineapple overnight.
Sift together dry ingredients.
In large mixing bowl, cream butter and eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add jam, butter, brown sugar and milk; blend well.
Add dry ingredients and mix well. Stir in raisins and pineapple mixture and nuts.
Bake in two greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until tests done.
Cool 10 minutes on wire rack; frost with following icing.

title: ground meat recipe
directions: Cook the ground meat with the tomato sauce, bell pepper and onion, then drain off grease.
Then put a layer of meat in the bottom of the casserole bowl, then cover it with cheese; repeat twice (2 times).
Cheese should be on top.
Then spread the biscuits as flat as possible on the top.
Then cook until brown.

title: hamburger dinner
directions: Brown the beef, Tater Tots and onion.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Pour the soups over the mixture.
Add salt and pepper. Rinse out soup cans with water and pour over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken casserole deluxe
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients together.
Place in casserole. Sprinkle with nuts.
Top with bread cubes.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour and cook until bubbling (1 to 2 minutes).
Slowly stir in stock, whisking constantly.
Heat to a near boil until soup thickens.
Add broccoli and half and half, then add cheese slowly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar and egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Stir in alternately with 1/2 cup milk.
Fill greased muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Roll in (or brush on) melted butter, then roll in cinnamon and sugar.

title: snicker's cake
directions: Put 1/2 of the batter in a prepared 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels with milk and margarine.
Pour over the cake.
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour remaining cake batter on top.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°, then 20 minutes at 325°.

title: crab dip
directions: Saute onions and crabmeat in butter.
Add garlic powder and salt.
Add crab boil.
Mix and let cook about 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese in mixture and pour into mold.
Chill.

title: flounder fillets with champagne
directions: In a large skillet combine flour with the champagne, add the salt and half of the butter.
Bring to a boil on medium heat, constantly stirring.
Add the 1/2 bouillon cube.
Add the flounder fillets and let simmer for about 3 minutes, then turn them and cook for another 3 to 4 minutes or until tender.

When ready move them on a dish, thicken the sauce by cooking it a little longer in the skillet, then remove it from the heat, add the remaining butter and then pour it on the fillets and serve immediately.

title: broccoli chowder
directions: Use 5-gallon pot.
Fill with water to handle level.
Add butter, chicken base and broccoli.
When broccoli is tender, add ham and cheese.
Stir. Mix together the flour, milk and water. Use a whip and beat until smooth.
When broccoli is tender, add the flour mixture and stir.
Heat to simmer and cook until thick and creamy.
Check for flavor and add more chicken base if needed.

title: low-fat bran muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and cinnamon in large bowl.
Mix cereal, milk and sugar in another bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in egg and applesauce.
Stir into flour mixture until moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Spoon into greased muffin pan (each 2/3 full).
Bake 18 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Makes 12.

title: lazy day lasagne
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare noodles according to directions, drain.
Combine sauce and oregano.
In a greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish alternate layers of noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and sauce, ending with sauce.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: mahogany meringue drops
directions: Beat egg whites to soft peaks.
Gradually add sugar, vanilla and salt, beating until stiff.
Fold in pecans.
Drop from teaspoon onto aluminum foil lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 18 to 20 minutes. Cool thoroughly before removing from foil. Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: green beans with bacon
directions: In a large skillet, cook bacon and onion over medium heat until bacon is crisp and onion is tender.

title: pecan pie number 2
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Blend in syrup and pecans.
Makes 1 large deep dish or 2 small pies.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: corn and ham casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Add 3/4 cheese.
Mix well. Add ham chunks.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or more.
Take out and add remaining cheese.
Let cool and enjoy.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly shortening and sugar.
Stir in milk or cream and vanilla or lemon flavoring.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Chill dough.
Roll very thin (1/16-inch).
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake until delicately brown.
Bake at 325°.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread as per instructions.
Let cool.
Crumble cooled cornbread into bowl and add tomato, bell pepper, onion and salad dressing.
Cool and serve.
Great for picnics.

title: texas cake
directions: Boil margarine, cocoa and water and remove from heat.
Add sifted sugar, flour and baking soda and mix.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in a 12 x 18 x 1-inch pan in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix the beans and soup together in 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Top with the onions. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon in large skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon; drain off fat, measure fat and return 1/4 cup to skillet.
Add onions and celery.
Saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Blend in flour.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Stir in sugar, salt, pepper and bacon.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pastry shell 8 minutes; remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Cut 6 slices cheese food into pieces; set aside.
In large skillet brown meat; pour off fat.
Add tomato sauce, green pepper, onion and bouillon; cook and stir until bouillon dissolves.
Remove from heat; stir in eggs, flour and cheese food pieces.
Turn into prepared shell. Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until hot.
Arrange remaining cheese food slices on top.
Return to oven 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese food begins to melt.
Garnish with tomato and lettuce if desired. Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: jumpin' frog legs
directions: Skin the frog legs first, then wash'em and cut off the feet. Soak'em for an hour or so in salt water. Beat an egg or two and season frog legs with salt and pepper. Dip'em in the cornmeal, then in the eggs and again in the cornmeal.
Deep fry in hot fat. I like to dip'em in melted butter, but ya don't gotta'.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, salt, butter and syrup.
Add pecans and pour mixture into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until brown and center is firm when pie is shaken.
Makes an 8-inch pie.

title: stuffed green bell peppers
directions: Blanche peppers 5 minutes in boiling water.
Mix together remaining ingredients except tomato sauce and stuff peppers with mixture.
Place in covered casserole and pour tomato sauce over them.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook and drain sweet potatoes and mix rest of ingredients. Pour into 4 pie crusts.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.
Makes 4 pies.

title: katie gooch wilmot's corn pudding
directions: Combine and top with butter and 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg.
Bake about 40 minutes at 350° (more or less according to oven).

title: spinach and artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Add salt and pepper to taste. Put in shallow baking pan. Top with grated Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mother's mess
directions: In a large roasting pan, mix all ingredients (except parsley) together, sprinkle parsley on top and bake in a 300° oven for 3 hours.

title: whole wheat soft pretzels
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
(If water is too hot, yeast will be killed and will not work.)
Add all-purpose flour, sugar and salt; beat on low speed until moistened.
Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 3 minutes.
Stir in enough whole wheat flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic, about 5 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl; turn greased side up.

title: summer salad
directions: Prepare macaroni according to directions on package; drain. Add Veg-All, tuna, cheese, onion and pickles.
Mix remaining ingredients and toss until macaroni mixture.
Chill.

title: thumbprint pastries
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Dip both sides of each biscuit into melted butter, then in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Make deep thumbprint in center of each roll.
Fill with 1 teaspoon jam. Bake in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 10 pastries.

title: macaroni pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 10 or 9-inch square pan.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain.
In large skillet, brown ground beef with celery; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and mushrooms and simmer 15 minutes.
In large bowl, combine cooked macaroni, eggs and 1/3 cup Parmesan cheese and toss lightly.
Press mixture in pan, forming a crust.
Pour meat over macaroni; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: sausage and egg brunch
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Pour meat and grease into casserole dish.
In separate dish, whip eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over meat mixture.
Cube 3 slices of bread and lay over top of meat and egg mixture.
Grate cheese and sprinkle over top of mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 375° in oven for 35 to 45 minutes (until egg mixture is at scrambled egg consistency you prefer).
Remove from oven.
Let sit 5 minutes before serving.

title: quick fudge
directions: Melt drops in microwave-safe dish just until they are smooth enough to blend.
Immediately add the peanut butter and beat together.
Immediately drop by teaspoon onto buttered wax paper. Must be done quickly.
It sets fast.
You can use chunky peanut butter if you like nutty fudge!

title: butterscotch yams
directions: Place yams in single layer in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Bake in 325° oven 15 minutes.

title: honey-citrus cooler
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags.
Steep for 5 minutes. Remove tea bags.
Stir in honey.
Add cold water and fruit juices. Chill for 1 hour.
Put ice cubes in tall glass.
Add soda to tea mixture.
Pour over ice cubes.

title: 3 layer dessert
directions: Crumble real well.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Press with hand.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine mashed or chopped sweet potatoes, salt, Molly McButter and brown sugar.
Pour into baking dish and mix in marshmallows and pineapples.
Top with cornflakes and bake for 25 minutes.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cornmeal.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add the 3 liquids.
Add lemon rind.
Pour into pie shells and bake for 35 minutes or until set at 350°.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs one at a time.
Add soda to sour cream. Add cream and flour to creamed mixture alternating.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Mix thoroughly. Bake in tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours. Do not open oven while baking.
Ice with favorite icing or leave plain.

title: eagle brand pineapple pie
directions: Mix Eagle Brand, cream cheese and lemon juice.
Spread over crumb crusts in dishes.
Chill.
Combine pineapple, Cool Whip and nuts; spread over cheese layer.
Chill thoroughly.
Makes 2 pies.

title: german chocolate cream cheese cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Butter or grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and pour cake mix into pan.
Sprinkle coconut and nuts on top of cake mixture.
In a separate bowl mix margarine, softened cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour this mixture on top of cake mixture.
Bake 50 minutes at 325°.

title: ms. eva's meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together and place in loaf pan.

title: spinach salad
directions: Fry the 2 strips of bacon crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Tear spinach; add bacon and 1 to 2 hard-boiled eggs, sliced.
May add drained bean sprouts, fried Chinese noodles and water chestnuts. Toss with dressing.
Garnish with sliced or whole black olives and some of the hard-boiled egg slices.

title: yummy cake
directions: Combine all cake ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and frost immediately with frosting.

title: snappy cheese sticks
directions: Prepare pie crust mix according to package directions thoroughly mixing in shredded cheese, mustard and paprika until mixture forms a ball.
Roll dough on lightly floured surface to 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
With pastry wheel or knife, cut into sticks 1/2-inch wide and 4-inches long.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake in hot oven (425°) for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 4 dozen sticks.

title: cran-apple oatmeal(sugar-free!)
directions: Combine milk, cranberries, cinnamon and salt in medium saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally. Add oats and apple. Simmer, uncovered, 5-6 minutes for old-fashioned oats or 1-2 minutes for quick oats, stirring occasionally until most of the liquid has been absorbed. Remove from heat. Stir in Equal, nuts and vanilla.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients; put in cake pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Thaw cauliflower and broccoli and drain.
Pour into a bowl, creamed corn, whole kernel corn, soup and cheese.
Mix all together and bake 35 minutes.
Put croutons mixed in melted butter on top.
Cook uncovered at 350°.

title: carrots and celery
directions: In a heavy skillet heat oil over high heat.
Add carrots, salt, sugar and water.
On medium heat, covered, cook 7 minutes. Uncover, add celery and cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Vegetables should be tender-crisp.

title: kerosene pickles
directions: Wash and dry enough cucumbers for six sterilized one-quart jars.
In the bottom of each jar, place a portion of dill, 1 hot pepper, 1 clove of garlic, 1 slice of onion, 1 teaspoon of whole spices, a small lump of alum and cucumbers.
In a saucepan, combine the vinegar, water and salt.
Let the mixture get to a rolling boil, then pour into the jars.
Seal immediately.
Makes six quarts.

title: apple walnut crisp
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Spread apple filling evenly in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Sprinkle half of cinnamon over apple filling. Pour dry cake mix evenly over apples so it covers the entire apple filling. Sprinkle remaining 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon over cake mix. Sprinkle walnuts over top; drizzle melted butter over entire pan. Bake in 350° oven until top is golden brown, about 55 minutes. Remove from oven and cool for 10 minutes. Top with vanilla ice cream, if desired.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In a double boiler, put peaches and stick of margarine.
Heat until this comes to a boil.
Mix in bowl the flour, milk and sugar; stir until smooth.
Add this mixture to the peaches and margarine. Stir and pour into long casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: earl's 4-way chili
directions: Cook first 11 ingredients slowly for 4 to 5 hours.
Add salt 15 minutes before taking up.
Pour into pan to cool.
Will keep a long time.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: old-time sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add all ingredients except flour; beat well.
Blend in flour; mix well.
Chill 2 hours.
Roll out on floured wax paper 1/4-inch thickness and cut with cookie cutters. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool and frost.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil; simmer for 1 hour.

title: german's chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, vanilla, butter flavor and buttermilk.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to other. Mix well.
Add chocolate that has been softened in double boiler or microwave.
Blend well.
Bake in well-greased and floured Bundt pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Remove from pan while still hot.
Cover in tight container until cold.

title: parmesan party rounds
directions: Combine mayonnaise, parmesan cheese and pimento in a bowl. Beat egg whites until stiff, not dry.
Fold egg whites into cheese mixture.
Spoon onto bread, place on baking sheet.
Broil for four (4) minutes or until golden brown.

title: scallops
directions: Blend the ingredients together.
Pour over the scallops. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Place under the broiler 3 inches from heat.
Broil until done.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; layer meat on top of noodles in a 9 x 13-inch pan or glass dish.
Next, layer bell pepper and onion on top of ground beef.
Dice up cheese, layer on top of bell pepper and onion.
Add sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Repeat layers 2 to 3 more times; bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 to 4 layers.

title: baby pot roast
directions: Peel carrots.
Score steaks and spread with mustard.
Cut steaks into 4-inch strips.
Cut carrots the same length.
Roll meat around carrots and close with toothpicks.
Brown meat and carrots in oil.
Drain peas (saving the liquid).
Add catsup to liquid from peas to make 1 cup.
Pour mixture over meat, cover and simmer until carrots are tender (45 minutes).
Serve with peas and mashed potatoes.

title: can do chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour oblong pan 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Combine all ingredients.
Blend on low speed 6 minutes. Pour into pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans in water to cover overnight.
Rinse.
Cover with water in heavy pot such as Dutch oven.
Add ham bone, fat trimmed off, and other ingredients, except sausage.
Bring to a boil. Simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add sausage steamed in skillet, drained and fried.
Just before serving remove bay leaf and add a little fresh parsley.
For added thickness, remove about 1 cup beans from pot.
Mash thoroughly and return to mixture. Serve over rice.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Crumble 10 pieces bacon.
Set aside.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Alternate a layer of the cheese, bacon, onion and pepper mixture, and mushrooms on each pastry shell.
In a small bowl blend together lightly beaten eggs, milk, flour, salt, Worcestershire sauce and basil.
Pour half the mixture over each pie.
Bake at 375° for 35-40 minutes.
It is done when knife comes out clean.

title: jambalaya
directions: Combine and saute the first three ingredients and set aside. Combine the fourth and fifth ingredients and saute, then set aside.
Combine final ingredients until thick.
Mix all ingredients together and heat thoroughly.
Cook rice and mix with other ingredients.

title: lime cheese cake
directions: Sprinkle crumbs in bottom of pan.
Combine jello and water. Stir until dissolved.
Pour into blender.
Add cream cheese and cottage cheese. Blend until smooth. Fold into Cool Whip.
Pour over graham cracker crumbs and chill 4 hours. Can use sugar-free and fat-free substitutions.
Use an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: carrot gold cake
directions: Sift first 5 dry ingredients together, then add sugar, oil and eggs and mix well.
Blend in thoroughly, carrots, pineapple, nuts and coconut.
This bakes a large cake or 3 greased and floured 9-inch round layers.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes for layers.

title: beef stew with confetti dumplings
directions: Brown onions and mushrooms in oil; set aside.
In a large stew pot, brown beef in small amount of oil.
Add the 2 cans of beef broth and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Mix flour and water and add to stew to thicken.
Add onions, mushrooms and peas.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add all other ingredients in order and mix thoroughly.
Bake in floured and greased layer cake pans at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Steep tea in 1-quart hot water for 20 minutes.
Add sugar, fruit juices, spices and remaining quart of water.
Bring to boiling point and serve hot.

title: rhubarb nut bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar. Beat in eggs one at a time. Add vanilla and sifted dry ingredients. Stir in nuts. Pour into loaf pan.

title: pepper steak
directions: Combine cornstarch, soy sauce, sherry and garlic.
Cut steak into thin crosswise slices. Add to soy mixture.
Heat oil and add peppers.
Stir-fry until almost tender. Stir in beef mixture, salt and pepper.
Cook until beef is brown, stirring frequently. Add tomatoes and cook until tender.
Serve over rice.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into punch cups with a small candy cane as stirrer.

title: chicken dorito casserole
directions: Heat both soups together. Heat cheese, rotel and onions together. Boil noodles. Mix all above ingredients together in a casserole bowl and cook in oven on 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and add water to cover.
Let stand all night.
Drain well and rinse and drain again.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil; add the zucchini mixture.
Bring to a simmer.
When hot, pour into jars.
Makes 7 pints.
Tastes just like the store bought relish.

title: white nut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed, except fold 1/3 cup finely chopped nuts into batter just before pouring into pan.

title: pistachio ambrosia
directions: Mix the chunky and crushed pineapple with all the liquid together and sprinkle the powdered pistachio pudding on top. Let this stand for 3 to 5 minutes. Mix the nuts and coconut together in a separate bowl.
Then add to the pineapple and pudding mixture. Blend in the whipped topping, thawed if you are using frozen, and marshmallows. Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Serve well with chilled.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add onion.
Beat the milk and egg together and add to dry ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep fat heated to 375°. When they float, they are done.

title: nettie strickland's cake dumplings
directions: Mix all together except berries.
Heat berries in saucepan. Drop dough on berries.
Cook 15 minutes, slowly with lid on. Serve warm.
Top with whipped cream.

title: mexican chow
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Saute onion in butter or margarine until soft.
Add ground beef.
Cook until brown, stirring occasionally.
Combine meat mixture with spaghetti, seasonings, kidney beans and tomato puree.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot in bowls.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 9 x 13 inch glass pan.
Mix first four ingredients and pour over chicken.
Place ginger slices around glass dish.
Cook at 375° covered for 1/2 hour.
Then bake for another 1/2 hour uncovered.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Dice onion and place in pot with sausage. Brown on low flame. Pour in tomatoes and simmer on low flame. Stir frequently, cook to desired thickness. Add water if sauce is too thick. Season with oregano, salt and pepper to taste.

title: italian rice
directions: Wash rice according to directions.
Heat fat in 10-inch heavy skillet.
Add rice, ground beef and onion.
Cook, stirring frequently until meat and rice are brown and onion is soft.
Add green peppers and celery; cook low about 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until rice is perfectly tender.
Stir occasionally. Makes 5 servings.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook and strain apples as for sauce. Mix in sugar and spices. Put in large pan. Cook down in oven at 300° for about 1 hour. Then at 225° for 8 to 10 hours. I cook it overnight. Put in hot jars and seal.

title: artichoke chili dip
directions: Combine the chopped artichoke hearts, chili peppers, cheese and mayonnaise.
Pour into 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes
or until heated through.
Serve warm with chips or bread sticks.
Makes 2 2/3 cups.

title: fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken thoroughly; drain; season with salt and pepper. Let stand overnight or 2-3 hours before fixing. Heat cooking oil in fairly deep pan slowly. Be sure it is hot before you put the chicken in. Dip chicken in a bowl or pan with half and half, then place chicken in bag with flour and shake well. Put chicken in hot oil, cooking on medium heat 15 minutes on each side until golden brown and well done.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, salt and water.
Cook over medium heat until sugar dissolves, stirring constantly.
Cook, without stirring, to firm ball stage.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour half over syrup; beat constantly.
Cook remainder of syrup until soft crack, then add syrup to other mixture, stirring constantly. Continue beating until candy holds shape.
Add vanilla and nuts. Drop from spoon onto foil.
Makes about 2 pounds.

title: toffee
directions: Lightly oil a cookie sheet and spread chopped nuts over oil. Melt butter in non-stick skillet.
Add brown sugar and stir well. Boil mixture over medium heat, stirring constantly, for 7 minutes. Pour over nuts immediately.
Pour milk chocolate chips over toffee; place cookie sheet or lid on top until chocolate melts. Spread chocolate evenly.
Allow to cool then break into pieces.

title: crock-pot stew beef
directions: Do not add any water.
This recipe makes a good thick rich gravy.

title: meat o's
directions: Do not add salt.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook the spaghetti or vermicelli in salted water until almost done (6 to 8 minutes).
Blanch in cold water; drain.
Add the Italian dressing and red wine.
Add the garlic powder; chop and add bell pepper, tomatoes and onion.
Season to taste with Salad Supreme (will need quite a bit).
Marinate in refrigerator at least 2 to 3 hours.
Better if allowed to stand overnight.

title: blueberry jello
directions: Boil 2 cups water and add jello.
Mix well.
Add pie filling. Whip sour cream, then add to jello mixture.
You can also add some more fresh or frozen blueberries.
